{"title_page": "The Favourite", "text_new": "{{distinguish|The Favorite (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|2018 film by Yorgos Lanthimos}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Favourite\n| image          = The Favourite.png\n| caption        = UK theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Yorgos Lanthimos]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Ceci Dempsey\n* [[Ed Guiney]]\n* Lee Magiday\n* Yorgos Lanthimos\n}}\n| writer         = {{Plainlist|\n* Deborah Davis\n* [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]]\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Olivia Colman]]\n* [[Emma Stone]]\n* [[Rachel Weisz]]\n}}<!--PER BILLING BLOCK ON THE POSTER. Statement in documentation: \"Names as they are listed in the billing block of the poster for the film's original theatrical release\".-->\n| cinematography = [[Robbie Ryan (cinematographer)|Robbie Ryan]]\n| editing        = [[Yorgos Mavropsaridis]]\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* Scarlet Films<ref name=insight>{{cite web|url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181021085213/http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archive-date=21 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Element Pictures]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Arcana<ref name=insight/>\n* [[Film4 Productions]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Waypoint Entertainment<ref name=insight/>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]]<ref name=insight/>\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|8|30|[[75th Venice International Film Festival|Venice]]|2018|11|23|United States|2019|1|1|United Kingdom and Ireland|ref1=<ref name=\"Filmoria.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/the-favourite-film-review-venice-film-festival/|title=The Favourite \u2013 Film Review (Venice Film Festival 2018)|publisher=Filmoria|access-date=18 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918194137/https://www.filmoria.co.uk/the-favourite-film-review-venice-film-festival/|archive-date=18 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| runtime        = 120 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2018/lineup/venezia-75-competition/favourite|title=The Favourite|website=[[Venice International Film Festival]] 2018|accessdate=25 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725183930/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2018/lineup/venezia-75-competition/favourite|archive-date=25 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = {{Plainlist|\n* United Kingdom<ref name=allmovie/>\n* Ireland<ref name=allmovie>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/the-favourite-v698473|title=The Favourite (2018)|work=[[AllMovie]]|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713073928/https://www.allmovie.com/movie/the-favourite-v698473|archive-date=13 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* United States<ref name=allmovie/>\n}}\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $15 million<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n| gross          = $95.9 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |title=The Favourite (2018) |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=thefavourite.htm |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |access-date=12 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190202214757/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=thefavourite.htm |archive-date=2 February 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| border         = no\n}}\n'''''The Favourite''''' is a 2018 [[historical drama|period]] [[black comedy]] film directed by [[Yorgos Lanthimos]], and written by Deborah Davis and [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]]. It is a co-production of the United Kingdom, Ireland, and the United States. Set in early 18th century England, the film's plot examines the relationship between two cousins, [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Sarah, Duchess of Marlborough]] ([[Rachel Weisz]]) and [[Abigail Masham, Baroness Masham|Abigail Masham]] ([[Emma Stone]]), who are vying to be Court favourites of [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]] ([[Olivia Colman]]). [[Principal photography]] lasted from March to May 2017, taking place at [[Hatfield House]] in [[Hertfordshire]] and at [[Hampton Court Palace]] in Richmond, [[Surrey]].\n\n''The Favourite'' premiered on 30 August 2018 at the [[75th Venice International Film Festival]], where it won the [[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]] and the [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]] for Colman. It was theatrically released in the United States on 23 November 2018 by [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]], and in the United Kingdom and Ireland on 1 January 2019. The film became a box office success, grossing $95 million worldwide on a $15 million budget.\n\n''The Favourite'' was praised for its screenplay, Lanthimos's direction, cinematography, editing, costume design, production values, music, and the lead actresses' performances. It received [[List of accolades received by The Favourite|numerous awards and nominations]], including ten [[91st Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nominations (tying ''[[Roma (2018 film)|Roma]]'' for the most nominations of any film that year). ''The Favourite'' also won seven [[72nd British Academy Film Awards|BAFTA Awards]] (including [[BAFTA Award for Outstanding British Film|Best British Film]] and [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]] for Weisz) and ten [[British Independent Film Awards 2018|British Independent Film Awards]]. Colman won Best Actress at the [[Academy Award for Best Actress|Academy Awards]], the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Comedy or Musical|Golden Globes]], and the [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|BAFTAs]]. The film was ranked by the [[American Film Institute]] as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2018#Top 10 Films|top ten films of 2018]]. The film also won eight [[European Film Awards]] including [[European Film Award for Best Film|Best Film]], [[European Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]] and [[European Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Colman.\n\n==Plot==\n[[File:Sarah, Duchess of Marlborough by Jervas.jpg|thumb|left|upright|[[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough]].]]\n\nIn 1711, England is at [[War of the Spanish Succession|war with France]]. [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]] is in frail health; she shows little interest in governing, preferring activities such as racing ducks and playing with her 17 rabbits, surrogates for the children she miscarried or lost in childhood. Her confidante, adviser, and furtive lover Sarah Churchill effectively rules the country through her influence over the Queen. Sarah's efforts to control Anne are undermined by [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Robert Harley]], the [[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]], who as a landowner argues against a doubling of property taxes proposed to fund the war.\n\n[[File:Abigail Masham portrait.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Abigail Masham, Baroness Masham]].]]\n\nAbigail Hill, Sarah's impoverished younger cousin, arrives in search of employment. Abigail's standing has been tainted by her father, who gambled her away in a game of [[whist]]. Abigail is forced to do menial work as a scullery maid in the palace. After seeing the Queen's [[gout]], Abigail forages for herbs and applies them to the Queen's inflamed legs. Sarah has Abigail whipped for entering the Queen's bedroom without permission but relents and appoints her [[Lady of the Bedchamber]] after realising the herbs have helped the Queen. Harley asks Abigail to spy on Sarah and the Queen, hoping to circumvent Sarah's authority. Abigail witnesses Sarah and the Queen having sex.\n\nWith Sarah focused on the war effort, Abigail kindles a friendship with Anne that becomes sexual. Sarah becomes aware of Abigail's machinations and attempts to send her away. Abigail drugs Sarah's tea, causing her to fall off her horse and be dragged unconscious on the ground. Sarah awakens in a brothel, battered from the fall. Anne, thinking Sarah has abandoned her to make her jealous, takes Abigail into her [[Favourite|favour]] and allows her to marry [[Samuel Masham, 1st Baron Masham|Colonel Masham]], reinstating Abigail's noble standing.\n\nWhen Sarah returns to court, she issues an ultimatum to Queen Anne: send Abigail away or Sarah will disclose her correspondence with Anne that details their sexual relationship. She tells Anne that Abigail does not love her and merely flatters her. Sarah, remorseful, burns the letters but Anne nevertheless sends her away from court. When Abigail, who has been promoted to [[Keeper of the Privy Purse]], presents what she claims is evidence Sarah had been embezzling money, Anne exiles Sarah and her husband from Britain.\n\nWith Sarah gone and her position secure, Abigail begins to neglect and ignore Anne while indulging in court society and openly having affairs. One day, while lounging in the Queen's chamber, Abigail abuses one of Anne's rabbits. Anne, now very sick, is awakened by the animal's distress cry. Finally realising Abigail's cruel nature, Anne forces herself out of bed and orders Abigail to massage her leg while gradually bearing down on Abigail's head with her hand.\n\n==Cast==\n<!--- Cast and order per tombstone closing credits, roles per closing credits scroll --->\n* [[Olivia Colman]] as [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]]\n* [[Emma Stone]] as [[Abigail Hill|Abigail]]\n* [[Rachel Weisz]] as [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Lady Sarah]]\n* [[Nicholas Hoult]] as [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Harley]]\n* [[Joe Alwyn]] as [[Samuel Masham, 1st Baron Masham|Masham]]\n* [[James Smith (actor)|James Smith]] as [[Sidney Godolphin, 1st Earl of Godolphin|Godolphin]]\n* [[Mark Gatiss]] as [[John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough|Lord Marlborough]]\n* [[Jenny Rainsford]] as Mae\n\n==Production==\n===Writing===\nDeborah Davis wrote the first draft of ''The Favourite'' in 1998. She had no prior screenwriting experience and studied screenwriting at night school. She took the draft, which was titled ''The Balance of Power,'' to producer [[Ceci Dempsey]], who responded enthusiastically.<ref name=\"AD_Davis\"/> Davis had little knowledge of Queen Anne and her relationships with Sarah Churchill and Abigail Masham; her research led her to the discovery of a \"female triangle\".<ref name=\"AD_Davis\">{{cite web|url=http://www.awardsdaily.com/2018/11/05/deborah-davis-talks-to-awards-daily-about-the-favourites-twenty-year-journey-to-the-big-screen/|title=Deborah Davis Talks To Awards Daily About The Favourite's Twenty Year Journey To The Big Screen|website=Awards Daily|first=Jazz|last=Tangcay|date=5 November 2018|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119051616/http://www.awardsdaily.com/2018/11/05/deborah-davis-talks-to-awards-daily-about-the-favourites-twenty-year-journey-to-the-big-screen/|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She studied letters written by Queen Anne, Sarah, and Abigail:\n\n{{quote|I did a lot of research and as it turns out, there is a wealth of original sources. You have historical accounts of the period. One of the best sources is [[Winston Churchill]] who wrote the story about his ancestor who was the Duke of Marlborough and he covers the female triangle and the relationship between Anne, Sarah and Abigail in his four-part biography. There are enormous amounts of sources out there. Another one was, of course, Sarah's memoir where she wrote about how she was replaced in the Queen's favour by Abigail and how Abigail had become the absolute favourite.<ref name=\"AD_Davis\" />}}\n\n''The Favourite'' is the first film Lanthimos directed with screenwriters Davis and McNamara. Lanthimos was attracted to Davis' and McNamara's script, and \"became acquainted with the three female characters who happened to be real people\".<ref name=\"colman\"/>  Lanthimos felt the story was interesting and also had a chance \"to create three complex female characters which is something you rarely see\".<ref name=\"colman\"/> Of her working relationship with Lanthimos, Dempsey said:\n\n{{quote|He has a very particular, contained view. And he reserves it and conserves it, deliberately. He's very intuitive on every level. Casting, yes. Even hiring the department, it's all the same process ... You're not going to talk him into anything ever, ever, ever, ever. Once you accept that, you have to intuit or inhale what he wants, but he's got a very particular contained view and you just need to go with it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-producer-directors-particular-vision-watch-1158810|title=Ceci Dempsey on Yorgos Lanthimos' \"Particular\" Vision for 'The Favourite'|website=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Ciara|last=McVey|date=7 November 2018|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119091900/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-producer-directors-particular-vision-watch-1158810|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n===Pre-production===\nProducer Ceci Dempsey, who read the first draft, said she was \"haunted\" by \"the passion, the survival instincts of these women, the manipulations and what they did to survive\".<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/> Dempsey had difficulty securing finance due to the script's lesbian content and the lack of male representation, which financers felt would be challenging to market. Almost a decade later, producer [[Ed Guiney]] obtained the script and was also attracted to the complex plot and relationships of the three women; he said, \"We didn't want to make just another British costume drama&nbsp;...&#0032;[we wanted] a story that felt contemporary and relevant and vibrant\u2014not something out of a museum\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n\nDuring this time, Guiney became acquainted with Lanthimos, whose film ''[[Dogtooth (film)|Dogtooth]]'' (2009) had received an [[Academy Award]] nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]. Guiney approached him with the prospect of directing the film. Lanthimos immediately became intrigued with the idea \"[t]hese three women possessed power that affected the lives of millions\"; at the same time he found the story to be \"intimate\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/> Lanthimos began working closely with screenwriter [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]] on \"freshening up\" the script. By 2013, the producers were receiving financing offers from several companies, including [[Film4 Productions]] and Waypoint Entertainment, which later worked on the film.<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/features/favourite-blows-up-metoo-gender-politics-love-triangle-1160665|title='The Favourite' Blows Up Gender Politics With the Year's Most Outrageous Love Triangle|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Tatiana|last=Siegel|date=14 November 2018|accessdate=14 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114174652/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/features/favourite-blows-up-metoo-gender-politics-love-triangle-1160665|archive-date=14 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, it was announced Lanthimos would direct the film from Deborah Davis and Tony McNamara's screenplay, which was described as \"a bawdy, acerbic tale of royal intrigue, passion, envy, and betrayal\".<ref name=\"wrap\"/> Ceci Dempsey, Ed Guiney, Lee Magiday and [[Andrew Lowe]] served as producers under their Scarlet Films and Element Pictures banners, respectively.<ref name=\"Jafaar\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/09/kate-winslet-emma-stone-olivia-colman-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-element-pictures-scarlet-queen-anne-1201548277/|title=Emma Stone & Olivia Colman In Talks To Board Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite'|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Ali|last=Jafaar|date=24 September 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417044525/http://deadline.com/2015/09/kate-winslet-emma-stone-olivia-colman-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-element-pictures-scarlet-queen-anne-1201548277/|archive-date=17 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On the film's lesbian-centric love triangle, Lanthimos said:\n\n{{quote|My instinct from the beginning was that I didn't want this to become an issue in the film, for us, like we're trying to make a point out of it&nbsp;... I didn't even want the characters in the film to be making an issue of it. I just wanted to deal with these three women as human beings. It didn't matter that there were relationships of the same gender. I stopped thinking about that very early on in the process.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-lesbian-love-triangle-1201999899/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos on the Lesbian Love Triangle of 'The Favourite': 'I Didn't Want This to Become an Issue'|website=[[IndieWire]]|first=Eric|last=Kohn|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215215/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-lesbian-love-triangle-1201999899/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nHe also elaborated on the \"positive\" effect the [[Me Too movement]] has had on the film: \"Because of the prevalent male gaze in cinema, women are portrayed as housewives, girlfriends&nbsp;... Our small contribution is we're just trying to show them as complex and wonderful and horrific as they are, like other human beings.\"<ref name=\"colman\"/>\n\n===Casting===\nCasting for ''The Favourite'' began in 2014 when Lanthimos contacted Colman.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/10-things-know-favourite-oscars-2019-1185846/item/stone-wants-a-sequel-follows-harleys-parliamentarian-story-oscars-10-things-know-best-picture-nomine-1186330|title=Oscars: 10 Things to Know About Best Picture Nominee 'The Favourite'|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Katherine|last=Schaffstall|date=22 February 2019}}</ref> By September 2015, it was announced Emma Stone, Olivia Colman and [[Kate Winslet]] had been cast to portray Abigail Masham, Queen Anne and Sarah Churchill, respectively.<ref name=\"Jafaar\"/> By October 2015, Rachel Weisz had replaced Winslet.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/10/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-emma-stone-olivia-colman-1201584014/|title=Rachel Weisz In Talks To Reunite With Yorgos Lanthimos In 'The Favourite'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Ali|last=Jafaar|date=15 October 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420225623/http://deadline.com/2015/10/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-emma-stone-olivia-colman-1201584014/|archive-date=20 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''The Favourite'' is the second collaboration between Lanthimos, Colman and Weisz: both actors appeared in Lanthimos' ''[[The Lobster]]'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorgos Lanthimos commences The Lobster shoot|url=http://www.cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&l=en&did=254300|work=Cineuropa|date=31 March 2014|accessdate=11 May 2014|last=Ramachandran|first=Naman|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419053512/http://www.cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&l=en&did=254300|archive-date=19 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2017, Nicholas Hoult joined the cast of the film, followed by Joe Alwyn, in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/nicholas-hoult-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-the-favourite-movie-1202030153/|title=Nicholas Hoult Joins Emma Stone And Rachel Weisz In 'The Favourite'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anita|last=Busch|date=28 February 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324175351/http://deadline.com/2017/02/nicholas-hoult-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-the-favourite-movie-1202030153/|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/billy-lynn-star-joe-alwyn-joins-emma-stone-favourite-983036|title='Billy Lynn' Star Joe Alwyn Joins Emma Stone in 'The Favourite' (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Rebecca|last=Ford|date=3 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114733/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/billy-lynn-star-joe-alwyn-joins-emma-stone-favourite-983036?utm_source=t.co&utm_medium=referral|archive-date=4 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 8 August 2018, Mark Gatiss, James Smith and Jenny Rainsford were announced as members of the cast.<ref name=\"centerpiece\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-london-film-festival-centerpiece-1202900434/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' to Be London Film Festival Centerpiece|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Henry|last=Chu|date=8 August 2018|accessdate=8 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809184127/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-london-film-festival-centerpiece-1202900434/|archive-date=9 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCasting was crucial for Lanthimos, who describes his process as \"instinctive\"; he said, \"It's one of those things when you feel you're right and you need to insist no matter what\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Colman was his only choice for Queen Anne. After Winslet left the project, Lanthimos offered the role to [[Cate Blanchett]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/11/23/rachel-weisz-loved-playing-devious-duchess-favourite/2056025002/|title=Rachel Weisz doesn't care about the royals, but loved playing one in 'The Favourite'|website=[[USA Today]]|first=Patrick|last=Ryan|date=23 November 2018|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103061514/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/11/23/rachel-weisz-loved-playing-devious-duchess-favourite/2056025002/|archive-date=3 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.joe.ie/movies-tv/yorgos-lanthimos-interview-652879|title=Yorgos Lanthimos discusses the very different original cast for The Favourite|website=JOE|first=Rory|last=Cashin|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103065016/https://www.joe.ie/movies-tv/yorgos-lanthimos-interview-652879|archive-date=3 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Stone auditioned after asking her agent to contact Lanthimos,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/emma-stone-timothee-chalamet-young-fame-1203078565/ |title=Variety magazine. Interview of Emma Stone with Timothy Shalament. 2018 |access-date=5 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306044522/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/emma-stone-timothee-chalamet-young-fame-1203078565/ |archive-date=6 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> who then asked Stone to work with a dialect coach. \"It was making sure that we would be able to work creatively free without the accent being a hindrance in the way that we wanted to work\", Lanthimos said.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/why-emma-stone-had-to-audition-for-her-new-movie-2018-11|title=Oscar winner Emma Stone explains why she had to audition for her new movie, but 'didn't find it insulting'|last=Guerrasio|first=Jason|date=20 November 2018|website=Business Insider Australia|language=en|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071750/https://www.businessinsider.com.au/why-emma-stone-had-to-audition-for-her-new-movie-2018-11|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nColman found playing Anne \"a joy because she sort of feels everything\".<ref name=\"colman\" /> When asked if the character was just a petulant child, she responded, \"she's just a woman who is underconfident and doesn't know if anyone genuinely loves her. She has too much power, too much time on her hands.\"<ref name=\"colman\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/the-favourite-olivia-colman-emma-stone-yorgos-lanthimos-venice-1202454629/|title=Olivia Colman On 'The Favourite': It Was \"Awfully Fun Having Sex With Emma Stone\" \u2013 Venice|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=30 August 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215310/https://deadline.com/2018/08/the-favourite-olivia-colman-emma-stone-yorgos-lanthimos-venice-1202454629/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Colman said the difference between Anne and the previous queens she has played was \"the other queens didn't get to fall in love with two hot women\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Weisz described the film as a comedy, comparing it to a \"funnier, sex driven\" ''[[All About Eve]]'' and was primarily attracted to the project by the prominent female leads, considering her role to be \"the juiciest\" of her career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/06/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-1201838213/|title=Rachel Weisz Says Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' Is Like a Funnier, Sex-Driven 'All About Eve'|website=IndieWire|first=Kate|last=Erbland|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=27 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727181358/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/06/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-1201838213/|archive-date=27 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Stone was hesitant to accept the role, at first thinking Abigail was \"a sweet kind of girl, the victim, a servant to these people\",<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> but changed her mind after reading the script and then \"begging\" Lanthimos to be cast. Stone's greatest concern was mastering her accent; \"It's 1705, which was about 300 years before any period I had ever done. It was pretty daunting on a few levels\u2014having to be British and not stick out like a sore thumb.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-stones-reveals-acting-breaking-points-1139241|title=Telluride: Emma Stone Reveals Her Acting Breaking Points|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Stephen|last=Galloway|date=2 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904190438/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-stones-reveals-acting-breaking-points-1139241|archive-date=4 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{quotebox|align=left|bgcolor=lavender|width=28%|quote=\"What makes ''The Favourite'' work are its women, who rule, both literally within the movie and outwardly, commanding our enjoyment ... Lanthimos's latest makes the men extraneous, building a potent hothouse atmosphere that swirls with secret desires.\"|source=\u2013 Critic Joshua Rothkopf's analysis of the gender dynamics in the film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com/us/film/the-favourite|title=The Favourite|website=TimeOut|first=Joshua|last=Rothkopf|date=28 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119034604/https://www.timeout.com/us/film/the-favourite|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nDespite having less-dynamic roles, Hoult and Alwyn were intrigued to be part of a film dominated by three complex, leading, female characters. \"It's obviously very timely to have three female leads, and it's wonderful to see because it's so rare,\" said Hoult, commenting on the audience appeal a three-way love-power struggle would have for audiences.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/scene/news/the-favourite-female-led-film-resonates-during-metoo-and-times-up-1202962340/|title='The Favourite': Female-Led Film Resonates During #MeToo and Times Up|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Cristina|last=Gibson|date=29 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120015112/https://variety.com/2018/scene/news/the-favourite-female-led-film-resonates-during-metoo-and-times-up-1202962340/|archive-date=20 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Alwyn shared similar views, saying; \"It's unusual, I suppose, to have a film led by three women, and these three women are so unbelievably talented and generous as performers and also as people, and to spend time with them and be on set with them and everyone else was just a lot of fun. I was just happy to be a part of it at all. It's rare to get a film like this to come along that is so different from what we're used to seeing, especially with a director like this, so to be any part in it was brilliant.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n===Filming===\n[[File:Hatfield House.jpg|thumb|A majority of the film's [[principal photography]] took place at [[Hatfield House]], [[Hertfordshire]].]]\n\nFilming was expected to begin in the spring of 2016 but was postponed for a year, during which time Lanthimos made ''[[The Killing of a Sacred Deer]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lodderhose|first1=Diana|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/cannes-colin-farrell-reunites-with-yorgos-lanthimos-for-the-killing-of-a-sacred-deer-exclusive-1201771113/|title=Cannes: Colin Farrell Reunites With Yorgos Lanthimos for 'The Killing of a Sacred Deer' (EXCLUSIVE)|date=11 May 2016|work=Variety|accessdate=26 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307162429/https://variety.com/2016/film/news/cannes-colin-farrell-reunites-with-yorgos-lanthimos-for-the-killing-of-a-sacred-deer-exclusive-1201771113/|archive-date=7 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Principal photography began in March 2017 at [[Hatfield House]], [[Hertfordshire]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theknowledgeonline.com/the-knowledge-bulletin/post/2017/01/10/emma-stone-to-film-the-favourite-in-uk-|title=Emma Stone to film The Favourite in UK|website=The Knowledge Bulletin|first=Nia|last=Daniels|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324083958/http://www.theknowledgeonline.com/the-knowledge-bulletin/post/2017/01/10/emma-stone-to-film-the-favourite-in-uk-|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/colin-farrell-oliver-north-amazon-show-iran-contra-1202008969/|title=Colin Farrell to Star as Oliver North in Iran-Contra Series for Amazon (EXCLUSIVE)|website=Variety|first=Justin|last=Kroll|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171104062617/http://variety.com/2017/tv/news/colin-farrell-oliver-north-amazon-show-iran-contra-1202008969/|archive-date=4 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> there were 45 filming days<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kodak.com/nz/en/motion/Blog/Blog_Post/?ContentId=4295011331|title=DP Robbie Ryan BSC ISC combined 35mm film with wide-angled lensing and a fluid camera to depict the courtly capers in The Favourite {{!}} Motion Picture Film|website=www.kodak.com|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> and filming finished in May.<ref name=\"wrap\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/05/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-plot-details-revealed-lesbian-love-triangle-1201817231/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos Wraps Period Piece 'The Favourite,' Official Synopsis Hints At Royal-Centric Lesbian Love Triangle|website=IndieWire|first=Jude|last=Dry|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721221818/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/05/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-plot-details-revealed-lesbian-love-triangle-1201817231/|archive-date=21 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Regarding his choice of location, Lanthimos said, \"from the beginning, I had this image of these lonely characters in (a) huge space\".<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nPrior to principal photography, Lanthimos engaged the main actors in an unorthodox rehearsal process that lasted three weeks. The actors \"delivered their lines while trying to tie themselves in knots, jumping from carpet tile to carpet tile, or writhing around on the floor\", according to the ''New York Times''.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/magazine/yorgos-lanthimoss-director-favourite.html|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Polarizing Visions|last=Kleeman|first=Alexandra|date=21 November 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=23 January 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071519/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/magazine/yorgos-lanthimoss-director-favourite.html|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A Coleman said, \"He had us do all sorts of things that keep you from thinking about what your lines mean\".<ref name=\":1\" /> According to Weisz, one exercise involved the actors linking arms to create a \"human pretzel\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/rachel-weisz-the-favourite-interview.html|title=Rachel Weisz: 'When Women Are Together, There's a Lot of Freedom'|last=Handler|first=Rachel|date=23 November 2018|website=www.vulture.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071732/https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/rachel-weisz-the-favourite-interview.html|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> \"Somebody's butt is in your face, your face is in their butt, and you're saying the lines for a really serious, dramatic scene while doing that\", she said.<ref name=\":2\" /> According to Stone, Lanthimos wanted to see \"how much we could sense each other without seeing each other\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Lanthimos said he believed the rehearsals allowed the actors \"to not take themselves too seriously, learn the text in a physical way by doing completely irrelevant things to what the scene is about, just be comfortable about making a fool of themselves\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n\nThe most challenging aspect of filming for cinematographer [[Robbie Ryan (cinematographer)|Robbie Ryan]] was trying to capture fluid camera movement without the use of [[Steadicam]]:\n<blockquote>We explored a lot of ways of trying to have a fluid camera movement that wasn't a Steadicam move. He showed me a film early on called ''[[Angst (1983 film)|Angst]]''&nbsp;... He wanted to try and instil that in the way we shot ''The Favourite'', but it was going to be really difficult to do that. Because of the costumes and just the physicality of it, it was not going to be possible. So we tried to come up with ways of being as fluid as we could with the camera. That was exciting because we came up with some interesting rigs\u2014we explored different gimbal rigs and things like that.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-favourite-robbie-ryan-yorgos-lanthimos-cinematography-interview-1202494103/|title='The Favourite' DP Robbie Ryan Brings Fisheye Lenses & Fluid, Roving Camera To Yorgos Lanthimos' Madcap Period Piece|last=Grobar|first=Matt|date=6 November 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119091948/https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-favourite-robbie-ryan-yorgos-lanthimos-cinematography-interview-1202494103/|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nLanthimos encouraged Ryan to use [[Fisheye lens|fisheye]] and [[Wide-angle lens|wide-angle]] lenses for a majority of the shots, which Ryan believed contributed significantly to the story:<blockquote>The wide lens is twofold. By showing you the whole room and also isolating the character in a small space&nbsp;... you get a feeling of no escape. I think one of the critiques of the film believed it was like a playground that turns into a battleground that turns into a prison. I think that's a very good explanation of what the film tries to get across with these characters. I think the wide lenses are pretty integral to that, as well.<ref name=\":5\" /></blockquote>\n\n===Set design===\nProduction designer Fiona Crombie drew inspiration for the film's colour palette from the chequered, black-and-white marble floor in the Great Hall at Hatfield House, noting that \"a character will walk into a room and you get this incredible wide-shot\u2014we're talking seeing from the floors to the ceilings to the corners. You see ''everything''.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Venice Film Festival crowd-pleaser The Favourite filmed almost exclusively at Hatfield House, Hertfordshire|last=Smith|first=Shona|date=3 September 2018|website=The Location Guide|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071653/https://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Several rooms at the house were altered, particularly for the Queen's room, which included removing paintings, furniture and other decorations, to \"put our own language into it\". The filmmakers used mostly natural lighting, which proved challenging for the candle-lit night time scenes; Crombie said, \"as you imagine, there are very strict protocols about managing candles&nbsp;... we had to use an enormous number of wax-catchers. But the people who manage Hatfield were very supportive and we negotiated and negotiated, and we would be able to do a vast majority of what we wanted to do\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/#|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Venice Film Festival crowd-pleaser The Favourite filmed almost exclusively at Hatfield House, Hertfordshire|website=The Location Guide|first=Shona|last=Smith|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215552/http://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Costume design===\nBecause she was a fan of his previous work, costume designer [[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]] specifically sought out Lanthimos. Powell wanted Abigail's rise to power to be reflected in her costumes; she said, \"I wanted to give her that vulgarity of the ''nouveau riche'', and her dresses get a little bolder and showier. There's more pattern involved and there are black-and-white stripes&nbsp;... I wanted her to stand out from everybody else as trying too hard\".<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/the-favourite-costumes-sandy-powell-interview/|title=How 'The Favourite' costumes added renegade 'punk' edge to Queen Anne's court|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|date=9 November 2018|website=EW.com|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204150223/https://ew.com/movies/the-favourite-costumes-sandy-powell-interview/|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Although the film's Queen Anne spends most of her time wearing a nightgown because she is ill, Powell wanted her to have an \"iconic\" look and constructed a robe made of [[ermine]], saying:\n<blockquote>This is the queen at her most queenly, in her ceremonial outfit&nbsp;... I looked at images and real things like it, and normally [this type of garment] would be solid gold, embroidered, and bejewelled, so I thought what else can I do just to give it an air of royalty? Ermine is associated with royalty, it's usually just used as a decoration in small amounts, so I decided to just cover her in it. Because in the rest of the film I have her in a nightgown, not bothering to get dressed every day.<ref name=\":4\" /></blockquote>\n\nAlthough unintentional, Powell drew inspiration for Sarah's contrasting, feminine gowns and her masculine recreational attire from her previous designs for [[Tilda Swinton]]'s character in ''[[Orlando (film)|Orlando]]'' (1992); she said, \"I didn't think about it at the time, it was just subliminal. I do think there is a similarity between the two films because ''Orlando'' was the last unconventional period film I'd done, so there is a similarity.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> Powell stated Lanthimos wanted the women in the film to have natural hair and faces but he wanted the men to wear considerable makeup and large wigs. He said; \"Normally films are filled with men and the women are the decoration in the background, and I've done many of those, so it was quite nice for it to be reversed this time where the women are the centre of the film and the men are the decoration in the background. Of course, they've got serious, important parts, but I think the frivolity of them is quite funny.\"<ref name=\":4\" />\n\nPowell would deliver the costumes, check they fitted the actors and that the actors had no problems and would leave the set, as Lanthimos requested. She described his directing style:<blockquote>He knew he wanted to be left alone with his actors and his camera. A lot of the time I wasn't aware of how it was going to be. Even when you see the dailies, you can't really tell until it's all put together&nbsp;... But when it all comes together, you're like of course it was all going to come together, he knows exactly what he's doing. We were all part of the jigsaw and he could put all the pieces together.<ref name=\":4\" /></blockquote>\n\n===Soundtrack===\nThe soundtrack of ''The Favourite'' consists mostly of [[Baroque music|baroque]] and [[Classical music|classical]] music, including pieces by [[W. F. Bach|W. F.]] and [[J. S. Bach]], [[George Frideric Handel|Handel]], [[Henry Purcell|Purcell]], [[Antonio Vivaldi|Vivaldi]], and [[Schubert]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/favourite-review-venice-2018-1138544 |title=The Favourite: Film Review |last=Rooney |first=David |date=30 August 2018 |website=THR |publisher=THR |accessdate=12 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013014301/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/favourite-review-venice-2018-1138544 |archive-date=13 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> It also includes works by [[20th-century classical music|20th-century composers]] [[Olivier Messiaen]] and [[Luc Ferrari]], and the contemporary British composer [[Anna Meredith]]. The first song to play over the closing credits is \"[[Skyline Pigeon]]\" by [[Elton John]], from his d\u00e9but album ''[[Empty Sky]]'' (1969).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.classicfm.com/discover-music/periods-genres/film-tv/the-favourite-soundtrack-trailer-music-credits/ |title=The Favourite soundtrack: trailer music, tracklisting and credits |last=Shaw Roberts |first=Maddy |date=25 January 2019 |website=FM |publisher=FM |accessdate=19 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nMuch of the music that appears to be contemporaneous with the time in which the film is set was composed later; for example, Bach's organ Fantasia in G minor, Schubert's Piano Trio no. 2 and Piano Sonata in B flat, and Schumann's Piano Quintet.{{citation needed|date=November 2019}}\n\nThe film's sound designer Johnnie Burn said; \"There was no composer on this film; we were working a lot in that space between music and sound\".<ref name=Burn-sound /> He also said he used \"specific [[Equalization (audio)|EQ]] frequencies to shape [atmospheric sound] like score\".<ref name=Burn-sound>{{Cite web|url=http://designingsound.org/2018/12/19/interview-johnnie-burn-on-creating-the-sound-for-the-favourite/|title=Interview: Johnnie Burn on Creating the Sound for The Favourite|language=en-US|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123223008/http://designingsound.org/2018/12/19/interview-johnnie-burn-on-creating-the-sound-for-the-favourite/|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nIn May 2017, [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]] acquired the distribution rights to ''The Favourite''.<ref name=\"wrap\"/> It had its world premiere at the [[75th Venice International Film Festival]] on 30 August 2018.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AlbertoBarbera2|number=1027149478946660353|title=Gioved\u00ec 30 agosto|first=Alberto|last=Barbera|date=8 August 2018|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/venice-film-festival-2018-lineup-full-list-1202433056/|title=Venice Film Festival Lineup: Welles, Coen Brothers, Cuaron, Greengrass, More \u2013 Live|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=25 July 2018|accessdate=25 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421175526/https://deadline.com/2018/07/venice-film-festival-2018-lineup-full-list-1202433056/|archive-date=21 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was screened the film at the [[BFI London Film Festival]] and the [[Telluride Film Festival]], and was the opening-night film at the [[New York Film Festival]].<ref name=\"centerpiece\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/festivals/2018-telluride-film-festival-line-up-1202918919/|title='First Man,' 'Front Runner' and 'Roma' Among 2018 Telluride Film Festival Selections|website=Variety|first=Kristopher|last=Tapley|date=30 August 2018|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830174303/https://variety.com/2018/film/festivals/2018-telluride-film-festival-line-up-1202918919/|archive-date=30 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telluridecms-production.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/guides/45th-TFF-program-guide-final.pdf|title=45th Telluride Film Festival Program Guide|website=[[Telluride Film Festival]]|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012115214/http://telluridecms-production.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/guides/45th-TFF-program-guide-final.pdf|archive-date=12 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/the-favourite-56th-new-york-film-festival-opening-night-film-yorgos-lanthimos-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-1202431888/|title='The Favourite' To Open 56th New York Film Festival|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=23 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724032150/https://deadline.com/2018/07/the-favourite-56th-new-york-film-festival-opening-night-film-yorgos-lanthimos-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-1202431888/|archive-date=24 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> ''The Favourite'' was given a [[limited release]] in the United States on 23 November 2018,<ref>{{cite news|last=Hayes|first=Britt|title=Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' Sets Awards Season Release|url=https://screencrush.com/lanthimos-the-favourite-fall-release/|work=[[ScreenCrush]]|accessdate=20 April 2018|date=20 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421015555/http://screencrush.com/lanthimos-the-favourite-fall-release/|archive-date=21 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"InComp1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-full-lineup-1129426 |title=Venice to Kick Off Awards Season With New Films From Coen Brothers, Luca Guadagnino and Alfonso Cuaron |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |first=Ariston |last=Anderson |date=25 July 2018 |accessdate=25 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725121213/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-full-lineup-1129426 |archive-date=25 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"InComp2\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/venice-film-festival-full-lineup-1202883737/ |title=Venice Film Festival Lineup: Heavy on Award Hopefuls, Netflix and Star Power |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Nick |last=Vivarelli |date=25 July 2018 |accessdate=25 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322165739/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/venice-film-festival-full-lineup-1202883737/ |archive-date=22 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and was released in the United Kingdom and Ireland on 1 January 2019.<ref name=\"guardukrelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/jan/02/uk-box-office-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-free-solo-the-favourite|title=Mary Poppins Returns is Christmas winner at UK box office|website=The Guardian|date=2 January 2019|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102145722/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/jan/02/uk-box-office-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-free-solo-the-favourite|archive-date=2 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/09/04/favourite-trailer-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-go-head-head-love/|title=The Favourite trailer: Rachel Weisz and Emma Stone go head to head as love rivals in Olivia Colman's bawdy Queen Anne drama|date=4 September 2018|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180909220351/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/09/04/favourite-trailer-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-go-head-head-love/|archivedate=9 September 2018|url-status=live|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n''The Favourite'' was released on [[Digital HD]] on 12 February 2019, and on Blu-ray and DVD on 5 March 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/9304/the-favourite|title=The Favourite (2018)|website=DVDsReleaseDates.com|date=5 March 2019|access-date=15 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329222620/https://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/9304/the-favourite|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''The Favourite'' grossed $34.4&nbsp;million in the United States and Canada, and $61.6&nbsp;million in other territories, for a worldwide gross of $95.9&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> In its opening weekend, the film grossed $422,410 from four theaters, a per-venue average of $105,603. It was the best of 2018, beating ''[[Suspiria (2018 film)|Suspiria]]''{{'}}s $89,903.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/ralph-breaks-the-internet-creed-ii-thanksgiving-box-office-1202505947/|title='Ralph' Scoring 2nd Best Thanksgiving Debut With $84M+; 'Creed II' $55M+ Live-Action Champ; 'Robin Hood' Goes Wrong At $14M+|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=25 November 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=25 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181125060917/https://deadline.com/2018/11/ralph-breaks-the-internet-creed-ii-thanksgiving-box-office-1202505947/|archive-date=25 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In its second weekend the film made $1.1 million from 34 theaters, an average of $32,500.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/the-possession-of-hannah-grace-grabs-625k-in-thursday-night-previews-1202511705/|title='Ralph' Breaking $25M+ 2nd Weekend; 'Grinch' Steals $203M+; 'Hannah Grace' $6M+ In Slow Post Thanksgiving Period \u2013 Sunday Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=2 December 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=2 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203182923/https://deadline.com/2018/12/the-possession-of-hannah-grace-grabs-625k-in-thursday-night-previews-1202511705/|archive-date=3 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In its third weekend, following its Golden Globe nominations, it made $1.4 million from 91 theaters, and then $2.6 million from 439 theaters in its fourth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/ralph-breaks-the-internet-the-favourite-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-weekend-box-office-1202516270/|title='Ralph' Keeps No. 1 Away From Greedy 'Grinch' For Third Weekend In A Row With $16M+ \u2013 Sunday Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=9 December 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=9 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181208135010/https://deadline.com/2018/12/ralph-breaks-the-internet-the-favourite-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-weekend-box-office-1202516270/|archive-date=8 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''The Favourite'' opened across the U.S. in its fifth weekend, grossing $2.1 million from 790 theaters and then $2.4 million in its sixth weekend.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Anthony|last1=D'Alessandro|title='Spider-Verse' Raises $35M+ As 'The Mule' Kicks Up $17M+ In Pre-Christmas Period, But 'Mortal Engines' Breaks Down With $7M+|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/spider-man-into-the-spider-verse-mortal-engines-clint-eastwood-the-mule-weekend-box-office-1202520137/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215131941/https://deadline.com/2018/12/spider-man-into-the-spider-verse-mortal-engines-clint-eastwood-the-mule-weekend-box-office-1202520137/|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/on-the-basis-of-sex-best-of-slow-holiday-weekend-start-for-newcomers-beale-street-decent-with-added-runs-specialty-box-office-1202527280/ |title='On The Basis of Sex' Best Of Holiday Weekend Start for Newcomers; 'Beale Street' Surges: Specialty Box Office |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=30 December 2018 |first=Brian |last=Brooks |accessdate=30 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181230235633/https://deadline.com/2018/12/on-the-basis-of-sex-best-of-slow-holiday-weekend-start-for-newcomers-beale-street-decent-with-added-runs-specialty-box-office-1202527280/ |archive-date=30 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the film's 10th week of release, following the announcement of its ten Oscar nominations, it was added to 1,023 theaters (for a total of 1,540) and made $2.5 million, an increase of 212% from the previous weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/box-office-glass-anne-hathaway-matthew-mcconaughey-serenity-bombs-oscars-best-picture-1202542005/|title='Glass' Leads Again At Weekend B. O., But Only A Handful Of Oscar Best Picture Noms Will See Boost|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=27 January 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=2 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128113931/https://deadline.com/2019/01/box-office-glass-anne-hathaway-matthew-mcconaughey-serenity-bombs-oscars-best-picture-1202542005/|archive-date=28 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n{{multiple images\n| total_width = 386\n| direction   = horizontal\n| align       = right\n| image1      = Olivia Colman at Moet BIFA 2014 (cropped).jpg\n| image2      = Emma Stone at Maniac UK premiere (cropped).jpg\n| image3      = Rachel Weisz Deauville 2012 3.jpg\n| footer      = The performances of (left to right) [[Olivia Colman]], [[Emma Stone]], and [[Rachel Weisz]] garnered widespread critical acclaim, with the former winning the [[Academy Award for Best Actress]] and the latter two being both nominated for [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]].\n}}\n\nOn review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 93% based on 387 reviews and an average rating of 8.49/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''The Favourite'' sees Yorgos Lanthimos balancing a period setting against rich, timely subtext\u2014and getting roundly stellar performances from his well-chosen stars\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_favourite_2018|title=The Favourite (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517210303/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_favourite_2018|archive-date=17 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gives the film a weighted average score of 90 out of 100, based on 53 critics, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-favourite|title=The Favourite Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=31 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227214338/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-favourite|archive-date=27 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[PostTrak]] gave the film 2.5 stars out of 5 and a 37% \"definite recommend\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/aquaman-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-new-years-weekend-box-office-1202526812/ |title='Aquaman' Sailing To $51M+ 2nd Weekend; $188M+ Cume Pacing Ahead Of 'Doctor Strange' & 'Guardians Of The Galaxy' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=29 December 2018 |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |accessdate=29 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231133017/https://deadline.com/2018/12/aquaman-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-new-years-weekend-box-office-1202526812/ |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn his review for ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', Chris Nashawaty gave the film an \"A\" rating, praising the effective presentation of themes dealing with royalty and associated \"steamier, fact-adjacent subplots\". He wrote, \"It's worth pointing out that ''The Favourite'' is easily Lanthimos' most user-friendly movie, which isn't to say it isn't strange enough to please his fans, just that it may also convert a legion of new ones\".<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Review of 'The Favourite' |last=Nashawaty |first=Chris |date=30 November 2018 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |page=37}}</ref> [[Peter Travers]] from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' gave the movie five stars, saying, \"Emma Stone, Rachel Weisz and the mighty Olivia Colman turn a period piece into a caustic comeuppance comedy with fangs and claws&nbsp;... It's a bawdy, brilliant triumph, directed by Greek auteur Yorgos Lanthimos with all the artistic reach and renegade deviltry&nbsp;... ''The Favourite'' belongs to its fierce, profanely funny female trio.\"<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-favourite-movie-review-758119/ |title='The Favourite' Movie Review: Welcome to 'All About Eve' in Corsets |last=Travers |first=Peter |date=20 November 2018 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=2 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228174739/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-favourite-movie-review-758119/ |archive-date=28 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/olivia-colman-interview-758116 |title=Olivia Colman: All Hail 'The Favourite' Queen |last=Grierson |first=Tim |date=19 November 2018 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=3 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201181034/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/olivia-colman-interview-758116/ |archive-date=1 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n \n[[Anthony Lane]], writing for ''[[The New Yorker]]'', contrasted the film's \u2033unmistakable whiff of&nbsp;... fun\" to the mood of Lanthimos' previous film, ''The Killing of a Sacred Deer'', making note of the strength of the film's female characters.<ref name=\"lane1\">{{cite web|work=The New Yorker|date=26 November 2018|title=Glamour, Wit, and Cunning in The Favourite Yorgos Lanthimos relishes the game of historical reconstruction in a tale of usurpation that borders on a romp.|author=Anthony Lane|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/11/26/glamour-wit-and-cunning-in-the-favourite|accessdate=15 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215023722/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/11/26/glamour-wit-and-cunning-in-the-favourite|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Two reviewers for ''Entertainment Weekly'', in their assessment of the year's best films, listed the film in first place, with Leah Greenblatt writing, \"You might not actually want to live in Yorgos Lanthimos' sticky tar pit of palace intrigue\u2014a place where Olivia Colman's batty Queen can't trust anyone beyond her pet rabbits, and Rachel Weisz and Emma Stone treat loyalty like a blood sport\u2014but God it's fun as hell to visit\".<ref>Entertainment Weekly. Leah Greenblatt. 2018 Year-End Special issue. Page 32.</ref> David Sims writing for ''[[The Atlantic]]'' magazine found the film to be an effective satire of its historical period, stating; \"Were it just a straightforward comedy, ''The Favourite'' would still be a success. It has plenty of satirical bite, and its plot structure (the roller-coaster-like power struggle between Abigail and Sarah) is an utter blast\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/11/the-favourite-movie-review-yorgos-lanthimos-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-olivia-colman/576520/|title=''The Favourite'' Is a Deliciously Nasty Satire of Royal-Court Intrigue|magazine=The Atlantic|first=David|last=Sims|date=23 November 2018|access-date=27 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228065905/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/11/the-favourite-movie-review-yorgos-lanthimos-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-olivia-colman/576520/|archive-date=28 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n\n{{main|List of accolades received by The Favourite}}\n\n''The Favourite''  has received multiple awards and nominations, and won two [[Venice International Film Festival]] awards: the [[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]] and the [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/news/collateral-awards-75th-venice-film-festival|title=Collateral Awards Of The 75th Venice Film Festival|publisher=[[Venice Biennale]]|date=7 September 2018|accessdate=8 September 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908213654/http://www.labiennale.org/en/news/official-awards-75th-venice-film-festival|archivedate=9 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It also won 10 [[British Independent Film Awards 2018|British Independent Film Awards]], including Best British Independent Film; Best Actress; Best Supporting Actress; Best Director, and Best Screenplay. It was nominated for five [[Golden Globe Awards]], including [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy|Best Picture]], and was ranked by the [[American Film Institute]] as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2018#Top 10 Films|top 10 films of 2018]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AFI Awards 2018|url=http://blog.afi.com/announcing-the-afi-awards-2018-honorees/|publisher=[[American Film Institute]]|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Anne|last=Thompson|title=AFI Awards: Top 10 Films and TV of 2018, Plus Special Award for \u2018Roma\u2019|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/12/afi-awards-top-10-films-tv-2018-roma-1202025280/|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref> It was nominated for ten Oscars at the [[91st Academy Awards]]\u2014including [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\u2014and was thus tied with ''[[Roma (2018 film)|Roma]]'' as the most-nominated film of that year. Colman won the [[Academy Award for Best Actress]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/2019-oscars-winners-list-academy-awards-1203145638/|title=Oscar Winners 2019: The Complete List|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=24 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Historical accuracy==\n[[File:Closterman, John - Queen Anne - NPG 215.jpg|thumb|Portrait of [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]], from the school of [[John Closterman]], {{Circa|1702}}. [[National Portrait Gallery, London|National Portrait Gallery]], London.]]\n\nLanthimos said, \"Some of the things in the film are accurate and a lot aren't\".<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> While the broad outlines of the characters' rivalry for Anne's attentions are true, many of the major episodes and themes of the film are fictional or speculative.<ref name=vulacc>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/the-favourite-historical-accuracy.html |title=Everything You Need to Know About the 18th-Century World of The Favourite |website=[[Vulture.com]] |first=Nate |last=Jones |date=27 November 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231030625/https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/the-favourite-historical-accuracy.html |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=ewacc>{{cite web |first=Dana |last=Schwartz |url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/12/03/the-favourite-historical-accuracy/ |title=How historically accurate is The Favourite? |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226232743/https://ew.com/movies/2018/12/03/the-favourite-historical-accuracy/ |archive-date=26 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Any evaluation of the sexual aspect to the film's relationships requires understanding of contemporaneous mores and practices, and use of language. Arguments both for and against the possibilities have been discussed by scholars of the era.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thecut.com/2018/12/how-accurate-are-the-sex-scenes-in-the-favourite.html |title=The Real Sex Lives of Historical Queens |first=Anna |last=Silman |website=[[thecut.com]] |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226233153/https://www.thecut.com/2018/12/how-accurate-are-the-sex-scenes-in-the-favourite.html |archive-date=26 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pictorial.jezebel.com/dissecting-the-real-romantic-rumors-behind-the-favourit-1830593926 |title=Dissecting the Real Romantic Rumors Behind The Favourite With a Queen Anne Biographer |first=Hazel |last=Cills |website=[[Jezebel.com]] |date=27 November 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181128011712/https://pictorial.jezebel.com/dissecting-the-real-romantic-rumors-behind-the-favourit-1830593926 |archive-date=28 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nHistorians consider it unlikely Anne was physically intimate with her female friends. [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Sarah Churchill]], who is erroneously referred to in the film as 'Lady Marlborough', had become [[Duke of Marlborough (title)|Duchess of Marlborough]] in 1702. She is known to have tried blackmailing Anne with the threat of publishing private letters between them; this has led some to wonder if the letters contained evidence the two women had a sexual relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/5468269/the-favourite-movie-true-story/|title=Entertainment Movies: The True Story Behind The Favourite|website=Time|first=Wilder|last=Davies|date=7 December 2018|access-date=8 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190113200152/http://time.com/5468269/the-favourite-movie-true-story/|archive-date=13 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAlwyn said there was little concern for historical research of characters' backgrounds:\n\n<blockquote>I think people turn up to the rehearsal period thinking maybe they should've read their history books and thought about their characters and their intentions and all of that stuff that you normally think about but Yorgos made it quite clear early on there wasn't going to be much consideration for historical accuracy to a degree. He wasn't too caught up with or concerned about that. He just wanted us to have fun as people, as a cast and to explore the relationships between us, which is what we did.<ref name=\"hracc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-team-historical-research-behind-british-period-film-1149239|title=N.Y. Film Fest: 'The Favourite' Team on Historical Research Behind British Period Film|first=Hilary|last=Lewis|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=31 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226234031/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-team-historical-research-behind-british-period-film-1149239|archive-date=26 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nIn his review of the film, Anthony Lane comments on its anachronisms, saying; \"For Lanthimos and his screenwriters&nbsp;... all historical reconstruction is a game and to pretend otherwise\u2014to nourish the illusion that we can know another epoch as intimately as we do our own\u2014is merest folly\".<ref name=\"lane1\" /> J. R. Kinnard wrote for ''[[PopMatters]]'':\n\n<blockquote>History records that England was ruled for a brief period in the early 18th century by Queen Anne whose physical infirmities were rivalled only by her psychological quirks. She was indeed counseled by her lifelong friend and ''perhaps'' lover, Lady Sarah Churchill{{sic|date=November 2019}}&nbsp;... Finally, there was a chambermaid named Abigail Masham&nbsp;... who infiltrated the highest levels of the royal house and, ''perhaps'', Queen Anne's bed. The rest is left to the sordid imagination of one of the world's most fascinating filmmakers.<ref name=\"pmacc\">{{cite web |first=J. R. |last=Kinnard |url=https://www.popmatters.com/film-the-favourite-2621519607.html |title=Queen Anne Costume Drama 'The Favourite' Dazzles with Humor, Tragedy, Weirdness |work=[[PopMatters]] |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=December 31, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231164550/https://www.popmatters.com/film-the-favourite-2621519607.html |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref></blockquote>\n\nQueen Anne was close to [[Prince George of Denmark|Prince George, Duke of Cumberland]] (died October 1708), her Danish husband, who was not portrayed in the film but was alive for most of the time covered.<ref name=\"vulacc\" /> Anne's health problems were severe enough that she may have had little sex drive.<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> Some episodes are fictional, such as Masham's attempt to poison the Duchess of Marlborough.<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> Anne's loss of children is accurate but she did not keep rabbits, which at that time were considered food or pests.<ref name=\"bbcacc\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.historyextra.com/period/stuart/real-history-the-favourite-film-queen-anne-olivia-colman-hannah-greig/|title=The Favourite: the real history behind the new Queen Anne film|website=History Extra|date=27 February 2019|access-date=14 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190115023420/https://www.historyextra.com/period/stuart/real-history-the-favourite-film-queen-anne-olivia-colman-hannah-greig/|archive-date=15 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Sequel==\nEmma Stone has indicated an interest in a possible sequel that would follow the political careers of the male characters in the film. According to ''[[Hollywood Reporter]]'', \"[Stone] added that if there was a sequel, she hoped that it would follow Nicholas Hoult's character [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Robert Harley]]. 'Hopefully, it would be Harley's [Nicholas Hoult's pompous parliamentarian] story,' she said. 'I would love to see where Harley goes from there.'\"<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.foxsearchlight.com/thefavourite/}}\n* {{IMDb title|5083738}}\n* {{Metacritic film|the-favourite}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|m/the_favourite_2018}}\n\n{{Yorgos Lanthimos}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= [[List of accolades received by The Favourite|Awards for ''The Favourite'']]\n|list=\n{{BAFTA Best British Film}}\n{{BIFA BestBritishFilm}}\n{{Broadcast Film Critics Association Award for Best Cast}}\n{{European Film Award for Best Film}}\n{{European Film Award for Best Comedy}}\n{{London Film Critics Circle Award for British Film of the Year}}\n{{Satellite Award for Best Cast \u2013 Motion Picture}}\n{{Venice Film Festival Special Jury Prize}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Favourite, The}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:American biographical films]]\n[[Category:American comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:American LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:BAFTA winners (films)]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about English royalty]]\n[[Category:British biographical films]]\n[[Category:British comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:British historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:British LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Comedy films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Anne of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of John Churchill, Duke of Marlborough]]\n[[Category:Drama films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Female bisexuality in film]]\n[[Category:Irish biographical films]]\n[[Category:Irish comedy films]]\n[[Category:Irish comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Irish films]]\n[[Category:Irish historical films]]\n[[Category:Irish LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Lesbian-related films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1700s]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1710s]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Yorgos Lanthimos]]\n[[Category:Films featuring a Best Actress Academy Award-winning performance]]\n[[Category:Films featuring a Best Musical or Comedy Actress Golden Globe winning performance]]\n[[Category:Film4 Productions films]]\n[[Category:Fox Searchlight Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Venice Grand Special Jury Prize winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|The Favorite (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|2018 film by Yorgos Lanthimos}}\n{{Use British English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Favourite\n| image          = The Favourite.png\n| caption        = UK theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Yorgos Lanthimos]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* Ceci Dempsey\n* [[Ed Guiney]]\n* Lee Magiday\n* Yorgos Lanthimos\n}}\n| writer         = {{Plainlist|\n* Deborah Davis\n* [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]]\n}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Olivia Colman]]\n* [[Emma Stone]]\n* [[Rachel Weisz]]\n}}<!--PER BILLING BLOCK ON THE POSTER. Statement in documentation: \"Names as they are listed in the billing block of the poster for the film's original theatrical release\".-->\n| cinematography = [[Robbie Ryan (cinematographer)|Robbie Ryan]]\n| editing        = [[Yorgos Mavropsaridis]]\n| production companies = {{Plainlist|\n* Scarlet Films<ref name=insight>{{cite web|url=https://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181021085213/http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|archive-date=21 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Element Pictures]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Arcana<ref name=insight/>\n* [[Film4 Productions]]<ref name=insight/>\n* Waypoint Entertainment<ref name=insight/>\n}}\n| distributor    = [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]]<ref name=insight/>\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|8|30|[[75th Venice International Film Festival|Venice]]|2018|11|23|United States|2019|1|1|United Kingdom and Ireland|ref1=<ref name=\"Filmoria.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmoria.co.uk/the-favourite-film-review-venice-film-festival/|title=The Favourite \u2013 Film Review (Venice Film Festival 2018)|publisher=Filmoria|access-date=18 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180918194137/https://www.filmoria.co.uk/the-favourite-film-review-venice-film-festival/|archive-date=18 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n| runtime        = 120 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2018/lineup/venezia-75-competition/favourite|title=The Favourite|website=[[Venice International Film Festival]] 2018|accessdate=25 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725183930/http://www.labiennale.org/en/cinema/2018/lineup/venezia-75-competition/favourite|archive-date=25 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| country        = {{Plainlist|\n* United Kingdom<ref name=allmovie/>\n* Ireland<ref name=allmovie>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/the-favourite-v698473|title=The Favourite (2018)|work=[[AllMovie]]|accessdate=12 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713073928/https://www.allmovie.com/movie/the-favourite-v698473|archive-date=13 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* United States<ref name=allmovie/>\n}}\n| language       = English\n| budget         = $15 million<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n| gross          = $95.9 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web |title=The Favourite (2018) |url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=thefavourite.htm |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |access-date=12 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190202214757/https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=thefavourite.htm |archive-date=2 February 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| border         = no\n}}\n'''''The Favourite''''' is a 2018 [[Historical period drama|period]] [[black comedy]] film directed by [[Yorgos Lanthimos]], and written by Deborah Davis and [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]]. It is a co-production of the United Kingdom, Ireland, and the United States. Set in early 18th century England, the film's plot examines the relationship between two cousins, [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Sarah, Duchess of Marlborough]] ([[Rachel Weisz]]) and [[Abigail Masham, Baroness Masham|Abigail Masham]] ([[Emma Stone]]), who are vying to be Court favourites of [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]] ([[Olivia Colman]]). [[Principal photography]] lasted from March to May 2017, taking place at [[Hatfield House]] in [[Hertfordshire]] and at [[Hampton Court Palace]] in Richmond, [[Surrey]].\n\n''The Favourite'' premiered on 30 August 2018 at the [[75th Venice International Film Festival]], where it won the [[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]] and the [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]] for Colman. It was theatrically released in the United States on 23 November 2018 by [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]], and in the United Kingdom and Ireland on 1 January 2019. The film became a box office success, grossing $95 million worldwide on a $15 million budget.\n\n''The Favourite'' was praised for its screenplay, Lanthimos's direction, cinematography, editing, costume design, production values, music, and the lead actresses' performances. It received [[List of accolades received by The Favourite|numerous awards and nominations]], including ten [[91st Academy Awards|Academy Award]] nominations (tying ''[[Roma (2018 film)|Roma]]'' for the most nominations of any film that year). ''The Favourite'' also won seven [[72nd British Academy Film Awards|BAFTA Awards]] (including [[BAFTA Award for Outstanding British Film|Best British Film]] and [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Supporting Role|Best Actress in a Supporting Role]] for Weisz) and ten [[British Independent Film Awards 2018|British Independent Film Awards]]. Colman won Best Actress at the [[Academy Award for Best Actress|Academy Awards]], the [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Motion Picture Comedy or Musical|Golden Globes]], and the [[BAFTA Award for Best Actress in a Leading Role|BAFTAs]]. The film was ranked by the [[American Film Institute]] as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2018#Top 10 Films|top ten films of 2018]]. The film also won eight [[European Film Awards]] including [[European Film Award for Best Film|Best Film]], [[European Film Award for Best Director|Best Director]] and [[European Film Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] for Colman.\n\n==Plot==\n[[File:Sarah, Duchess of Marlborough by Jervas.jpg|thumb|left|upright|[[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough]].]]\n\nIn 1711, England is at [[War of the Spanish Succession|war with France]]. [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]] is in frail health; she shows little interest in governing, preferring activities such as racing ducks and playing with her 17 rabbits, surrogates for the children she miscarried or lost in childhood. Her confidante, adviser, and furtive lover Sarah Churchill effectively rules the country through her influence over the Queen. Sarah's efforts to control Anne are undermined by [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Robert Harley]], the [[Leader of the Opposition (United Kingdom)|Leader of the Opposition]], who as a landowner argues against a doubling of property taxes proposed to fund the war.\n\n[[File:Abigail Masham portrait.jpg|thumb|upright|[[Abigail Masham, Baroness Masham]].]]\n\nAbigail Hill, Sarah's impoverished younger cousin, arrives in search of employment. Abigail's standing has been tainted by her father, who gambled her away in a game of [[whist]]. Abigail is forced to do menial work as a scullery maid in the palace. After seeing the Queen's [[gout]], Abigail forages for herbs and applies them to the Queen's inflamed legs. Sarah has Abigail whipped for entering the Queen's bedroom without permission but relents and appoints her [[Lady of the Bedchamber]] after realising the herbs have helped the Queen. Harley asks Abigail to spy on Sarah and the Queen, hoping to circumvent Sarah's authority. Abigail witnesses Sarah and the Queen having sex.\n\nWith Sarah focused on the war effort, Abigail kindles a friendship with Anne that becomes sexual. Sarah becomes aware of Abigail's machinations and attempts to send her away. Abigail drugs Sarah's tea, causing her to fall off her horse and be dragged unconscious on the ground. Sarah awakens in a brothel, battered from the fall. Anne, thinking Sarah has abandoned her to make her jealous, takes Abigail into her [[Favourite|favour]] and allows her to marry [[Samuel Masham, 1st Baron Masham|Colonel Masham]], reinstating Abigail's noble standing.\n\nWhen Sarah returns to court, she issues an ultimatum to Queen Anne: send Abigail away or Sarah will disclose her correspondence with Anne that details their sexual relationship. She tells Anne that Abigail does not love her and merely flatters her. Sarah, remorseful, burns the letters but Anne nevertheless sends her away from court. When Abigail, who has been promoted to [[Keeper of the Privy Purse]], presents what she claims is evidence Sarah had been embezzling money, Anne exiles Sarah and her husband from Britain.\n\nWith Sarah gone and her position secure, Abigail begins to neglect and ignore Anne while indulging in court society and openly having affairs. One day, while lounging in the Queen's chamber, Abigail abuses one of Anne's rabbits. Anne, now very sick, is awakened by the animal's distress cry. Finally realising Abigail's cruel nature, Anne forces herself out of bed and orders Abigail to massage her leg while gradually bearing down on Abigail's head with her hand.\n\n==Cast==\n<!--- Cast and order per tombstone closing credits, roles per closing credits scroll --->\n* [[Olivia Colman]] as [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]]\n* [[Emma Stone]] as [[Abigail Hill|Abigail]]\n* [[Rachel Weisz]] as [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Lady Sarah]]\n* [[Nicholas Hoult]] as [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Harley]]\n* [[Joe Alwyn]] as [[Samuel Masham, 1st Baron Masham|Masham]]\n* [[James Smith (actor)|James Smith]] as [[Sidney Godolphin, 1st Earl of Godolphin|Godolphin]]\n* [[Mark Gatiss]] as [[John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough|Lord Marlborough]]\n* [[Jenny Rainsford]] as Mae\n\n==Production==\n===Writing===\nDeborah Davis wrote the first draft of ''The Favourite'' in 1998. She had no prior screenwriting experience and studied screenwriting at night school. She took the draft, which was titled ''The Balance of Power,'' to producer [[Ceci Dempsey]], who responded enthusiastically.<ref name=\"AD_Davis\"/> Davis had little knowledge of Queen Anne and her relationships with Sarah Churchill and Abigail Masham; her research led her to the discovery of a \"female triangle\".<ref name=\"AD_Davis\">{{cite web|url=http://www.awardsdaily.com/2018/11/05/deborah-davis-talks-to-awards-daily-about-the-favourites-twenty-year-journey-to-the-big-screen/|title=Deborah Davis Talks To Awards Daily About The Favourite's Twenty Year Journey To The Big Screen|website=Awards Daily|first=Jazz|last=Tangcay|date=5 November 2018|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119051616/http://www.awardsdaily.com/2018/11/05/deborah-davis-talks-to-awards-daily-about-the-favourites-twenty-year-journey-to-the-big-screen/|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> She studied letters written by Queen Anne, Sarah, and Abigail:\n\n{{quote|I did a lot of research and as it turns out, there is a wealth of original sources. You have historical accounts of the period. One of the best sources is [[Winston Churchill]] who wrote the story about his ancestor who was the Duke of Marlborough and he covers the female triangle and the relationship between Anne, Sarah and Abigail in his four-part biography. There are enormous amounts of sources out there. Another one was, of course, Sarah's memoir where she wrote about how she was replaced in the Queen's favour by Abigail and how Abigail had become the absolute favourite.<ref name=\"AD_Davis\" />}}\n\n''The Favourite'' is the first film Lanthimos directed with screenwriters Davis and McNamara. Lanthimos was attracted to Davis' and McNamara's script, and \"became acquainted with the three female characters who happened to be real people\".<ref name=\"colman\"/>  Lanthimos felt the story was interesting and also had a chance \"to create three complex female characters which is something you rarely see\".<ref name=\"colman\"/> Of her working relationship with Lanthimos, Dempsey said:\n\n{{quote|He has a very particular, contained view. And he reserves it and conserves it, deliberately. He's very intuitive on every level. Casting, yes. Even hiring the department, it's all the same process ... You're not going to talk him into anything ever, ever, ever, ever. Once you accept that, you have to intuit or inhale what he wants, but he's got a very particular contained view and you just need to go with it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-producer-directors-particular-vision-watch-1158810|title=Ceci Dempsey on Yorgos Lanthimos' \"Particular\" Vision for 'The Favourite'|website=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Ciara|last=McVey|date=7 November 2018|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119091900/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-producer-directors-particular-vision-watch-1158810|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n===Pre-production===\nProducer Ceci Dempsey, who read the first draft, said she was \"haunted\" by \"the passion, the survival instincts of these women, the manipulations and what they did to survive\".<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/> Dempsey had difficulty securing finance due to the script's lesbian content and the lack of male representation, which financers felt would be challenging to market. Almost a decade later, producer [[Ed Guiney]] obtained the script and was also attracted to the complex plot and relationships of the three women; he said, \"We didn't want to make just another British costume drama&nbsp;...&#0032;[we wanted] a story that felt contemporary and relevant and vibrant\u2014not something out of a museum\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n\nDuring this time, Guiney became acquainted with Lanthimos, whose film ''[[Dogtooth (film)|Dogtooth]]'' (2009) had received an [[Academy Award]] nomination for [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]. Guiney approached him with the prospect of directing the film. Lanthimos immediately became intrigued with the idea \"[t]hese three women possessed power that affected the lives of millions\"; at the same time he found the story to be \"intimate\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/> Lanthimos began working closely with screenwriter [[Tony McNamara (writer)|Tony McNamara]] on \"freshening up\" the script. By 2013, the producers were receiving financing offers from several companies, including [[Film4 Productions]] and Waypoint Entertainment, which later worked on the film.<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/features/favourite-blows-up-metoo-gender-politics-love-triangle-1160665|title='The Favourite' Blows Up Gender Politics With the Year's Most Outrageous Love Triangle|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|first=Tatiana|last=Siegel|date=14 November 2018|accessdate=14 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181114174652/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/features/favourite-blows-up-metoo-gender-politics-love-triangle-1160665|archive-date=14 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2015, it was announced Lanthimos would direct the film from Deborah Davis and Tony McNamara's screenplay, which was described as \"a bawdy, acerbic tale of royal intrigue, passion, envy, and betrayal\".<ref name=\"wrap\"/> Ceci Dempsey, Ed Guiney, Lee Magiday and [[Andrew Lowe]] served as producers under their Scarlet Films and Element Pictures banners, respectively.<ref name=\"Jafaar\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/09/kate-winslet-emma-stone-olivia-colman-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-element-pictures-scarlet-queen-anne-1201548277/|title=Emma Stone & Olivia Colman In Talks To Board Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite'|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|first=Ali|last=Jafaar|date=24 September 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417044525/http://deadline.com/2015/09/kate-winslet-emma-stone-olivia-colman-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-element-pictures-scarlet-queen-anne-1201548277/|archive-date=17 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On the film's lesbian-centric love triangle, Lanthimos said:\n\n{{quote|My instinct from the beginning was that I didn't want this to become an issue in the film, for us, like we're trying to make a point out of it&nbsp;... I didn't even want the characters in the film to be making an issue of it. I just wanted to deal with these three women as human beings. It didn't matter that there were relationships of the same gender. I stopped thinking about that very early on in the process.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-lesbian-love-triangle-1201999899/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos on the Lesbian Love Triangle of 'The Favourite': 'I Didn't Want This to Become an Issue'|website=[[IndieWire]]|first=Eric|last=Kohn|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215215/https://www.indiewire.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-lesbian-love-triangle-1201999899/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nHe also elaborated on the \"positive\" effect the [[Me Too movement]] has had on the film: \"Because of the prevalent male gaze in cinema, women are portrayed as housewives, girlfriends&nbsp;... Our small contribution is we're just trying to show them as complex and wonderful and horrific as they are, like other human beings.\"<ref name=\"colman\"/>\n\n===Casting===\nCasting for ''The Favourite'' began in 2014 when Lanthimos contacted Colman.<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\">{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/10-things-know-favourite-oscars-2019-1185846/item/stone-wants-a-sequel-follows-harleys-parliamentarian-story-oscars-10-things-know-best-picture-nomine-1186330|title=Oscars: 10 Things to Know About Best Picture Nominee 'The Favourite'|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Katherine|last=Schaffstall|date=22 February 2019}}</ref> By September 2015, it was announced Emma Stone, Olivia Colman and [[Kate Winslet]] had been cast to portray Abigail Masham, Queen Anne and Sarah Churchill, respectively.<ref name=\"Jafaar\"/> By October 2015, Rachel Weisz had replaced Winslet.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/10/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-emma-stone-olivia-colman-1201584014/|title=Rachel Weisz In Talks To Reunite With Yorgos Lanthimos In 'The Favourite'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Ali|last=Jafaar|date=15 October 2015|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170420225623/http://deadline.com/2015/10/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-emma-stone-olivia-colman-1201584014/|archive-date=20 April 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> ''The Favourite'' is the second collaboration between Lanthimos, Colman and Weisz: both actors appeared in Lanthimos' ''[[The Lobster]]'' (2015).<ref>{{cite web|title=Yorgos Lanthimos commences The Lobster shoot|url=http://www.cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&l=en&did=254300|work=Cineuropa|date=31 March 2014|accessdate=11 May 2014|last=Ramachandran|first=Naman|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419053512/http://www.cineuropa.org/nw.aspx?t=newsdetail&l=en&did=254300|archive-date=19 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In February 2017, Nicholas Hoult joined the cast of the film, followed by Joe Alwyn, in March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2017/02/nicholas-hoult-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-the-favourite-movie-1202030153/|title=Nicholas Hoult Joins Emma Stone And Rachel Weisz In 'The Favourite'|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Anita|last=Busch|date=28 February 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324175351/http://deadline.com/2017/02/nicholas-hoult-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-the-favourite-movie-1202030153/|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/billy-lynn-star-joe-alwyn-joins-emma-stone-favourite-983036|title='Billy Lynn' Star Joe Alwyn Joins Emma Stone in 'The Favourite' (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Rebecca|last=Ford|date=3 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114733/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/billy-lynn-star-joe-alwyn-joins-emma-stone-favourite-983036?utm_source=t.co&utm_medium=referral|archive-date=4 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On 8 August 2018, Mark Gatiss, James Smith and Jenny Rainsford were announced as members of the cast.<ref name=\"centerpiece\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-london-film-festival-centerpiece-1202900434/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' to Be London Film Festival Centerpiece|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Henry|last=Chu|date=8 August 2018|accessdate=8 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809184127/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-london-film-festival-centerpiece-1202900434/|archive-date=9 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCasting was crucial for Lanthimos, who describes his process as \"instinctive\"; he said, \"It's one of those things when you feel you're right and you need to insist no matter what\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Colman was his only choice for Queen Anne. After Winslet left the project, Lanthimos offered the role to [[Cate Blanchett]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/11/23/rachel-weisz-loved-playing-devious-duchess-favourite/2056025002/|title=Rachel Weisz doesn't care about the royals, but loved playing one in 'The Favourite'|website=[[USA Today]]|first=Patrick|last=Ryan|date=23 November 2018|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103061514/https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/11/23/rachel-weisz-loved-playing-devious-duchess-favourite/2056025002/|archive-date=3 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.joe.ie/movies-tv/yorgos-lanthimos-interview-652879|title=Yorgos Lanthimos discusses the very different original cast for The Favourite|website=JOE|first=Rory|last=Cashin|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190103065016/https://www.joe.ie/movies-tv/yorgos-lanthimos-interview-652879|archive-date=3 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Stone auditioned after asking her agent to contact Lanthimos,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/emma-stone-timothee-chalamet-young-fame-1203078565/ |title=Variety magazine. Interview of Emma Stone with Timothy Shalament. 2018 |access-date=5 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306044522/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/emma-stone-timothee-chalamet-young-fame-1203078565/ |archive-date=6 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> who then asked Stone to work with a dialect coach. \"It was making sure that we would be able to work creatively free without the accent being a hindrance in the way that we wanted to work\", Lanthimos said.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/why-emma-stone-had-to-audition-for-her-new-movie-2018-11|title=Oscar winner Emma Stone explains why she had to audition for her new movie, but 'didn't find it insulting'|last=Guerrasio|first=Jason|date=20 November 2018|website=Business Insider Australia|language=en|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071750/https://www.businessinsider.com.au/why-emma-stone-had-to-audition-for-her-new-movie-2018-11|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nColman found playing Anne \"a joy because she sort of feels everything\".<ref name=\"colman\" /> When asked if the character was just a petulant child, she responded, \"she's just a woman who is underconfident and doesn't know if anyone genuinely loves her. She has too much power, too much time on her hands.\"<ref name=\"colman\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/08/the-favourite-olivia-colman-emma-stone-yorgos-lanthimos-venice-1202454629/|title=Olivia Colman On 'The Favourite': It Was \"Awfully Fun Having Sex With Emma Stone\" \u2013 Venice|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=30 August 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215310/https://deadline.com/2018/08/the-favourite-olivia-colman-emma-stone-yorgos-lanthimos-venice-1202454629/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Colman said the difference between Anne and the previous queens she has played was \"the other queens didn't get to fall in love with two hot women\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Weisz described the film as a comedy, comparing it to a \"funnier, sex driven\" ''[[All About Eve]]'' and was primarily attracted to the project by the prominent female leads, considering her role to be \"the juiciest\" of her career.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/06/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-1201838213/|title=Rachel Weisz Says Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' Is Like a Funnier, Sex-Driven 'All About Eve'|website=IndieWire|first=Kate|last=Erbland|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=27 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180727181358/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/06/rachel-weisz-yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-1201838213/|archive-date=27 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Stone was hesitant to accept the role, at first thinking Abigail was \"a sweet kind of girl, the victim, a servant to these people\",<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> but changed her mind after reading the script and then \"begging\" Lanthimos to be cast. Stone's greatest concern was mastering her accent; \"It's 1705, which was about 300 years before any period I had ever done. It was pretty daunting on a few levels\u2014having to be British and not stick out like a sore thumb.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-stones-reveals-acting-breaking-points-1139241|title=Telluride: Emma Stone Reveals Her Acting Breaking Points|work=The Hollywood Reporter|first=Stephen|last=Galloway|date=2 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180904190438/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/emma-stones-reveals-acting-breaking-points-1139241|archive-date=4 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n{{quotebox|align=left|bgcolor=lavender|width=28%|quote=\"What makes ''The Favourite'' work are its women, who rule, both literally within the movie and outwardly, commanding our enjoyment ... Lanthimos's latest makes the men extraneous, building a potent hothouse atmosphere that swirls with secret desires.\"|source=\u2013 Critic Joshua Rothkopf's analysis of the gender dynamics in the film<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timeout.com/us/film/the-favourite|title=The Favourite|website=TimeOut|first=Joshua|last=Rothkopf|date=28 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119034604/https://www.timeout.com/us/film/the-favourite|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nDespite having less-dynamic roles, Hoult and Alwyn were intrigued to be part of a film dominated by three complex, leading, female characters. \"It's obviously very timely to have three female leads, and it's wonderful to see because it's so rare,\" said Hoult, commenting on the audience appeal a three-way love-power struggle would have for audiences.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/scene/news/the-favourite-female-led-film-resonates-during-metoo-and-times-up-1202962340/|title='The Favourite': Female-Led Film Resonates During #MeToo and Times Up|website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|first=Cristina|last=Gibson|date=29 September 2018|accessdate=19 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181120015112/https://variety.com/2018/scene/news/the-favourite-female-led-film-resonates-during-metoo-and-times-up-1202962340/|archive-date=20 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Alwyn shared similar views, saying; \"It's unusual, I suppose, to have a film led by three women, and these three women are so unbelievably talented and generous as performers and also as people, and to spend time with them and be on set with them and everyone else was just a lot of fun. I was just happy to be a part of it at all. It's rare to get a film like this to come along that is so different from what we're used to seeing, especially with a director like this, so to be any part in it was brilliant.\"<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n===Filming===\n[[File:Hatfield House.jpg|thumb|A majority of the film's [[principal photography]] took place at [[Hatfield House]], [[Hertfordshire]].]]\n\nFilming was expected to begin in the spring of 2016 but was postponed for a year, during which time Lanthimos made ''[[The Killing of a Sacred Deer]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lodderhose|first1=Diana|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/cannes-colin-farrell-reunites-with-yorgos-lanthimos-for-the-killing-of-a-sacred-deer-exclusive-1201771113/|title=Cannes: Colin Farrell Reunites With Yorgos Lanthimos for 'The Killing of a Sacred Deer' (EXCLUSIVE)|date=11 May 2016|work=Variety|accessdate=26 August 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190307162429/https://variety.com/2016/film/news/cannes-colin-farrell-reunites-with-yorgos-lanthimos-for-the-killing-of-a-sacred-deer-exclusive-1201771113/|archive-date=7 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Principal photography began in March 2017 at [[Hatfield House]], [[Hertfordshire]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theknowledgeonline.com/the-knowledge-bulletin/post/2017/01/10/emma-stone-to-film-the-favourite-in-uk-|title=Emma Stone to film The Favourite in UK|website=The Knowledge Bulletin|first=Nia|last=Daniels|date=10 January 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170324083958/http://www.theknowledgeonline.com/the-knowledge-bulletin/post/2017/01/10/emma-stone-to-film-the-favourite-in-uk-|archive-date=24 March 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/colin-farrell-oliver-north-amazon-show-iran-contra-1202008969/|title=Colin Farrell to Star as Oliver North in Iran-Contra Series for Amazon (EXCLUSIVE)|website=Variety|first=Justin|last=Kroll|date=20 March 2017|accessdate=23 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171104062617/http://variety.com/2017/tv/news/colin-farrell-oliver-north-amazon-show-iran-contra-1202008969/|archive-date=4 November 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> there were 45 filming days<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.kodak.com/nz/en/motion/Blog/Blog_Post/?ContentId=4295011331|title=DP Robbie Ryan BSC ISC combined 35mm film with wide-angled lensing and a fluid camera to depict the courtly capers in The Favourite {{!}} Motion Picture Film|website=www.kodak.com|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> and filming finished in May.<ref name=\"wrap\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2017/05/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-plot-details-revealed-lesbian-love-triangle-1201817231/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos Wraps Period Piece 'The Favourite,' Official Synopsis Hints At Royal-Centric Lesbian Love Triangle|website=IndieWire|first=Jude|last=Dry|date=15 May 2017|accessdate=27 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180721221818/https://www.indiewire.com/2017/05/yorgos-lanthimos-the-favourite-plot-details-revealed-lesbian-love-triangle-1201817231/|archive-date=21 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Regarding his choice of location, Lanthimos said, \"from the beginning, I had this image of these lonely characters in (a) huge space\".<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nPrior to principal photography, Lanthimos engaged the main actors in an unorthodox rehearsal process that lasted three weeks. The actors \"delivered their lines while trying to tie themselves in knots, jumping from carpet tile to carpet tile, or writhing around on the floor\", according to the ''New York Times''.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/magazine/yorgos-lanthimoss-director-favourite.html|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Polarizing Visions|last=Kleeman|first=Alexandra|date=21 November 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=23 January 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071519/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/11/21/magazine/yorgos-lanthimoss-director-favourite.html|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> A Coleman said, \"He had us do all sorts of things that keep you from thinking about what your lines mean\".<ref name=\":1\" /> According to Weisz, one exercise involved the actors linking arms to create a \"human pretzel\".<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/rachel-weisz-the-favourite-interview.html|title=Rachel Weisz: 'When Women Are Together, There's a Lot of Freedom'|last=Handler|first=Rachel|date=23 November 2018|website=www.vulture.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071732/https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/rachel-weisz-the-favourite-interview.html|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> \"Somebody's butt is in your face, your face is in their butt, and you're saying the lines for a really serious, dramatic scene while doing that\", she said.<ref name=\":2\" /> According to Stone, Lanthimos wanted to see \"how much we could sense each other without seeing each other\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\" /> Lanthimos said he believed the rehearsals allowed the actors \"to not take themselves too seriously, learn the text in a physical way by doing completely irrelevant things to what the scene is about, just be comfortable about making a fool of themselves\".<ref name=\"HWR_gnder\"/>\n\nThe most challenging aspect of filming for cinematographer [[Robbie Ryan (cinematographer)|Robbie Ryan]] was trying to capture fluid camera movement without the use of [[Steadicam]]:\n<blockquote>We explored a lot of ways of trying to have a fluid camera movement that wasn't a Steadicam move. He showed me a film early on called ''[[Angst (1983 film)|Angst]]''&nbsp;... He wanted to try and instil that in the way we shot ''The Favourite'', but it was going to be really difficult to do that. Because of the costumes and just the physicality of it, it was not going to be possible. So we tried to come up with ways of being as fluid as we could with the camera. That was exciting because we came up with some interesting rigs\u2014we explored different gimbal rigs and things like that.<ref name=\":5\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-favourite-robbie-ryan-yorgos-lanthimos-cinematography-interview-1202494103/|title='The Favourite' DP Robbie Ryan Brings Fisheye Lenses & Fluid, Roving Camera To Yorgos Lanthimos' Madcap Period Piece|last=Grobar|first=Matt|date=6 November 2018|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=18 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181119091948/https://deadline.com/2018/11/the-favourite-robbie-ryan-yorgos-lanthimos-cinematography-interview-1202494103/|archive-date=19 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nLanthimos encouraged Ryan to use [[Fisheye lens|fisheye]] and [[Wide-angle lens|wide-angle]] lenses for a majority of the shots, which Ryan believed contributed significantly to the story:<blockquote>The wide lens is twofold. By showing you the whole room and also isolating the character in a small space&nbsp;... you get a feeling of no escape. I think one of the critiques of the film believed it was like a playground that turns into a battleground that turns into a prison. I think that's a very good explanation of what the film tries to get across with these characters. I think the wide lenses are pretty integral to that, as well.<ref name=\":5\" /></blockquote>\n\n===Set design===\nProduction designer Fiona Crombie drew inspiration for the film's colour palette from the chequered, black-and-white marble floor in the Great Hall at Hatfield House, noting that \"a character will walk into a room and you get this incredible wide-shot\u2014we're talking seeing from the floors to the ceilings to the corners. You see ''everything''.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Venice Film Festival crowd-pleaser The Favourite filmed almost exclusively at Hatfield House, Hertfordshire|last=Smith|first=Shona|date=3 September 2018|website=The Location Guide|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123071653/https://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Several rooms at the house were altered, particularly for the Queen's room, which included removing paintings, furniture and other decorations, to \"put our own language into it\". The filmmakers used mostly natural lighting, which proved challenging for the candle-lit night time scenes; Crombie said, \"as you imagine, there are very strict protocols about managing candles&nbsp;... we had to use an enormous number of wax-catchers. But the people who manage Hatfield were very supportive and we negotiated and negotiated, and we would be able to do a vast majority of what we wanted to do\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/#|title=Yorgos Lanthimos's Venice Film Festival crowd-pleaser The Favourite filmed almost exclusively at Hatfield House, Hertfordshire|website=The Location Guide|first=Shona|last=Smith|date=3 September 2018|accessdate=3 September 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180903215552/http://www.thelocationguide.com/2018/09/yorgos-lanthimoss-venice-film-festival-crowd-pleaser-the-favourite-filmed-almost-exclusively-at-hatfield-house-hertfordshire/|archive-date=3 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Costume design===\nBecause she was a fan of his previous work, costume designer [[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]] specifically sought out Lanthimos. Powell wanted Abigail's rise to power to be reflected in her costumes; she said, \"I wanted to give her that vulgarity of the ''nouveau riche'', and her dresses get a little bolder and showier. There's more pattern involved and there are black-and-white stripes&nbsp;... I wanted her to stand out from everybody else as trying too hard\".<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/the-favourite-costumes-sandy-powell-interview/|title=How 'The Favourite' costumes added renegade 'punk' edge to Queen Anne's court|last=Nolfi|first=Joey|date=9 November 2018|website=EW.com|language=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181204150223/https://ew.com/movies/the-favourite-costumes-sandy-powell-interview/|archive-date=4 December 2018|url-status=live|access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Although the film's Queen Anne spends most of her time wearing a nightgown because she is ill, Powell wanted her to have an \"iconic\" look and constructed a robe made of [[ermine]], saying:\n<blockquote>This is the queen at her most queenly, in her ceremonial outfit&nbsp;... I looked at images and real things like it, and normally [this type of garment] would be solid gold, embroidered, and bejewelled, so I thought what else can I do just to give it an air of royalty? Ermine is associated with royalty, it's usually just used as a decoration in small amounts, so I decided to just cover her in it. Because in the rest of the film I have her in a nightgown, not bothering to get dressed every day.<ref name=\":4\" /></blockquote>\n\nAlthough unintentional, Powell drew inspiration for Sarah's contrasting, feminine gowns and her masculine recreational attire from her previous designs for [[Tilda Swinton]]'s character in ''[[Orlando (film)|Orlando]]'' (1992); she said, \"I didn't think about it at the time, it was just subliminal. I do think there is a similarity between the two films because ''Orlando'' was the last unconventional period film I'd done, so there is a similarity.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> Powell stated Lanthimos wanted the women in the film to have natural hair and faces but he wanted the men to wear considerable makeup and large wigs. He said; \"Normally films are filled with men and the women are the decoration in the background, and I've done many of those, so it was quite nice for it to be reversed this time where the women are the centre of the film and the men are the decoration in the background. Of course, they've got serious, important parts, but I think the frivolity of them is quite funny.\"<ref name=\":4\" /> \n\nPowell would deliver the costumes, check they fitted the actors and that the actors had no problems and would leave the set, as Lanthimos requested. She described his directing style:<blockquote>He knew he wanted to be left alone with his actors and his camera. A lot of the time I wasn't aware of how it was going to be. Even when you see the dailies, you can't really tell until it's all put together&nbsp;... But when it all comes together, you're like of course it was all going to come together, he knows exactly what he's doing. We were all part of the jigsaw and he could put all the pieces together.<ref name=\":4\" /></blockquote>\n\n===Soundtrack===\nThe soundtrack of ''The Favourite'' consists mostly of [[Baroque music|baroque]] and [[Classical music|classical]] music, including pieces by [[W. F. Bach|W. F.]] and [[J. S. Bach]], [[George Frideric Handel|Handel]], [[Henry Purcell|Purcell]], [[Antonio Vivaldi|Vivaldi]], and [[Schubert]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/favourite-review-venice-2018-1138544 |title=The Favourite: Film Review |last=Rooney |first=David |date=30 August 2018 |website=THR |publisher=THR |accessdate=12 October 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013014301/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/favourite-review-venice-2018-1138544 |archive-date=13 October 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>. It also includes works by [[20th-century classical music|20th-century composers]] [[Olivier Messiaen]] and [[Luc Ferrari]], and the contemporary British composer [[Anna Meredith]]. The first song to play over the closing credits is \"[[Skyline Pigeon]]\" by [[Elton John]], from his d\u00e9but album ''[[Empty Sky]]'' (1969).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.classicfm.com/discover-music/periods-genres/film-tv/the-favourite-soundtrack-trailer-music-credits/ |title=The Favourite soundtrack: trailer music, tracklisting and credits |last=Shaw Roberts |first=Maddy |date=25 January 2019 |website=FM |publisher=FM |accessdate=19 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nMuch of the music that appears to be contemporaneous with the time in which the film is set was composed later; for example, Bach's organ Fantasia in G minor, Schubert's Piano Trio no. 2 and Piano Sonata in B flat, and Schumann's Piano Quintet.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n\nThe film's sound designer Johnnie Burn said; \"There was no composer on this film; we were working a lot in that space between music and sound\".<ref name=Burn-sound /> He also said he used \"specific [[Equalization (audio)|EQ]] frequencies to shape [atmospheric sound] like score\".<ref name=Burn-sound>{{Cite web|url=http://designingsound.org/2018/12/19/interview-johnnie-burn-on-creating-the-sound-for-the-favourite/|title=Interview: Johnnie Burn on Creating the Sound for The Favourite|language=en-US|access-date=23 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190123223008/http://designingsound.org/2018/12/19/interview-johnnie-burn-on-creating-the-sound-for-the-favourite/|archive-date=23 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nIn May 2017, [[Searchlight Pictures|Fox Searchlight Pictures]] acquired the distribution rights to ''The Favourite''.<ref name=\"wrap\"/> It had its world premiere at the [[75th Venice International Film Festival]] on 30 August 2018.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AlbertoBarbera2|number=1027149478946660353|title=Gioved\u00ec 30 agosto|first=Alberto|last=Barbera|date=8 August 2018|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/venice-film-festival-2018-lineup-full-list-1202433056/|title=Venice Film Festival Lineup: Welles, Coen Brothers, Cuaron, Greengrass, More \u2013 Live|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Nancy|last=Tartaglione|date=25 July 2018|accessdate=25 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421175526/https://deadline.com/2018/07/venice-film-festival-2018-lineup-full-list-1202433056/|archive-date=21 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was screened the film at the [[BFI London Film Festival]] and the [[Telluride Film Festival]], and was the opening-night film at the [[New York Film Festival]].<ref name=\"centerpiece\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/festivals/2018-telluride-film-festival-line-up-1202918919/|title='First Man,' 'Front Runner' and 'Roma' Among 2018 Telluride Film Festival Selections|website=Variety|first=Kristopher|last=Tapley|date=30 August 2018|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180830174303/https://variety.com/2018/film/festivals/2018-telluride-film-festival-line-up-1202918919/|archive-date=30 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://telluridecms-production.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/guides/45th-TFF-program-guide-final.pdf|title=45th Telluride Film Festival Program Guide|website=[[Telluride Film Festival]]|accessdate=30 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012115214/http://telluridecms-production.s3.amazonaws.com/assets/guides/45th-TFF-program-guide-final.pdf|archive-date=12 October 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/the-favourite-56th-new-york-film-festival-opening-night-film-yorgos-lanthimos-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-1202431888/|title='The Favourite' To Open 56th New York Film Festival|website=Deadline Hollywood|first=Mike Jr.|last=Fleming|date=23 July 2018|accessdate=23 July 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724032150/https://deadline.com/2018/07/the-favourite-56th-new-york-film-festival-opening-night-film-yorgos-lanthimos-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-1202431888/|archive-date=24 July 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> ''The Favourite'' was given a [[limited release]] in the United States on 23 November 2018,<ref>{{cite news|last=Hayes|first=Britt|title=Yorgos Lanthimos' 'The Favourite' Sets Awards Season Release|url=https://screencrush.com/lanthimos-the-favourite-fall-release/|work=[[ScreenCrush]]|accessdate=20 April 2018|date=20 April 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180421015555/http://screencrush.com/lanthimos-the-favourite-fall-release/|archive-date=21 April 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"InComp1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-full-lineup-1129426 |title=Venice to Kick Off Awards Season With New Films From Coen Brothers, Luca Guadagnino and Alfonso Cuaron |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |first=Ariston |last=Anderson |date=25 July 2018 |accessdate=25 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180725121213/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/venice-film-festival-unveils-full-lineup-1129426 |archive-date=25 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"InComp2\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/venice-film-festival-full-lineup-1202883737/ |title=Venice Film Festival Lineup: Heavy on Award Hopefuls, Netflix and Star Power |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Nick |last=Vivarelli |date=25 July 2018 |accessdate=25 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322165739/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/venice-film-festival-full-lineup-1202883737/ |archive-date=22 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and was released in the United Kingdom and Ireland on 1 January 2019.<ref name=\"guardukrelease\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/jan/02/uk-box-office-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-free-solo-the-favourite|title=Mary Poppins Returns is Christmas winner at UK box office|website=The Guardian|date=2 January 2019|accessdate=2 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102145722/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/jan/02/uk-box-office-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-free-solo-the-favourite|archive-date=2 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/09/04/favourite-trailer-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-go-head-head-love/|title=The Favourite trailer: Rachel Weisz and Emma Stone go head to head as love rivals in Olivia Colman's bawdy Queen Anne drama|date=4 September 2018|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180909220351/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/films/2018/09/04/favourite-trailer-rachel-weisz-emma-stone-go-head-head-love/|archivedate=9 September 2018|url-status=live|accessdate=17 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n''The Favourite'' was released on [[Digital HD]] on 12 February 2019, and on Blu-ray and DVD on 5 March 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/9304/the-favourite|title=The Favourite (2018)|website=DVDsReleaseDates.com|date=5 March 2019|access-date=15 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329222620/https://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/9304/the-favourite|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\n''The Favourite'' grossed $34.4&nbsp;million in the United States and Canada, and $61.6&nbsp;million in other territories, for a worldwide gross of $95.9&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/> In its opening weekend, the film grossed $422,410 from four theaters, a per-venue average of $105,603. It was the best of 2018, beating ''[[Suspiria (2018 film)|Suspiria]]''{{'}}s $89,903.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/ralph-breaks-the-internet-creed-ii-thanksgiving-box-office-1202505947/|title='Ralph' Scoring 2nd Best Thanksgiving Debut With $84M+; 'Creed II' $55M+ Live-Action Champ; 'Robin Hood' Goes Wrong At $14M+|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=25 November 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=25 November 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181125060917/https://deadline.com/2018/11/ralph-breaks-the-internet-creed-ii-thanksgiving-box-office-1202505947/|archive-date=25 November 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In its second weekend the film made $1.1 million from 34 theaters, an average of $32,500.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/the-possession-of-hannah-grace-grabs-625k-in-thursday-night-previews-1202511705/|title='Ralph' Breaking $25M+ 2nd Weekend; 'Grinch' Steals $203M+; 'Hannah Grace' $6M+ In Slow Post Thanksgiving Period \u2013 Sunday Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=2 December 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=2 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181203182923/https://deadline.com/2018/12/the-possession-of-hannah-grace-grabs-625k-in-thursday-night-previews-1202511705/|archive-date=3 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In its third weekend, following its Golden Globe nominations, it made $1.4 million from 91 theaters, and then $2.6 million from 439 theaters in its fourth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/ralph-breaks-the-internet-the-favourite-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-weekend-box-office-1202516270/|title='Ralph' Keeps No. 1 Away From Greedy 'Grinch' For Third Weekend In A Row With $16M+ \u2013 Sunday Update|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=9 December 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=9 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181208135010/https://deadline.com/2018/12/ralph-breaks-the-internet-the-favourite-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-weekend-box-office-1202516270/|archive-date=8 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\n''The Favourite'' opened across the U.S. in its fifth weekend, grossing $2.1 million from 790 theaters and then $2.4 million in its sixth weekend.<ref>{{cite web|first1=Anthony|last1=D'Alessandro|title='Spider-Verse' Raises $35M+ As 'The Mule' Kicks Up $17M+ In Pre-Christmas Period, But 'Mortal Engines' Breaks Down With $7M+|url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/spider-man-into-the-spider-verse-mortal-engines-clint-eastwood-the-mule-weekend-box-office-1202520137/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=16 December 2018|accessdate=17 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215131941/https://deadline.com/2018/12/spider-man-into-the-spider-verse-mortal-engines-clint-eastwood-the-mule-weekend-box-office-1202520137/|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/on-the-basis-of-sex-best-of-slow-holiday-weekend-start-for-newcomers-beale-street-decent-with-added-runs-specialty-box-office-1202527280/ |title='On The Basis of Sex' Best Of Holiday Weekend Start for Newcomers; 'Beale Street' Surges: Specialty Box Office |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=30 December 2018 |first=Brian |last=Brooks |accessdate=30 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181230235633/https://deadline.com/2018/12/on-the-basis-of-sex-best-of-slow-holiday-weekend-start-for-newcomers-beale-street-decent-with-added-runs-specialty-box-office-1202527280/ |archive-date=30 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> In the film's 10th week of release, following the announcement of its ten Oscar nominations, it was added to 1,023 theaters (for a total of 1,540) and made $2.5 million, an increase of 212% from the previous weekend.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/01/box-office-glass-anne-hathaway-matthew-mcconaughey-serenity-bombs-oscars-best-picture-1202542005/|title='Glass' Leads Again At Weekend B. O., But Only A Handful Of Oscar Best Picture Noms Will See Boost|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=27 January 2018|first=Anthony|last=D'Alessandro|accessdate=2 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128113931/https://deadline.com/2019/01/box-office-glass-anne-hathaway-matthew-mcconaughey-serenity-bombs-oscars-best-picture-1202542005/|archive-date=28 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n{{multiple images\n| total_width = 386\n| direction   = horizontal\n| align       = right\n| image1      = Olivia Colman at Moet BIFA 2014 (cropped).jpg\n| image2      = Emma Stone at Maniac UK premiere (cropped).jpg\n| image3      = Rachel Weisz Deauville 2012 3.jpg\n| footer      = The performances of (left to right) [[Olivia Colman]], [[Emma Stone]], and [[Rachel Weisz]] garnered widespread critical acclaim, with the former winning the [[Academy Award for Best Actress]] and the latter two being both nominated for [[Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress|Best Supporting Actress]].\n}}\n\nOn review aggregator [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an approval rating of 93% based on 387 reviews and an average rating of 8.49/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''The Favourite'' sees Yorgos Lanthimos balancing a period setting against rich, timely subtext\u2014and getting roundly stellar performances from his well-chosen stars\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_favourite_2018|title=The Favourite (2018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|access-date=2 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517210303/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/the_favourite_2018|archive-date=17 May 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gives the film a weighted average score of 90 out of 100, based on 53 critics, indicating \"universal acclaim\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-favourite|title=The Favourite Reviews|website=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=31 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227214338/https://www.metacritic.com/movie/the-favourite|archive-date=27 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[PostTrak]] gave the film 2.5 stars out of 5 and a 37% \"definite recommend\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/12/aquaman-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-new-years-weekend-box-office-1202526812/ |title='Aquaman' Sailing To $51M+ 2nd Weekend; $188M+ Cume Pacing Ahead Of 'Doctor Strange' & 'Guardians Of The Galaxy' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=29 December 2018 |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |accessdate=29 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231133017/https://deadline.com/2018/12/aquaman-mary-poppins-returns-bumblebee-new-years-weekend-box-office-1202526812/ |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn his review for ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', Chris Nashawaty gave the film an \"A\" rating, praising the effective presentation of themes dealing with royalty and associated \"steamier, fact-adjacent subplots\". He wrote, \"It's worth pointing out that ''The Favourite'' is easily Lanthimos' most user-friendly movie, which isn't to say it isn't strange enough to please his fans, just that it may also convert a legion of new ones\".<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Review of 'The Favourite' |last=Nashawaty |first=Chris |date=30 November 2018 |magazine=Entertainment Weekly |page=37}}</ref> [[Peter Travers]] from ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' gave the movie five stars, saying, \"Emma Stone, Rachel Weisz and the mighty Olivia Colman turn a period piece into a caustic comeuppance comedy with fangs and claws&nbsp;... It's a bawdy, brilliant triumph, directed by Greek auteur Yorgos Lanthimos with all the artistic reach and renegade deviltry&nbsp;... ''The Favourite'' belongs to its fierce, profanely funny female trio.\"<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-favourite-movie-review-758119/ |title='The Favourite' Movie Review: Welcome to 'All About Eve' in Corsets |last=Travers |first=Peter |date=20 November 2018 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=2 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181228174739/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/the-favourite-movie-review-758119/ |archive-date=28 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/olivia-colman-interview-758116 |title=Olivia Colman: All Hail 'The Favourite' Queen |last=Grierson |first=Tim |date=19 November 2018 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=3 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181201181034/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/olivia-colman-interview-758116/ |archive-date=1 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n \n[[Anthony Lane]], writing for ''[[The New Yorker]]'', contrasted the film's \u2033unmistakable whiff of&nbsp;... fun\" to the mood of Lanthimos' previous film, ''The Killing of a Sacred Deer'', making note of the strength of the film's female characters.<ref name=\"lane1\">{{cite web|work=The New Yorker|date=26 November 2018|title=Glamour, Wit, and Cunning in The Favourite Yorgos Lanthimos relishes the game of historical reconstruction in a tale of usurpation that borders on a romp.|author=Anthony Lane|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/11/26/glamour-wit-and-cunning-in-the-favourite|accessdate=15 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181215023722/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2018/11/26/glamour-wit-and-cunning-in-the-favourite|archive-date=15 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Two reviewers for ''Entertainment Weekly'', in their assessment of the year's best films, listed the film in first place, with Leah Greenblatt writing, \"You might not actually want to live in Yorgos Lanthimos' sticky tar pit of palace intrigue\u2014a place where Olivia Colman's batty Queen can't trust anyone beyond her pet rabbits, and Rachel Weisz and Emma Stone treat loyalty like a blood sport\u2014but God it's fun as hell to visit\".<ref>Entertainment Weekly. Leah Greenblatt. 2018 Year-End Special issue. Page 32.</ref> David Sims writing for ''[[The Atlantic]]'' magazine found the film to be an effective satire of its historical period, stating; \"Were it just a straightforward comedy, ''The Favourite'' would still be a success. It has plenty of satirical bite, and its plot structure (the roller-coaster-like power struggle between Abigail and Sarah) is an utter blast\".<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/11/the-favourite-movie-review-yorgos-lanthimos-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-olivia-colman/576520/|title=''The Favourite'' Is a Deliciously Nasty Satire of Royal-Court Intrigue|magazine=The Atlantic|first=David|last=Sims|date=23 November 2018|access-date=27 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190228065905/https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/11/the-favourite-movie-review-yorgos-lanthimos-emma-stone-rachel-weisz-olivia-colman/576520/|archive-date=28 February 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n\n{{main|List of accolades received by The Favourite}}\n\n''The Favourite''  has received multiple awards and nominations, and won two [[Venice International Film Festival]] awards: the [[Grand Jury Prize (Venice Film Festival)|Grand Jury Prize]] and the [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.labiennale.org/en/news/collateral-awards-75th-venice-film-festival|title=Collateral Awards Of The 75th Venice Film Festival|publisher=[[Venice Biennale]]|date=7 September 2018|accessdate=8 September 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908213654/http://www.labiennale.org/en/news/official-awards-75th-venice-film-festival|archivedate=9 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> It also won 10 [[British Independent Film Awards 2018|British Independent Film Awards]], including Best British Independent Film; Best Actress; Best Supporting Actress; Best Director, and Best Screenplay. It was nominated for five [[Golden Globe Awards]], including [[Golden Globe Award for Best Motion Picture \u2013 Musical or Comedy|Best Picture]], and was ranked by the [[American Film Institute]] as one of the [[American Film Institute Awards 2018#Top 10 Films|top 10 films of 2018]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AFI Awards 2018|url=http://blog.afi.com/announcing-the-afi-awards-2018-honorees/|publisher=[[American Film Institute]]|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Anne|last=Thompson|title=AFI Awards: Top 10 Films and TV of 2018, Plus Special Award for \u2018Roma\u2019|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/12/afi-awards-top-10-films-tv-2018-roma-1202025280/|work=[[IndieWire]]|date=4 December 2018|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref> It was nominated for ten Oscars at the [[91st Academy Awards]]\u2014including [[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\u2014and was thus tied with ''[[Roma (2018 film)|Roma]]'' as the most-nominated film of that year. Colman won the [[Academy Award for Best Actress]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/2019-oscars-winners-list-academy-awards-1203145638/|title=Oscar Winners 2019: The Complete List|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=24 February 2019|accessdate=24 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Historical accuracy==\n[[File:Closterman, John - Queen Anne - NPG 215.jpg|thumb|Portrait of [[Anne, Queen of Great Britain|Queen Anne]], from the school of [[John Closterman]], {{Circa|1702}}. [[National Portrait Gallery, London|National Portrait Gallery]], London.]]\n\nLanthimos said, \"Some of the things in the film are accurate and a lot aren't\".<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> While the broad outlines of the characters' rivalry for Anne's attentions are true, many of the major episodes and themes of the film are fictional or speculative.<ref name=vulacc>{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/the-favourite-historical-accuracy.html |title=Everything You Need to Know About the 18th-Century World of The Favourite |website=[[Vulture.com]] |first=Nate |last=Jones |date=27 November 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231030625/https://www.vulture.com/2018/11/the-favourite-historical-accuracy.html |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=ewacc>{{cite web |first=Dana |last=Schwartz |url=https://ew.com/movies/2018/12/03/the-favourite-historical-accuracy/ |title=How historically accurate is The Favourite? |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226232743/https://ew.com/movies/2018/12/03/the-favourite-historical-accuracy/ |archive-date=26 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Any evaluation of the sexual aspect to the film's relationships requires understanding of contemporaneous mores and practices, and use of language. Arguments both for and against the possibilities have been discussed by scholars of the era.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thecut.com/2018/12/how-accurate-are-the-sex-scenes-in-the-favourite.html |title=The Real Sex Lives of Historical Queens |first=Anna |last=Silman |website=[[thecut.com]] |date=3 December 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226233153/https://www.thecut.com/2018/12/how-accurate-are-the-sex-scenes-in-the-favourite.html |archive-date=26 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://pictorial.jezebel.com/dissecting-the-real-romantic-rumors-behind-the-favourit-1830593926 |title=Dissecting the Real Romantic Rumors Behind The Favourite With a Queen Anne Biographer |first=Hazel |last=Cills |website=[[Jezebel.com]] |date=27 November 2018 |accessdate=31 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181128011712/https://pictorial.jezebel.com/dissecting-the-real-romantic-rumors-behind-the-favourit-1830593926 |archive-date=28 November 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nHistorians consider it unlikely Anne was physically intimate with her female friends. [[Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough|Sarah Churchill]], who is erroneously referred to in the film as 'Lady Marlborough', had become [[Duke of Marlborough (title)|Duchess of Marlborough]] in 1702. She is known to have tried blackmailing Anne with the threat of publishing private letters between them; this has led some to wonder if the letters contained evidence the two women had a sexual relationship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/5468269/the-favourite-movie-true-story/|title=Entertainment Movies: The True Story Behind The Favourite|website=Time|first=Wilder|last=Davies|date=7 December 2018|access-date=8 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190113200152/http://time.com/5468269/the-favourite-movie-true-story/|archive-date=13 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAlwyn said there was little concern for historical research of characters' backgrounds:\n\n<blockquote>I think people turn up to the rehearsal period thinking maybe they should've read their history books and thought about their characters and their intentions and all of that stuff that you normally think about but Yorgos made it quite clear early on there wasn't going to be much consideration for historical accuracy to a degree. He wasn't too caught up with or concerned about that. He just wanted us to have fun as people, as a cast and to explore the relationships between us, which is what we did.<ref name=\"hracc\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-team-historical-research-behind-british-period-film-1149239|title=N.Y. Film Fest: 'The Favourite' Team on Historical Research Behind British Period Film|first=Hilary|last=Lewis|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=31 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226234031/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/favourite-team-historical-research-behind-british-period-film-1149239|archive-date=26 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref></blockquote> \n\nIn his review of the film, Anthony Lane comments on its anachronisms, saying; \"For Lanthimos and his screenwriters&nbsp;... all historical reconstruction is a game and to pretend otherwise\u2014to nourish the illusion that we can know another epoch as intimately as we do our own\u2014is merest folly\".<ref name=\"lane1\" /> J. R. Kinnard wrote for ''[[PopMatters]]'':\n\n<blockquote>History records that England was ruled for a brief period in the early 18th century by Queen Anne whose physical infirmities were rivalled only by her psychological quirks. She was indeed counseled by her lifelong friend and ''perhaps'' lover, Lady Sarah Churchill{{sic|date=November 2019}}&nbsp;... Finally, there was a chambermaid named Abigail Masham&nbsp;... who infiltrated the highest levels of the royal house and, ''perhaps'', Queen Anne's bed. The rest is left to the sordid imagination of one of the world's most fascinating filmmakers.<ref name=\"pmacc\">{{cite web |first=J. R. |last=Kinnard |url=https://www.popmatters.com/film-the-favourite-2621519607.html |title=Queen Anne Costume Drama 'The Favourite' Dazzles with Humor, Tragedy, Weirdness |work=[[PopMatters]] |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=December 31, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231164550/https://www.popmatters.com/film-the-favourite-2621519607.html |archive-date=31 December 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref></blockquote>\n\nQueen Anne was close to [[Prince George of Denmark|Prince George, Duke of Cumberland]] (died October 1708), her Danish husband, who was not portrayed in the film but was alive for most of the time covered.<ref name=\"vulacc\" /> Anne's health problems were severe enough that she may have had little sex drive.<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> Some episodes are fictional, such as Masham's attempt to poison the Duchess of Marlborough.<ref name=\"ewacc\" /> Anne's loss of children is accurate but she did not keep rabbits, which at that time were considered food or pests.<ref name=\"bbcacc\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.historyextra.com/period/stuart/real-history-the-favourite-film-queen-anne-olivia-colman-hannah-greig/|title=The Favourite: the real history behind the new Queen Anne film|website=History Extra|date=27 February 2019|access-date=14 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190115023420/https://www.historyextra.com/period/stuart/real-history-the-favourite-film-queen-anne-olivia-colman-hannah-greig/|archive-date=15 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Sequel==\nEmma Stone has indicated an interest in a possible sequel that would follow the political careers of the male characters in the film. According to ''[[Hollywood Reporter]]'', \"[Stone] added that if there was a sequel, she hoped that it would follow Nicholas Hoult's character [[Robert Harley, 1st Earl of Oxford and Earl Mortimer|Robert Harley]]. 'Hopefully, it would be Harley's [Nicholas Hoult's pompous parliamentarian] story,' she said. 'I would love to see where Harley goes from there.'\"<ref name=\"hollywoodreporter.com\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.foxsearchlight.com/thefavourite/}}\n* {{IMDb title|5083738}}\n* {{Metacritic film|the-favourite}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|m/the_favourite_2018}}\n\n{{Yorgos Lanthimos}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title= [[List of accolades received by The Favourite|Awards for ''The Favourite'']]\n|list=\n{{BAFTA Best British Film}}\n{{BIFA BestBritishFilm}}\n{{Broadcast Film Critics Association Award for Best Cast}}\n{{European Film Award for Best Film}}\n{{European Film Award for Best Comedy}}\n{{London Film Critics Circle Award for British Film of the Year}}\n{{Satellite Award for Best Cast \u2013 Motion Picture}}\n{{Venice Film Festival Special Jury Prize}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Favourite, The}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s biographical films]]\n[[Category:2010s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:American biographical films]]\n[[Category:American comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:American LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:BAFTA winners (films)]]\n[[Category:Biographical films about English royalty]]\n[[Category:British biographical films]]\n[[Category:British comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:British historical comedy films]]\n[[Category:British LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Comedy films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Anne of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of Sarah Churchill, Duchess of Marlborough]]\n[[Category:Cultural depictions of John Churchill, Duke of Marlborough]]\n[[Category:Drama films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Female bisexuality in film]]\n[[Category:Irish biographical films]]\n[[Category:Irish comedy films]]\n[[Category:Irish comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Irish films]]\n[[Category:Irish historical films]]\n[[Category:Irish LGBT-related films]]\n[[Category:Lesbian-related films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:LGBT-related films based on actual events]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1700s]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 1710s]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Yorgos Lanthimos]]\n[[Category:Films featuring a Best Actress Academy Award-winning performance]]\n[[Category:Films featuring a Best Musical or Comedy Actress Golden Globe winning performance]]\n[[Category:Film4 Productions films]]\n[[Category:Fox Searchlight Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Venice Grand Special Jury Prize winners]]\n", "name_user": "Kailash29792", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Favourite"}
{"title_page": "Coropuna", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{short description|Volcano in Peru}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox mountain\n| name              = Coropuna\n| other_name        = Nevado Coropuna\n| etymology         = [[Coropuna#Etymology|Etymology]]\n| native_name       = {{lang|qu|Qhuru Puna}}\n| native_name_lang  = [[Quechua languages|Quechua]]\n| translation       = \"Golden mountain\", \"cold, snowy\" or \"cut off at the top\"\n| pronunciation     = \n| photo             = Coropuna Volcano.jpg\n| photo_alt         = A snow-covered mountain with two hump-like summits rises above an unvegetated landscape with a lake\n| photo_caption     = \n| map               = Peru\n| map_alt           = A topographic map of Peru within South America\n| map_image         = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_relief        = \n| map_size          = \n| coordinates       = {{coord|15|33|S|72|39|W|display=title,inline}}\n| coordinates_ref   = {{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}}\n| elevation_m       = 6377\n| elevation_ref     = <ref name=\"GVP\" />\n| location          = \n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| prominence        = \n| prominence_m      = <!-- Needed -->\n| prominence_ref    = \n| isolation         = \n| isolation_km      = \n| isolation_mi      = \n| isolation_ref     = \n| parent_peak       = \n| listing           = \n| range             = [[Cordillera Occidental (Peru)|Cordillera Occidental]], [[Peru|Peruvian]] [[Andes]]\n| type              = [[Stratovolcano]] complex\n| age               = [[Early Pliocene]]-[[Holocene]]<br>~5 Ma - 1 ka\n| geology           = [[Coropuna#Geology|Geology]]\n| volcanic_belt     = [[Andean Volcanic Belt]]\n| volcanic_arc      = [[Central Volcanic Zone]]\n| volcanic_field    = \n| last_eruption     = 1,100 [[Margin of error|\u00b1]] 100 or 700 \u00b1 200 years ago\n| first_ascent      = [[Coropuna#First ascent|First ascents]]\n| easiest_route     = \n| normal_route      = \n| access            = \n}}\n'''Coropuna''' is a [[Volcano#Dormant|dormant]] [[Complex volcano|compound volcano]] located in the [[Andes]] mountains of southeast-central [[Peru]]. The upper reaches of Coropuna consist of several [[wikt:perennially|perennially]] snowbound conical summits, lending it the name '''Nevado Coropuna''' in Spanish. The complex extends over an area of {{convert|240|km2|abbr=off}} and its highest summit reaches an altitude of {{convert|6377|m|abbr=off}} above sea level. This makes the Coropuna complex the [[List of mountains in Peru|third-highest of Peru]]. Its thick ice cap is the most extensive in Earth's [[Tropics|tropical zone]], with several [[Glacier morphology#Outlet Glaciers|outlet glaciers]] stretching out to lower altitudes. Below an elevation of {{convert|5000|m|abbr=off}}, there are various vegetation belts which include trees, [[peat bog]]s, grasses and also [[agricultural]] areas and [[pastures]].\n\nThe Coropuna complex consists of several [[stratovolcano]]s. These are composed chiefly of [[ignimbrite]]s{{efn|[[Volcanic ash|Ash]] flows{{sfn|Herrmann|Bucksch|2014|p=1513}}}} and [[lava flow]]s on a [[basement (geology)|basement]] formed by [[Middle Miocene]] ignimbrites and lava flows. The Coropuna complex has been active for at least five million years, with the bulk of the current cone having been formed during the [[Quaternary]].{{efn|The age of man, including [[Pleistocene]] and [[Holocene]].{{sfn|Herrmann|Bucksch|2014|p=2296}}}} Coropuna has had two or three [[Holocene]] eruptions {{nowrap|2,100 \u00b1 200}} and either {{nowrap|1,100 \u00b1 100}} or {{nowrap|700 \u00b1 200 years}} ago which generated lava flows, plus an additional eruption which may have taken place some 6,000&nbsp;years ago. Current activity occurs exclusively in the form of [[hot spring]]s.\n\nCoropuna is located {{convert|150|km|abbr=off}} northwest of the city of [[Arequipa]]. People have lived on the slopes of Coropuna for millennia. The mountain was regarded as sacred by the [[Inca Empire|Inca]] and several archaeological sites have been discovered there, including the Inca sites of [[Mawk'allaqta, Castilla|Maucallacta]] and [[Acchaymarca]]. The mountain was considered one of the most important Inca religious sites in their realm; human sacrifices were performed on its slopes, Coropuna forms part of many local legends and the mountain is worshiped to the present day.\n\nThe ice cap of Coropuna, which during the [[Last Glacial Maximum]] (LGM) had expanded to over {{convert|500|km2|abbr=on}}, has been in [[Retreat of glaciers since 1850|retreat since at least 1850]]. Estimates published in 2018 imply that the ice cap will persist until about 2120. The retreat of the Coropuna glaciers threatens the water supply of tens of thousands of people relying upon its [[Drainage basin|watershed]], and interaction between volcanic activity and glacial effects has generated [[mudflow]]s that could be hazardous to surrounding populations. Because of this, the Peruvian geological agency, [[INGEMMET]], monitors Coropuna and has published a hazard map for the volcano.\n\n== Name and etymology ==\nIn [[Quechuan languages|Quechua]], {{lang|qu|puna}} means \"plateau\", and {{lang|qu|coro}} is a common component of toponyms such as with [[Coro Coro, Bolivia]], though its etymology is unclear.<ref name=\"Holmer1960\" /> The name may mean {{lang|qu|Qoripuna}}, \"Puna of Gold\",<ref name=\"Trawick2003\" /> \"golden mountain\",<ref name=\"MINCETUR2019\" /> \"cold, snowy\" or \"cut off at the top\".<ref name=\"Wilson2009\" /> The name is also spelled {{lang|qu|Qhuru Puna}}.<ref name=\"Besom2010\" /> The mountain is also called Nevado Coropuna; \"Nevado\" is the Spanish word for \"snowy\".{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=305}} There is another volcano in the [[Andagua volcanic field|Andahua volcanic field]] which has the same name, but is completely separate.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=66}}\n\n== Geography and geomorphology ==\nCoropuna lies in the [[Andes]] of Peru,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} on the border between the [[Castilla Province|Castilla]] and [[Condesuyos Province]]s{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=176}} of the [[Arequipa Department]].{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=176}}{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=16}} Towns around the volcano belong to the [[Chuquibamba District|Chuquibamba]], [[Machaguay District|Machaguay]], [[Pampacolca District|Pampacolca]] and [[Viraco District]]s.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} The volcano can be reached on paved roads through the town of Andahua, either from [[Arequipa]] or through [[Aplao]] from the [[Pan-American Highway]].{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=4}} Roads also pass along the northern and western sides of the volcano.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}}\n\n=== Regional ===\nThe Andes stretch northwards along the western coast of South America from [[Tierra del Fuego]] to [[Venezuela]] forming the longest mountain chain in the world.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=61}} More regionally, the volcano is in the {{interlanguage link|Cordillera Ampato|es}}, a mountain range which lies at an average of {{convert|100|km}} from the Pacific coastline,{{sfn|Schotterer|Delachaux|Ledru|Angelis|2009|p=28}} and contains nearly one hundred glaciers.{{sfn|Racoviteanu|Manley|Arnaud|Williams|2007|p=111}}\n\nCoropuna is in the [[Central Volcanic Zone]] of the Andes,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}}{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=287}} which contains 44&nbsp;stratovolcanoes{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=63}}{{Spaced en dash}}including many of the world's highest{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=287}}{{Spaced en dash}}and several glaciated volcanoes.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=3}} Besides Coropuna, some of the latter are [[Sara Sara]], [[Solimana (volcano)|Solimana]], [[Mismi]], [[Ampato]], [[Hualca Hualca]], [[Sabancaya]], [[Chachani]], [[Misti]], [[Ubinas]], [[Huaynaputina]], [[Tutupaca]], [[Yucamane]] and [[Casiri (Tacna)|Casiri]].{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=62}}{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=247}} Also found nearby are [[Neogene]]-age [[caldera]]s.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=62}} Sixteen volcanoes in Peru are active or potentially active.{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|p=4}}\n\nThere is no habitation on Coropuna above {{convert|5200|m}},{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=7}} but numerous villages dot the lower slopes.{{efn|Villages on the lower slopes of Corpuna include: [[Ocororuro]], [[Arma (Peru)|Arma]], [[Maucallacta (town)|Maucallacta]], [[Purhua Purhua]], [[Chaupipuna (town)|Chaupipuna]], [[Utchu-Amayani]], [[Torilla (Peruvian town)|Torilla]], [[Patilla (town)|Patilla]], [[Pallca (town)|Pallca]], [[Alco Llacta]], [[Viques (town)|Viques]], [[Campanayo]], [[Pecoy]], [[Tagre]], [[Pillcull]], [[Chupacca]], [[Chipcama]], [[Cabra Grande]], [[Pampacolca (town)|Pampacolca]], [[Huncor]], [[Huanjo]], [[Santa Maria (town in Peru)|Santa Maria]], [[Toma de Hayllaura]] and [[Huayllaura]].{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}}}} [[Agriculture]] and [[animal husbandry]] are the most common economic activities;{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=61}} there are [[copper]] and [[gold]] [[mining|mine]]s as well.{{sfn|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|Steinm\u00fcller|1998|p=52}} The city of Arequipa lies {{convert|150|km|abbr=on}} to the southeast.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}}\n\n=== Local ===\n\n==== General outline ====\n[[File:CoropunaSouthViewUSGS.jpg|thumb|right|alt=An elongated snow-covered ridge rises from a dark landscape with valleys|Coropuna seen from the south in 1988]]\nSeen from above, Coropuna has a pear-shaped outline{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} and is a {{convert|20|km|abbr=on}} east{{en dash}}west ridge{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=16}} that features four summits that are separated by broad [[Saddle (landform)|saddles]].{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}}{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} In addition, there is another summit north of the east{{en dash}}west trend.<ref name=\"GVP\" /> A {{convert|5558|m|abbr=on}} high subsidiary peak named Cerro Cuncaicha lies east of Coropuna,{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=105}} it is a stratovolcano.<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> Coropuna covers a surface area of {{convert|240|km2}}{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}} and its various main summits rise about {{convert|3|km|spell=in}} above the surrounding plateau.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=3}}\n\nThe volcano is formed from alternating layers of ignimbrite and lava,{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} and consists of coalesced stratovolcanoes{{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=124}} and seven separate [[Lava dome#Lava coul\u00e9es|coulee]]s.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}} Ice cover makes discerning its structure difficult,{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} but about{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} six separate peaks{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}}{{sfn|Bullard|1962|p=444}}<ref name=\"IGdP2018\" /> as well as six not readily recognisable [[summit crater]]s  have been counted.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}}{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} Additional [[lava dome]]s form a southeastward trending line on the southwestern side of the volcano{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} and [[dike (geology)|dike]]s crop out close to Lake [[Pallarcocha]].{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} Coropuna overlies the margin of a buried caldera.<ref name=\"Yates2013\" />\n\nThe higher elevations of Coropuna consist of an ice cap and glaciated terrain{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}} but old\u00a0[[lava flow]]s with gentle slopes{{sfn|Racoviteanu|Manley|Arnaud|Williams|2007|p=112}} and [[Lava|blocky lava]] crop out from underneath the ice.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=63}} Regions of [[hydrothermal]]ly altered rocks, lava flows, [[pyroclastic flow]]s and areas covered by [[volcanic ash]] occur all around the mountain.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} Glacial activity has eroded these volcanic rocks, carving valleys into them or removing them altogether.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=104}} This process created [[U-shaped valley]]s such as Buenavista, Cospanja and Tuilaqui on the southern flank, and glacial valleys such as Chaque, Mapa Mayo, R\u00edo Blanco, Torcom and Ullulo on the northern slopes.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=12}} Glacial valleys of Coropuna are up to {{convert|300|m|abbr=on}} deep and {{convert|7|km|abbr=on|spell=in}} long.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=19}}\n\nThere are several collapse [[Cliff|scarps]] on the mountain, especially around its central sector.<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> A [[sector collapse]] took place on the southwestern flank and formed a [[landslide]] deposit as well as a horseshoe-shaped valley that was later filled by glaciers.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=19}} Also on the southern side, mud-water flow deposits have been found in the Capiza River valley and appear to relate to Coropuna;{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}} at least eight such debris flows have been identified.{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=120}} [[Lahar]]s (mudflows) have reached the [[Colca River]] valley.{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=118}} Lahars are dangerous phenomena owing to their high speed and density, causing large scale destruction and fatalities.{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}}\n\n==== Lakes and rivers ====\n[[File:COROPUNA LAKE - panoramio.jpg|thumb|right|alt=A barren, rock-strewn terrain with two ice-covered mountains in the background; to the left lies a blue lake and to the right a scarp|Coropuna seen from Lake Pallacocha]]\nLakes  lie on the flanks of the volcano.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=5}} These include [[Lake Pallarcocha]] on the southwestern flank on formerly glaciated terrain,{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|pp=3\u20134}} Laguna Pucaylla on Coropuna's northeastern side and Laguna Caracara on the southeastern side. A number of streams and rivers originate on the mountain. Clockwise around Coropuna, these include Quebrada Chauqui-Huayco, Rio Amayani on the northern side, Quebrada Chinchina/Infernillo, Quebrada Jollpa, Quebrada Caspanja with the lake Laguna Caracara, Quebrada Buena Vista, Quebrada Tuallqui, Rio Testane on the southern flank, Rio de Huayllaura on the southwestern flank, Quebrada del Apacheta,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}} Quebrada Sigue Chico{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2515}} and Quebrada Sepulturayoc on the western flank.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}} The Rio Blanco and Rio Amayani eventually form the [[Rio Arma]],{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=21}} while the Rio Capiza discharges water from Coropuna to the Colca River.{{sfn|Caldas Vidal|1993|p=10}} During the [[dry season]], most of these rivers do not carry substantial discharge.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}}\n\nThe volcano is situated on a [[drainage divide]].{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5878}} To the west the Rio Arma is a tributary of the [[Oco\u00f1a River]], while to the east the Colca River is part of the [[Majes River]] watershed.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=104}} An [[endorheic]] area that receives meltwater from the volcano also exists northeast from Coropuna, on Pampa Pucaylla{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}} where the lake of the same name lies.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}}\n\n==== Surrounding terrain ====\nCoropuna rises {{convert|2|km|abbr=on}} above the surrounding terrain{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}}{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} from a base elevation of {{convert|4500|m|abbr=on}},{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=16}} and about {{convert|3.5|km|abbr=on}} on the southern side where the Rio Llacllaja has incised the underlying [[basement (geology)|basement]]{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}}{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} almost to the foot of the volcano, forming sharp, amphitheatre-like valleys.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}} In general, many deep valleys cut into the flanks of the volcano{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|p=9}} and give the mountain an \"impressive topographic relief\".<ref name=\"GVP\"/>\n\nThe region is characterised by high plateaus separated by deep [[canyon]]s, including some of the world's deepest gorges{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2515}} that reach depths of {{convert|600|-|3000|m|abbr=on}}.{{sfn|Thouret|Gunnell|Jicha|Paquette|2017|p=2}} Apart from river erosion, giant landslides have affected the [[Altiplano]] below Coropuna,{{sfn|G\u00f3mez|Mac\u00edas|Arce|S\u00e1nchez-Nu\u00f1ez|2012|p=1025}} such as the Chuquibamba landslide, which took place over the last 120,000{{nbsp;}}years in the form of multiple collapse events within a [[fault (geology)|fault]]-controlled basin.{{sfn|Thouret|Gunnell|Jicha|Paquette|2017|p=14}}\n\nGeomorphologically, Coropuna lies at the edge of the Altiplano high plateau on the [[Cordillera Occidental (Peru)|Western Cordillera]] mountain range;{{sfn|Kuentz|Mera|Ledru|Thouret|2007|p=1764}} in the Central Andes this mountain chain is split into two ranges{{Spaced en dash}}the western and the eastern Cordillera{{Spaced en dash}}separated by the Altiplano.{{sfn|Bullard|1962|p=443}} The Pucuncho Basin{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=305}} and [[Firura]] volcano lie north of Coropuna, while Solimana volcano is northwest from Coropuna.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} Sara Sara is another volcano in the area.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}} A large [[lava dome]] lies northwest of Coropuna{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}} while [[Puma Ranra (Castilla-Condesuyos)|Cerro Pumaranra]], a {{convert|5089|m|abbr=on}}{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=105}} eroded volcano, is to the northeast.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} {{convert|19|km|abbr=on}} west-southwest from Coropuna lies the {{convert|4855|m|abbr=on}} high [[Antapuna]],{{sfn|Dornbusch|2002|p=116}} while the [[Andahua]] \"[[Valley of the Volcanoes]]\" is {{convert|20|km|abbr=on}} east-northeast of Coropuna.{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=298}}\n\n=== Elevation and size ===\n[[File:Coropuna Este (30293366316).jpg|thumb|right|alt=A gentle, ice-covered ridge with hump-like summits|Coropuna Este]]\nCoropuna is the largest{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=214}} and highest volcano in Peru, highest peak of the {{ill|Cordillera Ampato|es}}{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} and the third-highest mountain in Peru.<ref name=\"Trawick2003\" /><ref name=\"MINCETUR2019\" /> The highest point of Coropuna is the northwestern dome<ref name=\"GVP\" />{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}} named Coropuna Casulla,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} with {{convert|6377|m}} elevation.<ref name=\"GVP\" /><ref name=\"MdA2019\" /><ref name=\"IGdP2018\" /> [[Mountaineering]] sources also cite an elevation of {{convert|6425|m|abbr=on}} for the El Toro summit,<ref name=\"Biggar2015\" /><ref name=\"AAC1990\" /> which would make Coropuna the 22nd highest mountain in the Andes.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=63}}{{efn|Other estimates of its height are {{convert|6380|m|abbr=on}};{{sfn|Kuentz|Ledru|Thouret|2011b|p=1216}}{{sfn|Thouret|Juvigne|Mari\u00f1o|Moscol|2002|p=3}} {{convert|6426|m|abbr=on}}{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}}{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}}{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} on the western summit;{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}} {{convert|6446|m|abbr=on}};{{sfn|Silverio|Herold|Peduzzi|2010|p=314}} and {{convert|6450|m}}.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=305}}}}\n\nEstimates on the height of Coropuna have changed over time. In the 19th century, it was one of the candidates for \"highest mountain in Peru\", with the Mapa del Per\u00fa (Map of Peru) of [[Antonio Raimondi]] giving an estimated height of {{convert|6949|m|abbr=on}}; other candidates were peaks in the [[Cordillera Blanca]].{{sfn|Wise|2004|p=97}} In 1910 it was believed that the volcano was over {{convert|23000|ft|m|order=flip|abbr=on}} high and thus the highest mountain in South America ahead of [[Aconcagua]],<ref name=\"Bingham2010\" /><ref name=\"Bandelier1910\" /> although a North American expedition during the preceding year had determined that Coropuna was not the highest as they only found an elevation of {{convert|6615|m|abbr=on}} and [[Huascaran]] is higher than this.{{sfn|Wise|2004|p=98}} Varying snow elevations might also lead to varying height estimates.<ref name=\"Biggar2015\" />\n\nCoropuna has several summits (up to ten overall according to one count){{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} which exceed {{convert|6000|m|abbr=on}} elevation,{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5878}} plus a {{convert|5623|m|abbr=on}} northern summit.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} Those with individual names are the northwestern Coropuna Casulla at {{convert|6377|m|abbr=on}},{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=35}} El Toro,<ref name=\"Biggar2015\" /><ref name=\"AAC1990\" /> the western Nevado Pallacocha at {{convert|6171|m|abbr=on}}, the central Coropuna Central II at {{convert|6161|m|abbr=on}},<ref name=\"Hernandez2013\" /> Escalera in the western sector of the volcano, Paiche in the central sector,<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> and Coropuna Este{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=308}} and Yana Ranra in the eastern sector.<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" />\n\n== Ice cap ==\n[[File:Nevado Coropuna, Peru.JPG|thumb|right|Coropuna\u2019s ice cap seen from space in 2010|alt=A roughly pear-shaped ice area, from which valleys emanate, lies within a multicolored landscape, as seen from a satellite image]]\nCoropuna features the largest [[ice cap]] of the tropics.{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}} As of 2014 it was {{convert|8.5|km|abbr=on}} wide and {{convert|11|km|abbr=on}} long.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}} It is larger than the [[Quelccaya Ice Cap]] {{convert|250|km|abbr=on}} farther northeast, which was considered to be the largest,{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}}{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=101}} but has since shrunk to a size less than Coropuna's.<ref name=\"NOAA2018\" /> A subsidiary peak named Cerro Cuncaicha, east of Coropuna, has a small ice cap as well.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}} In general, Peruvian glaciers form the bulk of the world's tropical glaciers.{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5876}} The ice cap consists of three ice domes and many glaciers.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}} Perennial [[snow field]]s are present on Coropuna, sometimes making it hard to measure the true extent of glaciation or glacier retreat.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}}\n\nOn average, the ice cap of Coropuna is about {{convert|80.8|m|abbr=on}} thick,{{sfn|Silverio|Herold|Peduzzi|2010|p=320}} with maximum thicknesses exceeding {{convert|180|m|abbr=on}}.{{sfn|Silverio|Herold|Peduzzi|2010|p=321}} In 2003{{en dash}}2004 the ice cap had a volume of about {{convert|3.69|km3}} [[snow water equivalent]]s.{{sfn|Silverio|2018|p=49}} [[Ice core]]s have been taken from the Coropuna ice cap{{sfn|Weide|Fritz|Brinson|Thompson|2017|p=3}} and from a summit crater;<ref name=\"Lin2018\" /> one of these ice cores covers a timespan beginning from 20,000{{nbsp;}}years ago.{{sfn|Engel|Skrzypek|Chuman|\u0160efrna|2014|p=63}}\n\n[[Penitente (snow formation)|Penitente]]s{{sfn|Schotterer|Delachaux|Ledru|Angelis|2009|p=28}} reaching heights of {{convert|2|m|abbr=on}}{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=67}} and [[serac]]s (blocks of ice in glaciers delimited by cracks) occur on the glaciers,{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} while debris cover is rare.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=178}} Mudflows (lahars) originated from the ice cap{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} and left deposits at the bottom of valleys.{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|p=9}}\n\n=== Glaciers and periglacial phenomena ===\nA number of glaciers flow down from the ice cap,{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} their number variously estimated to be  15,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} 17{{sfn|Silverio|2018|p=45}}{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5878}} and 23.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}} Some glaciers have been named; on the southwestern flank two glaciers are known as {{lang|es|Azufrioc}}&nbsp;1 and 2, three {{lang|es|Rio Blanco}}&nbsp;1 through 3 and six {{lang|es|Tuialqui}} 1 through 6.{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=7}} Eighteen separate accumulation areas have been found as well.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=24}} There are no substantive valley glaciers presently on Coropuna{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} and some glaciers, especially in the eastern side, emanate from [[cirque]]s.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} The ongoing downward movement of the ice on Coropuna produces [[icequake]]s.<ref name=\"IGdP2018\" />\n\nGlaciers descend to elevations of about {{convert|5100|to|5300|m|abbr=on}} on the southern flank, and to about {{convert|5500|to|5800|m|abbr=on}} on the northern flank.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}}{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}}{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}} This is higher than the [[freezing level]], owing to the dry climate;{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} the freezing level at Coropuna lies at about {{convert|4900|m|abbr=on}} elevation.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} In 2001, the ice limits were located at elevations of {{convert|5300|m|abbr=on}} on the southern and at {{convert|5600|m|abbr=on}} on the northern flank.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=9}}\n\n[[Moraine]]s are mostly found on Coropuna's northern and southern side{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=10}} and reach lengths of {{convert|3|to|8|km|abbr=on}}, with longer moraines on the northern flank.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=12}} In general, moraines on Coropuna are steep and have prominent crests as they are little eroded.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}} Grey-coloured, fresh moraines up to {{convert|500|m|abbr=on}} from the ice cap may reflect the position of the glaciers before the onset of [[glacier retreat]] which has left small mounds that often contain ice between these moraines and the ice cap{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}} and small, discontinuous moraines.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=310}}\n\nApart from normal glaciers, 78&nbsp;[[rock glacier]]s have been counted on Coropuna, but only 11 of them are considered to be active.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=28}} [[Permafrost]] has also been reported on Coropuna.<ref name=\"UbedaYoshikawa2015\" /> [[Cryoturbation]],{{sfn|Gal\u00e1n|Linares Perea|2012|p=15}} [[gelifluction]], [[patterned ground]]s,{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} [[solifluction]]{{sfn|Gal\u00e1n|Linares Perea|2012|p=48}} and other [[periglacial]] landforms are noticeable{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} at over {{convert|4500|m|abbr=on}} elevation.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}}\n\n==== Recent area and retreat ====\n[[File:Coropuna ice cap extent 1950-2015.svg|alt=While individual trend series of the extent of Coropuna's ice cap often heavily diverge from each other, a strong declining tendency is noticeable|thumb|upright=1.35|Extent of the ice cap over the years, from various sources:{{efn|As cited in Forget et al (2008),{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}} Palenque et al (2018),{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=101}} Marinque et al (2018),{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=178}} Silverio (2018),{{sfn|Silverio|2018|p=45}} Silverio, Herold & Peduzzi (2010),{{sfn|Silverio|Herold|Peduzzi|2010|p=318}} and Silverio & Jaquet (2012).{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5882}}}}]]\n\nMeasuring the surface area of Coropuna's ice cap is difficult as seasonal snow can be mistaken for ice,{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=180}} and different studies come to various conclusions about the retreat rate, due to the use of different time periods and methodological practices. However, all studies conclude that the net retreat trend is obvious and that the ice cap is diminishing.<ref name=\"Veettil2017\" /> Retreat rates shortly before 2009 reached 13{{nbsp;}}per cent in only 21{{nbsp;}}years.{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=12}} Between 1980 and 2014 the ice cap shrank at a rate of {{convert|0.409|km2/year|mi2/year||abbr=}}{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=179}} with a 2015 estimate amounting to {{convert|0.5|km2/year|mi2/year}},<ref name=\"Kochtitzky2015\" /> and a brief slowdown observed during the late 1990s and early 2000s.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=181}} Total shrinkage has been estimated to amount to 26{{nbsp;}}per cent between 1962 and 2000, and by 18{{nbsp;}}per cent between 1955 and 2007.{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}}\n\nThe Coropuna ice cap retreat follows the pattern recorded elsewhere in Peru such as in the Cordillera Blanca, [[Cordillera Vilcanota]] and the mountains Ampato, Quelccaya and Sabancaya.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=31}} All of this retreat is attributed to [[global warming]],{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=9}} and tends to increase during [[El Ni\u00f1o]] years owing to a drier climate. The glaciers lose mass through both [[sublimation (phase transition)|sublimation]] and [[melting]]. This meltwater rarely forms streams, though some do exist. The Quebrada Ullulo on the northern side is the largest such meltwater stream.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}}\n\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" widths=\"360\">\nFile:Coropuna glacier areas.png|alt=The ice area has been steadily decreasing since 1950 and it may completely disappear in the future|Glacier trends and extrapolation\nFile:Coropuna ice profile.png|alt=Radar display of a transect through the ice cap|Ice profile\nFile:Ice loss Coropuna-2.png|alt=The thickest ice lies in the western portion, while marginal ice is thinner|Ice thickness\nFile:Radar profile and glacier evolution Coropuna.png|alt=A number of transects across the ice cap have been made, with the ice cap retreating at its margins|Ice schematics\n</gallery>\n\n=== Glacial history ===\nBefore the first human settlement of the area,{{sfn|Sandweiss|\u00c1lvarez|Reid|Leach|2014|p=468}}{{sfn|Sandweiss|\u00c1lvarez|Reid|Leach|2014|pp=466\u2013467}} the ice cap on Coropuna was much larger than today, with its surface exceeding {{convert|500|km2}}{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=102}} and its glaciers descending to much lower elevations.{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2515}} Additionally, glaciers also expanded from the mountains Pumaranra, Pucaylla and Cuncaicha to the east of Coropuna.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=107}} They covered the Pampa Pucaylla northeast from Coropuna and descended the Jellojello valley and other valleys to the east.{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=3}} [[Glacial valley]]s radiate from Coropuna,{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} and [[glaciofluvial]] landforms are associated with moraines.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}}\n\nRegional climate oscillations are recorded in the ice masses of Coropuna.{{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=24}} The glacial history of the volcano has been reconstructed with [[tephrochronology]] (using dated [[tephra]] layers such as those from the 1600 Huaynaputina eruptions), [[radiocarbon dating]]{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}} and [[surface exposure dating]] using [[helium-3]].{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} Three separate moraine generations<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> and about five separate glacial stages have been recorded on the volcano.<ref name=\"GSA2007\" /> Glacial advances on Coropuna appear to be synchronous to advances of the ice sheets in the [[Northern Hemisphere]].{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=30}} Glaciers developed on other mountains in the region as well.{{sfn|Dornbusch|2002|p=123}}\n\n==== Last glacial maximum ====\nDuring the [[Last Glacial Maximum]] (LGM) 25,000{{en dash}}20,000{{nbsp;}}years ago,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=308}} valley glaciers on Coropuna were considerably longer than today.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}} The longest glacier, at {{convert|12|km|abbr=on}}, was in the Quebrada Ullulo.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=308}} The glaciers had a cover of boulders and [[gravel]] and formed tall moraines, and both lateral and terminal moraines where [[outlet glacier]]s ended. At the crest, these moraines were as much as {{convert|100|m|abbr=on}} high, {{convert|8|km|abbr=on}} long, and {{convert|5|-|10|m|abbr=on}} wide.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|pp=307\u2013308}} On the northern flank, moraine systems have been observed in the Santiago, Ullulo,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=39}} Kea\u00f1a, Que\u00f1ua Ranra, Cuncaicha, Pommulca and Huajra Huire valleys,{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}} while the southeastern flank was covered by glaciers in the Yanaorco, Viques, Cospanja, Buena Vista Este, Buena Vista Oeste and Huasi valleys.{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=3}} [[Riegel (glacial)|Rock bar]]s occur in some glacial valleys on the southern and southwestern side of the volcano.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} There are large cirques around Cerro Cuncaicha.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}}{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}}\n\nThe LGM ice cap had an area of at least {{convert|365|km2|abbr=on}}, with glaciers descending to {{convert|3780|-|4540|m|abbr=on}} elevation. Glacier ends were lower on the northern{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=308}} and western sides, probably due to airflow-mediated variations in sublimation.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=312}} The growth of the ice cap has been explained by a decrease of the [[equilibrium line altitude]] of about {{convert|750|m|abbr=on|adj=on}}. Assuming constant precipitation, temperatures may have decreased by {{convert|4.5|-|5.5|C-change}}.{{sfn|Heine|2019|p=264}} The glaciers began to retreat between 12,000 and 11,000{{nbsp;}}years ago.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=118}}\n\n==== Other glacial periods ====\nIce has been present on Coropuna for at least 80,000{{nbsp;}}years.<ref name=\"\u00dabedaPalacio2012\" /> At least two pre-LGM advances spread beyond the area that was covered with ice during the LGM,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=38}} with an expansion occurring in particular in the eastern sector of the volcano.{{sfn|Heine|2019|p=269}} Moraines older than [[marine isotope stage]] 2 are widespread.{{sfn|Heine|2019|p=262}} Those close to the village of Viraco may date back 40,000{{en dash}}45,000{{nbsp;}}years and thus be part of an earlier glaciation,{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=22}} and old dates of 47,000{{en dash}}31,000 and 61,000{{en dash}}37,000{{nbsp;}}years ago in the Huayllaura and Sigue Chico valleys could reflect even larger glacier expansions during marine isotope stage&nbsp;3 or 4.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=113}}\n\nGlaciers retreated after the end of the last glacial maximum 20,000{{en dash}}18,000{{nbsp;}}years ago and then re-expanded.<ref name=\"GSA2007\" /> During the [[Late Glacial|Lateglacial]], a group of moraines formed between the position of the LGM moraines and the position of the recent moraines,{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}} with one lateglacial advance dated to either 13,400{{en dash}}10,000 or 13,900{{en dash}}11,900{{nbsp;}}years ago.{{sfn|Heine|2019|p=263}} Full glacial conditions lasted until 10,000{{en dash}}9,000{{nbsp;}}years ago;<ref name=\"\u00dabedaPalacio2012\" /> minor advances took place about {{nowrap|13,000{{en dash}}9,000 years}} ago, and again some 6,000&nbsp;years ago.{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=5}} The late glacial advances coincide with similar glacier expansions worldwide{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2520}} and some of them may correlate with the [[Younger Dryas]] cold period or the [[Antarctic Cold Reversal]].{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Schaefer|Winckler|2011b|p=42}} During the [[Little Ice Age]], glaciers on Coropuna did not expand much, although some rock glaciers might have formed during that time. The glaciers descended to {{convert|4900|m|abbr=on}} elevation.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=30}}\n\n=== Importance as a source of water ===\nGlaciers in Peru are important sources of water for local communities and for [[hydropower]] generation, especially during the dry season; their shrinkage is thus of concern.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=175}} A 2003 study by Bryan G. Mark and Geoffrey O. Seltzer estimated that about 30{{nbsp;}}per cent of the dry season runoff in the Cordillera Blanca comes from glaciers.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=183}} Meltwater from the glaciers on Coropuna sustains the [[baseflow]] of the rivers{{sfn|Silverio|2018|p=44}} during dry periods;{{sfn|Silverio|2018|p=45}} Coropuna is an important source of water for the valleys of the surrounding areas and for the desert-like [[piedmont]],{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=31}} with an estimated 38,000&nbsp;people depending directly or indirectly on water originating from it.{{sfn|Silverio|Herold|Peduzzi|2010|p=314}} This water supply is threatened by the retreat of the glaciers{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=31}} and would require costly mitigation measures to compensate for its reduction. The Peruvian government is making preparations for Coropuna ceasing to be a contributor to the local water supply by 2025; a 2018 study and re-evaluation of past data concluded that the ice cap should persist until about 2120, and recommends that greater ''[[in situ]]'' monitoring of Coropuna's glaciers is needed to aid future planning and mitigation.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=182}}\n\n== Geology ==\n\n=== Regional setting ===\n[[File:South American plates.png|thumb|The larger [[List of tectonic plates|tectonic plates]] around South America|alt=South America has been a stable continent since the Paleozoic, but the whole Pacific coast is geologically very active]]\n\nOff the coast of Peru, the [[Nazca Plate]] [[Subduction|subducts]] beneath the [[South American Plate]] at a rate of {{convert|9|cm/year|in/year}}.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=59}} This subduction process, along with the subduction of the [[Antarctic Plate]] also underneath the South American Plate, is responsible for the volcanism in the Andes and the uplift of the mountain chain.<ref name=\"Stern2004\" /> In the Cordillera Occidental (Western Cordillera) uplift commenced about 50{{nbsp;}}million years ago in the [[Eocene]], paused until 25&nbsp;million{{nbsp;}}years ago in the [[Oligocene]], and increased substantially after about 10{{nbsp;}}million years ago in the [[Miocene]].{{sfn|Thouret|Gunnell|Jicha|Paquette|2017|p=3}} Andean uplift in the area of Coropuna is ongoing.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} \n\nCoropuna is part of the [[volcanic arc]] of southern Peru{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}} and is considered to be a member of the Barroso volcanic arc.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=9}} There are over six hundred volcanoes in southern Peru{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=213}} and the entire Cordillera Occidental from southern Peru to northern Chile is covered with volcanic rocks, although present-day volcanic activity is scarce.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}} Many of the older volcanoes are deeply eroded by glaciation while younger volcanoes often still resemble cones.{{sfn|Bullard|1962|p=443}}\n\nVolcanic activity in the Andes occurred during three eras. The first was between 195 and 190{{nbsp;}}million years ago in the Early [[Jurassic]], and generated the [[Geology of Peru#Mesozoic (251-66&nbsp;million years ago)|Chocolate Formation]]. The second between 78&nbsp;and 50{{nbsp;}}million years ago (Late [[Cretaceous]] to Early Eocene) generated the Toquepala Formation and the Andean [[batholith]]s.{{sfn|Thouret|Gunnell|Jicha|Paquette|2017|p=3}} Volcanic activity in southern Peru commenced about 13{{nbsp;}}million years ago in the Miocene.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=57}} One volcanic unit{{Spaced en dash}}after being folded and eroded{{Spaced en dash}}was covered by a second lava and [[tuff]] unit which in turn was followed by the emplacement of large volcanoes.{{sfn|Bullard|1962|p=443}} Ignimbrites and stratovolcano activity, at times subdivided into a \"rhyolitic\" and an \"andesitic\" formation, alternated.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}}\n\n=== Basement ===\nCoropuna is constructed atop of 14{{nbsp;}}million year old ignimbrites{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=214}} and lava flows of [[Neogene]] age.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=16}} Individual ignimbrites crop out mainly in valleys; on the highlands they are buried beneath more recent volcanic products.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=246}} The volcanic basement includes the Miocene to [[Plio-Pleistocene]] [[Tacaza Formation|Tacaza]], [[Huaylillas Formation|Huaylillas]], [[Sencca Formation|Sencca]] and [[Barroso Formation, Peru|Barroso Formations]]; the latter formation includes Coropuna itself. Below these formations lie the sedimentary Murco and Socosani formations and the Yura Group, which are [[sediment]]s of Jurassic-Cretaceous age with intruded [[pluton]]s of the same age; finally there is a Basal Complex of [[Precambrian]] age.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=37}}\n\n=== Faults and lineaments ===\nThe basement is cut by faults and [[lineament]]s such as the [[Pampacolca Fault]] on the southern side of the volcano and the [[Pumaranra lineament|Pumaranra]] and [[Cerro Casulla lineament]]s,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=57}} which trend southeast{{en dash}}northwest and northeast{{en dash}}southwest, respectively. One east\u2013west lineament may have influenced the recent volcanism;{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=58}} the alignment of Coropuna with [[Sara Sara]], [[Solimana (volcano)|Solimana]] and [[El Misti]] may indicate a tectonic control on the volcano in general.{{sfn|Caldas Vidal|1993|p=35}} On the southern flank, Holocene [[normal fault]]s have offset lava flows and streams.{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}}\n\n=== Composition ===\nThe rocks released by Coropuna are dark brown to black and [[porphyritic]].{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=248}} They consist of [[andesite]],{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} [[dacite]],{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=104}} [[rhyodacite]],{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=251}} [[rhyolite]],{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=215}} trachy-[[basaltic andesite]], [[trachyandesite]] and [[trachydacite]].{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} The more recent lava flows have been dacitic{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=49}} or trachydacitic.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} [[Phenocryst]] phases include [[amphibole]], [[biotite]], [[plagioclase]], [[pyroxene]] and [[titanomagnetite]].{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=214}} Aside from the volcanic rocks, deposits of [[salt]]s, [[sulfur]] and [[travertine]] produced by [[hot spring]]s are found on the southern flank.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=26}}\n\nThe volcanic rocks define a [[calc-alkaline]]{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=215}} [[potassium]]-rich suite which resembles that of{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} Chilean{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=250}} and Peruvian volcanoes such as Tutupaca.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} They contain large amounts of [[rubidium]], [[strontium]] and [[barium]].{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} Complicated processes{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=225}} of crystallisation and interaction with Earth's [[Crust (geology)|crust]] appear to have produced the magma.{{sfn|Venturelli|Fragipane|Weibel|Antiga|1978|p=226}}\n\n== Eruption history ==\nThe beginning of Coropuna's growth has variously been placed over 5{{nbsp;}}million years ago,{{sfn|Tosdal|Farrar|Clark|1981|p=168}} during the [[Pliocene]]{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=43}} or late Miocene, but most of its structure developed during the Quaternary.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} Volcanic activity has been subdivided into two stages: [[explosive eruption]]s during the now mostly eroded Coropuna I stage produced volcanic ash, pyroclastic flows and [[pumice]] but also lava flows, while Coropuna II above {{convert|6000|m}} elevation erupted lava flows from the now snow-covered vents.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}}{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=44}} The existence of a Coropuna III sequence has been proposed.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=49}} The most recent eruption products have been described as the \"Andahua Group\".{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=87}} About 5.3{{nbsp;}}million years ago, the Sunjillpa volcano was active southwest from Coropuna,<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> while Pumaranra is of Pliocene to Quaternary age.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}}\n\nA major ignimbrite eruption took place about 2{{nbsp;}}million years ago at Coropuna; its deposits have been identified west of the volcano{{sfn|Tosdal|Farrar|Clark|1981|p=169}}{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=104}} and it led to the destruction of the edifice, which later re-formed on the remains of the old volcano.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}} The occurrence of explosive eruptions during a mostly effusive activity has been found at Chachani and Sara Sara as well.{{sfn|Weibel|Frangipane-Gysel|Hunziker|1978|p=245}}\n\nIn addition, the Upper Sencca Ignimbrite, the Lower Sencca Ignimbrite<ref name=\"\u00c7ubuk\u00e7u2012\" /> and the Chuquibamba (Huaylillas{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=11}}) Ignimbrite{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=17}} may have originated here as well;{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=21}} the latter was produced by a [[Volcanic Explosivity Index|volcanic explosivity index]] 7&nbsp;class \"super-eruption\"{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=19}} between 14.3 and 13.2{{nbsp;}}million years ago in the [[Middle Miocene]].{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=20}} The Upper Sencca Ignimbrites are a {{nowrap|2.09\u20131.76 million}} years old{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=17}} composite ignimbrite{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=15}} which form a {{convert|10|-|30|m|abbr=on}} thick apron around Coropuna and other regional volcanoes; Coropuna appears to have formed on top of one of the Upper Sencca Ignimbrite vents.{{sfn|Cubukcu|Paquette|Jicha|Thouret|2016|p=17}}\n\nAfter a hiatus,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=55}} volcanic activity continued into the [[Pleistocene]].{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=104}} Several lava flows on the western and central sides of Coropuna have been dated, yielding ages ranging from {{nowrap|410,000 \u00b1 9,000}} to {{nowrap|62,600 \u00b1 4,300 years}} ago.<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> During the last glacial maximum, Coropuna was inactive{{sfn|Thouret|Juvigne|Mari\u00f1o|Moscol|2002|p=3}} and moraines buried its lava flows.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=3}} However, one{{sfn|Thouret|Juvigne|Mari\u00f1o|Moscol|2002|p=3}} or two tephra layers on a moraine close to the village of Viraco on the southern side have been dated to be about 41,000 and 30,000{{Spaced en dash}}31,000{{nbsp;}}years old. These ages correspond to [[radiocarbon]] ages of {{nowrap|37,370 \u00b1 1,160}} and {{nowrap|27,200 \u00b1 300 years}}. These tephras may have originated in [[fissure eruption]]s associated with the three recent lava flows.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=22}} In postglacial times [[lava bomb]]s, [[lapilli]] and volcanic ash were deposited on previously glaciated terrain.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}} Pumice deposits may have formed during the Holocene.{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|p=9}}\n\n=== Holocene ===\nNo eruptions of Coropuna during historical<ref name=\"DeggChester2005\" /> or modern times are known,{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=175}} and the volcano was considered to be long-extinct.{{sfn|Bullard|1962|p=444}} However, young-looking{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} [[Lava#\u02bbA\u02bb\u0101|\u02bba\u02bb\u0101 lava]]{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=15}} or [[Lava#Block lava flows|block lava]]{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=3}} flows erupted during the Holocene and in part overlie late-glacial moraines.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=49}}{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}}{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=15}} Their vents are now hidden beneath glacier ice{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=63}} and the flows have been affected by later glacial advances.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=8-9}} These lava flows are found on the west{{en dash}}northwest, south{{en dash}}southeast and northeast side of the mountain:{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}}\n\n* A northwesterly lava flow \u2013 Coropuna's longest{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=49}} at {{convert|8.5|km|abbr=on}} \u2013 occupies the Cerro Sepulturayoc valley.{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=3}} It has been dated to about 6,000{{nbsp;}}years ago,{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=3}} but research published in 2019 has suggested it may have erupted somewhat earlier, during the [[Late Glacial]] period.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=12}}\n* A southeasterly flow lies in the Cospanja valley and is either {{nowrap|1,100 \u00b1 100}}{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=4}} or {{nowrap|700 \u00b1 200 years}} old,<ref name=\"Mapa2017\" /> the latter age being derived from [[Cosmogenic dating|cosmogenic isotope dating]].{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}} It was probably formed during a single eruption and is {{convert|4|km|spell=in|}} long.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=6}}\n* A dark, young-looking lava<ref name=\"GVPP\" /> flow runs northeasterly{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=105}} in the Que\u00f1ua Ranra valley{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=108}} and is {{convert|5|km|spell=in}} long.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=8}} The eruption took place about {{nowrap|2,100 \u00b1 200 years}} ago{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=109}} according to cosmogenic isotope dating.{{sfn|Garc\u00eda Z\u00fa\u00f1iga|Mari\u00f1o Salazar|Valdivia Humerez|2018|p=117}} Its deposition was preceded by the eruption of lava bombs that cover the valley and by the production of a lahar that advanced {{convert|14|km|abbr=on}} from its source. Whether a secondary lava flow in the same valley occurred at the same time or later is not clear, as that flow has not yet been dated.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=109}}\n\nThe ages of the flows indicate an eastward shift in activity.<ref name=\"\u00dabedaPalacio2012\" /> The southeasterly and northeasterly flows may have been erupted within 500&nbsp;years from the same fissure,{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=12}} while the eruption of the northwesterly flow might be a consequence of the retreat of the ice cap.{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|pp=2, 13}} These lava flows are the most recent manifestation of volcanic activity{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} and they imply that Coropuna is still active;{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=175}} it is thus considered to be a [[dormant volcano]], rather than an extinct one.{{sfn|Thouret|Juvigne|Mari\u00f1o|Moscol|2002|p=2}} There is no evidence of Holocene tephras in [[peat bog]] [[drill core]]s{{sfn|Thouret|Juvigne|Mari\u00f1o|Moscol|2002|p=3}} and volcanism at Coropuna since the last ice age has been primarily [[effusive eruption|effusive]].{{sfn|Bromley|Thouret|Schimmelpfennig|Mari\u00f1o|2019|p=12}}\n\n=== Present day status ===\n[[File:Steam vents on Coropuna Este (30293366136).jpg|thumb|Steam rising on Coropuna Este]]\nThe volcano is still hydrothermally active.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=3}} Six hot springs are found on Coropuna, mostly on the southeastern foot,{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|p=12}} such as at Acopallpa, Antaura, Viques, Ccollpa, and Aguas Calientes and, on its northern flank, at Huaman\u00ed Loma. Their water temperatures range between {{convert|18|and|51|C}}.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=25}} With the exception of the last two, which are situated in glacial terrain, these hot springs rise within valleys via rock fractures.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=26}} Geochemical analyses of the water from these springs published in 2015 show no major variations in composition, implying a stable volcanic system.{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|p=18}} Whether [[solfataric]] or [[fumarolic]] activity occurs at Coropuna is unclear,<ref name=\"GVP\" />{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=25}} and the thick glaciation indicates that the summit craters have no thermal activity.{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}}\n\nSome of the hot springs on Coropuna are used for bathing.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=26}} The volcano had been considered a potential site for [[geothermal power]] production,<ref name=\"DiazHuaina1988\" /> but research published in 1998 concluded that the available energy of the Coropuna area was insufficient.{{sfn|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|Steinm\u00fcller|1998|p=42}}\n\nThe first volcano activity report published in 2018 noted ongoing [[seismic]] activity involving [[Volcano tectonic earthquake|volcano-tectonic earthquakes]].<ref name=\"IGdP2018\" /> [[Seismic swarm]]s were observed at Coropuna after the [[2001 southern Peru earthquake]]{{sfn|Lohman|Pritchard|Holtkamp|2011|p=139}} and were possibly triggered by that earthquake.{{sfn|Lohman|Pritchard|Holtkamp|2011|p=144}} Observations of deformation of the volcanic edifice have shown that [[gravitational instability]] and [[soil]] water absorption result in movements of part of the volcano but, as a whole, Coropuna shows no evidence of volcanic deformation.{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|pp=27\u201328}}\n\n=== Hazards and monitoring ===\nThe Peruvian [[INGEMMET|Instituto Geol\u00f3gico Minero y Metal\u00fargico]] (INGEMMET) monitors Coropuna for activity. It uses data such as the composition of hot spring waters{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|p=11}} and the shape of the volcano as estimated by [[Satellite imagery|satellite images]],{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|p=25}} [[GPS]] and [[geodesy]],{{sfn|INGEMMET|2015|p=27}} as well as information from five seismic stations.<ref name=\"MdA2019\" /> A volcanic hazard map has been published{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=75}} and there are regular status reports published by the Peruvian government.<ref name=\"MdA2019b\" /> About 90,000 people live in risk areas,<ref name=\"MdA2019\" /> and the sites most in danger are towns in the steep southern valleys.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}}\n\nTogether with [[El Misti]], Sabancaya and Ubinas, Coropuna is considered to be one of Peru's most dangerous volcanoes.{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|p=28}} The presence of an ice cap, and therefore the risk of [[incandescent]] volcanic rocks melting that ice, creates a hazard of lahars, or mudflows, such as those that in 1985 killed over 23,000 people at [[Nevado del Ruiz]] volcano in [[Colombia]].{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=61}}{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=175}} The risk to life is further increased by Coropuna's steep slopes and by the concentration of people in nearby valleys.{{sfn|\u00dabeda|Palacios|V\u00e1zquez-Selem|2012|p=1}} The terrain around the volcano has one of the greatest topographic reliefs in the world and a number of towns lie on the floor of the Majes valley, right down to the Pacific Ocean where the district capital [[Caman\u00e1]]{{sfn|de Silva|Francis|1990|p=292}} with 20,000 inhabitants is situated.<ref name=\"DeggChester2005\" /> Although there is no evidence of past mudflows of such size, lahars could reach as far as the coast,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=69}} affecting a number of towns{{sfn|Vela|C\u00e1ceres|Calder\u00f3n|Chijcheapaza|2016|loc=Anexo No.4}} and infrastructure such as roads, [[antenna (radio)|antenna]]s and small [[hydropower]] plants.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=61}} According to the 2007 census, 110,481 people lived in the provinces that span Coropuna and lie downstream of it.{{sfn|Marinque|Marino|Enderlin|Edwards|2018|p=175}}\n\nLava flows are also a potential danger at Coropuna.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} Other hazards with lesser probabilities are [[Lateral eruption|directed volcanic blast]]s, lava dome collapses,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} fast-moving massive pyroclastic flows{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=73}} and flows of pumice and volcanic ash,{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=88}} lava bombs{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=70}} and [[shock wave]]s from volcanic explosions.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=76}}\n\n== Climate ==\n\n=== Precipitation ===\nCoropuna lies between the semi-humid Altiplano and the [[arid]] western slope of the Andes.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=236}} Its climate is [[semi-arid]], with precipitation at {{convert|6080|m|abbr=on}} elevation reaching {{convert|390|mm/year|in/year}}.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} Other reported precipitation values range between {{convert|700|mm/year|in/year|abbr=on}}{{sfn|Weide|Fritz|Brinson|Thompson|2017|p=2}} and {{convert|1000|mm/year|in/year|abbr=on}}.{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2515}} Lower down the mountain, at altitudes between at {{convert|3000|and|4000|m|abbr=on}}, annual precipitation levels increase to between {{convert|226|and|560|mm/year|in/year|abbr=on}} (semi-humid). Even further down, at altitudes around {{convert|2000|-|3000|m|abbr=on}}, they decrease again to {{convert|98|-|227|mm/year|in/year|abbr=on}} (desert).{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=7}} Cold water brought from [[Antarctica]] along the Pacific Ocean by the [[Humboldt Current]],{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=99}} the presence of a stable [[anticyclone]] {{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=25}} and of a [[temperature inversion]] over the Pacific, and the Andean [[rainshadow]] are all responsible for this dryness.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} \n\nMost precipitation falls as [[hail]] or snow.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=7}} This happens mostly during the summer{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=306}} [[wet season]], between December and March,{{sfn|Bromley|Schaefer|Winckler|Hall|2009|p=2515}} when the [[ITCZ]] moves south{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=98}} and a summer [[monsoon]] is active over South America.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=99}} Most precipitation is brought by easterly winds coming from the [[Amazon basin|Amazon]] and the [[Atlantic Ocean]], whereas the westerly winds that dominate during the dry season do not carry much moisture.{{sfn|Campos|2015|p=2}} Thus, humidity generally decreases in a westward direction.{{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=25}}\n\nThe amount of precipitation is modulated by the [[El Ni\u00f1o Southern Oscillation]]. During phases of El Ni\u00f1o the weather is drier, snow cover smaller and glacier retreat increases.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=31}}<ref name=\"Kochtitzky2016\" /> Over longer timespans, precipitation in the region increases whenever [[iceberg]] discharge and cooling occur in the [[North Atlantic]]. This was the case during the [[Heinrich event]]s and the Younger Dryas when lakes formed on the Bolivian [[Altiplano]]: The [[Sajsi]] formed about 25,000\u201319,000{{nbsp;}}years ago, [[Lake Tauca|Tauca]] about 18,000\u201314,000 and Coipasa 13,000\u201311,000{{nbsp;}}years ago.{{sfn|Palenque|Ni\u00f1o de Guzm\u00e1n|Choque|\u00c1lvarez|2018|p=99}} Cold periods in the [[Southern Hemisphere]] such as the Antarctic Cold Reversal between 14,500 and 12,900{{nbsp;}}years ago may have pushed the [[polar front]] north and increased precipitation as well.{{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=25}} That increased precipitation may have delayed the retreat of Coropuna's glaciers after the end of the last glacial maximum.{{sfn|\u00dabeda Palenque|2013|p=27}} Coropuna experienced moist conditions during the early Holocene, whereas the late Holocene beginning 5,200{{nbsp;}}years ago was drier there,{{sfn|Kuentz|Ledru|Thouret|2011b|p=1224}} with a pronounced dry period lasting from 5,200 to 3,000{{nbsp;}}years ago.<ref name=\"Escobar-Torrez2018\" />\n\n=== Temperature ===\nTemperatures decrease with altitude gain, and at lower elevations around {{convert|2000|-|3000|m|abbr=on}} they average {{convert|12|-|17|C|abbr=on}}. Between {{convert|3000|and|4000|m|abbr=on}} they average  {{convert|7.8|C|abbr=on}} and at {{convert|4000|-|5200|m|abbr=on}} elevation they average {{convert|0|-|6|C|abbr=on}}. At altitudes above {{convert|5200|m|abbr=on}} they remain below freezing.{{sfn|Valenzuela Ortiz|N\u00fa\u00f1ez Ju\u00e1rez|2001|p=7}} Temperatures fluctuate more over daily timescales than over seasonal ones when measured close to the glaciers.{{sfn|Silverio|Jaquet|2012|p=5878}} Southerly cold waves can sometimes reach Coropuna, leaving traces in ice cores in the form of southern [[pollen]].{{sfn|Schotterer|Delachaux|Ledru|Angelis|2009|pp=32\u201333}} During the Little Ice Age, at {{convert|5000|-|5200|m|abbr=on}} elevation temperatures decreased to {{convert|-5|to|-7|C|abbr=on}}.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=30}} Warm fluctuations between about 2,200 and 900{{nbsp;}}years ago, plus a cold fluctuation between around 970 to 1010 [[AD]], are also recorded.{{sfn|Engel|Skrzypek|Chuman|\u0160efrna|2014|p=73}}\n\n== Vegetation, fauna and agriculture ==\n[[File:Yareta Peru.jpg|thumb|Yareta on Coropuna|alt=Cushion-shaped plants grow in a wide rock-strewn valley]]\nMost of the region is covered by [[puna grassland]], with the exception of isolated ''[[Polylepis]]'' woods to the southwest of the volcano, plus other different vegetation types to the west and southeast.{{sfn|Kuentz|Mera|Ledru|Thouret|2007|p=1765}} Peat bogs are present on the southern and southwestern sides of Coropuna, and some of these have been drilled to obtain [[sediment core]]s.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}}{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=17}} Elsewhere, agriculture is widespread around Coropuna.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} Insects such as beetles and [[hymenoptera]]ns, birds such as the [[Andean condor]],{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=67}} fish and mammals such as the [[alpaca]], [[llama]]{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=242}} and [[vicu\u00f1a]] occur in the region.{{sfn|Cuber|Panajew|Ga\u0142a\u015b|2015|p=67}} Several new species of [[butterfly]] have been discovered there.<ref name=\"Larico2018\" />\n\nThe mountain has several distinct vegetation belts:\n* Between {{convert|800|and|2500|m|abbr=on}} lies [[steppe]] vegetation with ''[[Ambrosia]]'' [[shrub]]s and [[cacti]]. [[Irrigation]] permits the cultivation of garlic, olive, onion, potato, rice, sugar cane and wheat. [[Pasture]]s are also present.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|pp=241\u2013242}}\n* The steppe vegetation is also present between {{convert|2500|and|3500|m|abbr=on}} in the \"pre-Puna\", but it is denser here{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=242}} and includes shrubs of the family [[Asteraceae]], such as ''Ambrosia'', ''[[Diplostephium]]'' and ''[[Senecio]]''.{{sfn|Kuentz|Ledru|Thouret|2011b|p=1216}} Crops grown here include [[alfalfa]], but there is also some [[dairy farming]] and  the planting of [[eucalyptus]] and [[pine tree]]s  as a wood supply for the local population.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=242}}\n* Between {{convert|3000|and|4000|m|abbr=on}} lies a so-called \"supra-tropical facies\" on soils overlying lava flows. It includes shrubs and [[Thorns, spines, and prickles|thorny]] vegetation in very wet and very dry areas, respectively. Agriculture is practised here, including the growing of [[kiwicha]], maize, [[quinoa]] and vegetables on [[anthropogenic soils]]{{sfn|Kuentz|Mera|Ledru|Thouret|2007|pp=1767\u20131768}} and [[terrace (agriculture)|terrace]]d fields.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=242}} Dominant natural plants between {{convert|3500|and|4000|m|abbr=on}} include herbaceous plants of the families [[Fabaceae]] and [[Solanaceae]], as well as shrubs of the Asteraceae.{{sfn|Kuentz|Ledru|Thouret|2011b|p=1216}}\n* Between {{convert|4000|and|4800|m|abbr=on}} vegetation is found in [[marsh]]es and peat bogs where sufficient water is available, in the form of relic ''Polylepis'' woodlands as well as herbaceous puna vegetation{{sfn|Kuentz|Mera|Ledru|Thouret|2007|pp=1768\u20131769}} which is particularly prolific during the wet season. These areas are used for pasture of [[alpaca]]s and [[llama]]s, and for [[fishing]] in wetlands and ''Polylepis'' woods; hamlets are found close to wetlands and forests.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=242}} Plant genera found here include ''[[Baccharis]]'', ''[[Calamagrostis]]'', ''[[Chuquiraga]]'', ''[[Festuca]]'', ''[[Parastrephia]]'', ''Senecio'' and ''[[Stipa]]''.{{sfn|Kuentz|Ledru|Thouret|2011b|p=1216}}\n* Above {{convert|4800|m|abbr=on}} lies the so-called \"Puna brava\", with herbs and deep-rooted plants that have all adapted to withstand permafrost conditions.{{sfn|Kuentz|Mera|Ledru|Thouret|2007|p=1769}} The [[cushion plant]], [[yareta]], which is used as a fuel source, is the dominant plant in this belt.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=243}} Other plants from the [[Apiaceae]] and Asteraceae also occur.{{sfn|Weide|Fritz|Brinson|Thompson|2017|p=3}} Vegetation, including [[Jarava ichu|ichu grass]] and yareta, exist up to about {{convert|5|km|abbr=on|spell=in}} elevation; higher elevations are unvegetated.{{sfn|Bromley|Hall|Rademaker|Todd|2011|p=307}}\n\n== Archaeology and religious importance ==\nNumerous archaeological sites lie on Coropuna, especially at the southern and northern bases of the volcano and on its western slope.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} Among these are funerary towers known as ''[[chullpa]]s''.<ref name=\"Duchesne2005\" /> Some of these western sites are on the ice cap.{{sfn|Forget|Thouret|Kuentz|Fontugne|2008|p=18}} Proposals have been made to make the area of Coropuna including these archaeological sites into a [[protected area]].<ref name=\"Goicochea2009\" />\n\nThe coastal regions of Peru were first occupied 11,000 and 9,000{{nbsp;}}years [[Before Christ|BC]].{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=243}} Evidence of the presence of [[hunter-gatherer]]s near Coropuna first appear in the archaeological record in the caves of Cavalca and Pintasayoc, respectively north and south of the volcano. In the latter cave, [[rock painting]]s interpreted as being 7,000{{Spaced en dash}}3,000{{nbsp;}}years BC have been found.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=246}} The first human activity at Coropuna in the Cuncaicha [[cave]] north of the volcano began shortly after the final retreat of glaciers from the mountain.{{sfn|Sandweiss|\u00c1lvarez|Reid|Leach|2014|p=469}} The region around the volcano was settled over the last 4,000{{nbsp;}}years.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=236}}\n\n=== Inca times ===\nA larger number of archaeological sites go back to the 2nd Intermediate Period{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|pp=246\u2013248}} and during the Inca era. The Inca expanded preexisting irrigation and terrace systems which are in part still existing today.{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=248}} These include the highest irrigation system in the world<ref name=\"Ch\u00e1vez2001\" /> which was possibly constructed on Coropuna to allow the cultivation of bitter potatoes.<ref name=\"Orellana2017\" /> Inca sites are often found at higher elevations than the sites left by preceding civilisations; the highest one is located at {{convert|5700|m|abbr=on}} elevation{{sfn|Kuentz|Thouret|Ledru|Forget|2011|p=249}} and there is evidence of Inca presence to {{convert|6200|m|abbr=on}} elevation.<ref name=\"Ch\u00e1vez2001\" /> In addition, an important branch of the [[Inca road system]] passes by the western foot of Coropuna.<ref name=\"Ch\u00e1vez2001\" /> The region was densely populated; the close location of the mountains and favourable climatic conditions facilitated its settlement.{{sfn|Baca|Molak|Sobczyk|W\u0119gle\u0144ski|2014|p=3}}\n\nAs noted by [[Spaniards|Spanish]] chroniclers<ref name=\"Woloszyn2010\" /> such as [[Pedro de Cieza de Le\u00f3n]],{{sfn|Urton|Hagen|2015|p=105}} Coropuna played an important role in Inca religion and an important temple was situated there,{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|p=131}} possibly at [[Mawk'allaqta, Castilla|Maucallacta]].{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|p=145}} Pedro de Cieza de Le\u00f3n considered Coropuna to be the fifth most important holy site of the Inca empire.{{sfn|Urton|Hagen|2015|p=105}} One archaeological site on the volcano may have been a stopover for religious ceremonies to its summit.{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|p=138}} ''[[Capacocha]]'', a form of [[human sacrifice]], were offered to the mountain;<ref name=\"Woloszyn2010\" /> reportedly, in 1965, a [[mummy]] was found there.<ref name=\"Schobinger1999\" />\n\n==== Maucallacta and Acchaymarca ====\nAmong the archaeological sites at Coropuna is the important Inca site of Maucallacta, on the southwestern flank of the mountain.{{sfn|Sobczyk|2012|p=215}} Some of the structures there were built to evoke the appearance of the mountain.{{sfn|Sobczyk|2012|p=219}} A royal residence, an [[oracle]] and a political unit were associated with Maucallacta,{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|pp=131\u2013132}} and the oracle of Coropuna would have answered the rulers' queries all year round.{{sfn|Urton|Hagen|2015|p=211}} The Maucallacta site was probably the most important one at Coropuna; the western summit today known as \"La Ni\u00f1a\" was apparently also significant.{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|p=154}}\n\nAnother important site associated with Coropuna is Acchaymarca, to the west of the mountain,{{sfn|Baca|Molak|Sobczyk|W\u0119gle\u0144ski|2014|p=2}} where about 280 Inca stone structures have been found.{{sfn|Baca|Molak|Sobczyk|W\u0119gle\u0144ski|2014|p=3}} It is likely that many pilgrims came there for ceremonies honouring the ''[[Apu (god)|apus]]'' of Coropuna and Solimana.{{sfn|Baca|Molak|Sobczyk|W\u0119gle\u0144ski|2014|p=8}}\n\n== Mythology, religion and legends ==\nIn the Inca Empire, Coropuna was a [[Sacred mountains|sacred mountain]],{{sfn|Sobczyk|2012|p=215}} especially for the people of [[Cotahuasi]].<ref name=\"MINCETUR2019\" /> It was regarded as the most important mountain deity (''[[apu (god)|apu]]'') of the southern region,<ref name=\"Ch\u00e1vez2001\" /> and the second-most important in the [[cosmology]] of the Andes.<ref name=\"Trawick2003\" /> The mountain was considered to be an abode of the dead{{sfn|Fourtan\u00e9|2001|p=16}} \u2013 a large village where holy people received the souls of the departed, who lived there in the afterlife.<ref name=\"Trawick2003\" />{{sfn|Fourtan\u00e9|2001|p=17}} In different mythologies Coropuna is instead the starting point for the deceased on a journey to [[Surimana]].{{sfn|Fourtan\u00e9|2001|p=17}} Sometimes Coropuna is seen as a male entity while Solimana volcano is seen as a female one.<ref name=\"Golte2004\" /> Local people continue to observe these ancient mortuary rites today.<ref name=\"Trawick2003\" /> \n\nAn enduring Franciscan influence from a colonial-era [[Cusco]] friary, the \"pious among today's Peruvian peasantry\" revere a \"Flying\" [[St Francis of Assisi]], who is believed to await the souls of the dead on top of Coropuna.<ref name=\"Lara2013\" /> Other poorly recorded legends are associated with Coropuna.{{sfn|Zi\u00f3\u0142kowski|2008|p=143}} One story narrates how a brother tried to deceive Coropuna and other mountains, and was turned into a deer.<ref name=\"Campos2018\" /> Another legend tells of a conflict between Coropuna and other local mountains against an interloping Inca.<ref name=\"Menaker2019\" /> A third story states that a troupe was transporting precious metals for Coropuna and Solimana when the animal leading it was shot by a hunter; the mountains then castrated the hunter.<ref name=\"Gose1986\" />\n\n== Climbing ==\nThe archaeological findings made on Coropuna indicate that the Inca may have reached the summit.<ref name=\"Echevarria1980\" /> [[Annie Peck]] and [[Hiram Bingham III]] each reached a summit of Coropuna in 1911; Annie Peck raised a banner saying \"Votes for Women\" on the summit she had ascended, which was slightly lower than the one reached by Bingham.<ref name=\"Smith2004\" /> This banner action was part of the [[women's suffrage]] campaigns that were taking place at that time, and meant to illustrate that women were just as capable as men of physical deeds.<ref name=\"Schultz2010\" /> Since then, other summits of the mountain have been ascended as well.<ref name=\"Hernandez2013\" />\n\nThe rugged area offers [[mountaineering]] opportunities.<ref name=\"MINCETUR2019\" /> Coropuna is normally ascended from Laguna Pallarcocha, from where a route along the western rib and glacier slopes leads up to a foresummit and then to the main summit. Along this way, a high camp can be set up at {{convert|5600|-|5800|m}} elevation. An ascent of Coropuna would normally be a three-day trip, and on the [[Grade (climbing)#International French adjectival system (IFAS)|French adjectival climbing scale]] the route is graded as Facile (F). Pallarcocha itself can be reached from a road that begins in the town of Chuquibamba.<ref name=\"Biggar2015\" />\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Lara2013\">{{cite journal|last1=Lara|first1=Jaime|title=Francis Alive and Aloft: Franciscan Apocalypticism in the Colonial Andes|journal=The Americas|date=2013|volume=70|issue=2|pages=162\u2013163|doi=10.1353/tam.2013.0096|language=en|issn=0003-1615}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"AAC1990\">{{cite book |author1=American Alpine Club |title=The American alpine journal |date=1990 |publisher=The Mountaineers Books |isbn=978-1-933056-37-1 |page=328 |language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Bingham2010\">{{cite book |last1=Bingham |first1=Hiram |title=Lost City of the Incas |date=2010 |publisher=Orion |isbn=978-0-297-86533-9 |language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Biggar2015\">{{cite book|last1=Biggar|first1=John|title=Cordiellera Occidental: The Andes, a Guide For Climbers|date=2015|publisher=Andes|isbn=9780993438752|url=https://books.google.com/?id=9qDtCgAAQBAJ&q=coropuna#v=snippet&q=coropuna&f=false|accessdate=12 November 2019|language=en}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MdA2019b\">{{cite web|title=Archivo de reportes y alertas de actividad del Volc\u00e1n Coropuna|trans-title=Archive of reports and alerts of volcanic activity of Coropuna|url=https://www.igp.gob.pe/servicios/centro-vulcanologico-nacional/archivo-de-reportes-y-alertas-de-actividad/coropuna|website=Centro Vulcanol\u00f3gico Nacional|publisher=Ministerio del Ambiente|accessdate=12 October 2019|language=es}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MdA2019\">{{cite web|title=Volcanes monitoreados|trans-title=Monitored volcanoes|url=https://www.igp.gob.pe/servicios/centro-vulcanologico-nacional/volcanes-monitoreados/coropuna|website=Centro Vulcanol\u00f3gico Nacional|publisher=Ministerio del Ambiente|accessdate=12 October 2019|language=es}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MINCETUR2019\">{{cite web|title=Nevado Coropuna|url=http://ficha.sigmincetur.mincetur.gob.pe/index.aspx?cod_Ficha=2845|website=Recursos Tur\u00edsticos|publisher=Ministerio de Comercio Exterior y Turismo|accessdate=12 October 2019|language=es}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"NOAA2018\">{{cite web|title=Peru's Shrinking Tropical Ice Caps|url=https://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/31014|website=Hyperwall|publisher=NOAA|accessdate=5 September 2019|date=14 December 2018}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Gose1986\">{{cite journal|last1=Gose|first1=Peter|title=Sacrifice and the Commodity Form in the Andes|journal=Man|date=1986|volume=21|issue=2|page=303|doi=10.2307/2803161|issn=0025-1496|jstor=2803161}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Golte2004\">{{cite journal|last1=Golte|first1=J\u00fcrgen|last2=S\u00e1nchez|first2=Rodolfo|title=Sawasiray - Pitusiray, la antiguedad del concepto y santuario en los Andes|journal=Investigaciones Sociales|date=2004|volume=8|i