{"title_page": "Abbotsholme School", "text_new": "{{for|the defunct Australian school|Abbotsholme College}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Abbotsholme School\n| image         = \n| image_size          = \n| coordinates   = {{coord|52.944374|-1.82542|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| motto         = Glad Day Love and Duty\n| established   = 1889\n| closed        = \n| type          = [[Independent school (UK)|Independent]] day and boarding school\n| religious_affiliation      = Christian\n| president     = \n| head_label    = Headmaster\n| head          = Simon Ruscoe-Price\n| r_head_label  = \n| r_head        = \n| chair_label   = \n| chair         = \n| founder       = Cecil Reddie\n| specialist    = \n| address        = \n| city          = [[Rocester]]\n| county        = [[Derbyshire]]\n| country       = England\n| postcode      = ST14 5BS\n| local_authority           =\n| ofsted        = \n| dfeno         = 830/6005\n| urn           = 113003 \n| staff         = \n| enrolment    = 290~\n| gender        = Coeducational\n| lower_age     = 2\n| upper_age     = 18\n| houses        = \n| colours       = Green, Gold \n{{colour box|#0B6121}}{{colour box|#DBA901}}\n| publication   = \n| free_label_1  = Former pupils\n| free_1        = Old Abbotsholmians\n| free_label_2  = \n| free_2        = \n| free_label_3  = \n| free_3        = \n| website       = http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/\n}}\n\n'''Abbotsholme School''' is a co-educational [[Independent school (UK)|independent]] [[boarding school|boarding]] and [[day school]]. The school is situated on a 140-acre campus on the banks of the [[River Dove, Central England|River Dove]] in [[Derbyshire]], England near the county border and the village of [[Rocester]] in [[Staffordshire]]. It is a member of the [[Society of Headmasters & Headmistresses of Independent Schools|SHHIS]] (Society of Headmasters & Headmistresses of Independent Schools) and is a [[Round Square (educational organisation)|Round Square]] school.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Adityajit Singh Kang (second from left in red Scholar Blazer & blue Scarf) with Classmates at Abbotsholme School, Rocester, Uttoxeter, Staffordshire, England, UK.jpg|thumb|Exchange student and classmates at Abbotsholme School in 2012]]\nAbbotsholme was founded by Scottish academic and educationist [[Cecil Reddie]]<ref>{{cite web\n |url          = http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/494634/Cecil-Reddie\n |title        = Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica\n |accessdate   = 10 October 2013\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20150610225138/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/494634/Cecil-Reddie\n |archive-date = 2015-06-10\n |url-status     = live\n}}</ref> as an experiment for his progressive educational philosophies and theories.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abbotsholme.com/pdfs/inspection_report.pdf |title=Inspection Report |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=INDEPENDENT SCHOOLS INSPECTORATE |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090320060819/http://www.abbotsholme.com/pdfs/inspection_report.pdf |archive-date=2009-03-20 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Burns|first=R.W.|title=The Life and Times of Alan Dower Blumlein|url=https://books.google.com/?id=B2z2ONO7nBQC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|publisher=[[Institute of Engineering and Technology|IET]]|year=2000|pages=19|isbn=9780852967737}}</ref> The school, then known \"The New School\", opened to boys aged 10 to 19 in 1889. From the very beginning, the school departed from the structure of the traditional [[Public school (UK)|public school]] in favour of a less rigid environment and more liberal education. [[Top hat]]s and \"[[Eton College|Eton]] collars\" were discarded in favour of a more comfortable and practical uniform, and English, French and German were taught in place of [[Classics]] (Latin and Greek). The fine arts were introduced as core subjects, considered unusual at that time, since music and art were mostly taught at cathedral schools or specialist art institutes. Practical skills such as animal husbandry and carpentry were integrated into the curriculum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/Abbotsholmes-History|title=Our History|access-date=2012-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826045726/http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/Abbotsholmes-History|archive-date=2012-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> It has been coeducational since 1969; girls now make up over one third of overall pupil numbers. The school was bought by Chinese company, Achieve Education, in 2017.\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n{{see also|Category:People educated at Abbotsholme School}}\n* [[Roger Altounyan]] \u2013 physician and pharmacologist who pioneered the use of [[sodium cromoglycate]] as a preventative for asthma<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.wellcomelibrary.org/2012/06/if-not-duffers-wont-drown/|title='If not duffers won't drown'|access-date=2016-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121171323/http://blog.wellcomelibrary.org/2012/06/if-not-duffers-wont-drown/|archive-date=2016-11-21|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.wellcome.ac.uk/DServe/dserve.exe?dsqIni=Dserve.ini&dsqApp=Archive&dsqCmd=Show.tcl&dsqDb=Catalog&dsqPos=0&dsqSearch=((AltRefNo='pp/rca')AND(Level='collection'))|title=Wellcome Library Western Manuscripts and Archives catalogue|website=archives.wellcome.ac.uk}}</ref>\n* Sir [[Samuel Bedson|Samuel Phillips Bedson]], FRS  Professor of [[Bacteriology]], [[University of London]]\n* [[Alan Dower Blumlein]], Electronics engineer and inventor\n* [[Peter Crossley-Holland]], Ethnomusicologist and composer\n* [[Robin Gandy]], Mathematician\n* [[Ted Koppel|Edward James Martin Koppel]], British-born American broadcast journalist,\n* [[Alfred Angas Scott|Alfred Angas Scott (1875-1923)]], motorcycle designer, inventor and founder of The Scott Motorcycle Company <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scotttechnicalities.com.au/technicalities/Scott%20eNewsletter/Scott%20eNewsletter%2018.pdf |title=Scott e Newsletter |accessdate=5 October 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Shapiro]], political scientist\n* [[Lytton Strachey]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://search.proquest.com/openview/6f3d89c1b106e348/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=1434|title=REDDIE OF ABBOTSHOLME. - ProQuest|website=search.proquest.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref> British writer and critic\n* Sir [[Alan Muir Wood]], FRS FREng FICE, Civil Engineer\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/ School Website]\n* [http://www.ukboardingschools.com/school/abbotsholme-school.html UK Boarding Schools Guide Profile]\n* [http://www.isc.co.uk/schools/england/derbyshire/uttoxeter/abbotsholme-school Profile] on the [[Independent Schools Council|ISC]] website\n\n{{Schools in Derbyshire}}\n\n[[Category:Round Square schools]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1889]]\n[[Category:Boarding schools in Derbyshire]]\n[[Category:Independent schools in Derbyshire]]\n[[Category:1889 establishments in England]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the defunct Australian school|Abbotsholme College}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox school \n| name          = Abbotsholme School\n| image         = \n| image_size          = \n| coordinates   = {{coord|52.944374|-1.82542|type:edu_region:GB_dim:100|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| motto         = Glad Day Love and Duty\n| established   = 1889\n| closed        = \n| type          = [[Independent school (UK)|Independent]] day and boarding school\n| religious_affiliation      = Christian\n| president     = \n| head_label    = Headmaster\n| head          = Robert Barnes\n| r_head_label  = \n| r_head        = \n| chair_label   = \n| chair         = \n| founder       = Cecil Reddie\n| specialist    = \n| address        = \n| city          = [[Rocester]]\n| county        = [[Derbyshire]]\n| country       = England\n| postcode      = ST14 5BS\n| local_authority           =\n| ofsted        = \n| dfeno         = 830/6005\n| urn           = 113003 \n| staff         = \n| enrolment    = 290~\n| gender        = Coeducational\n| lower_age     = 2\n| upper_age     = 18\n| houses        = \n| colours       = Green, Gold \n{{colour box|#0B6121}}{{colour box|#DBA901}}\n| publication   = \n| free_label_1  = Former pupils\n| free_1        = Old Abbotsholmians\n| free_label_2  = \n| free_2        = \n| free_label_3  = \n| free_3        = \n| website       = http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/\n}}\n\n'''Abbotsholme School''' is a co-educational [[Independent school (UK)|independent]] [[boarding school|boarding]] and [[day school]]. The school is situated on a 140-acre campus on the banks of the [[River Dove, Central England|River Dove]] in [[Derbyshire]], England near the county border and the village of [[Rocester]] in [[Staffordshire]]. It is a member of the [[Society of Headmasters & Headmistresses of Independent Schools|SHHIS]] (Society of Headmasters & Headmistresses of Independent Schools) and is a [[Round Square (educational organisation)|Round Square]] school.\n\n== History ==\n[[File:Adityajit Singh Kang (second from left in red Scholar Blazer & blue Scarf) with Classmates at Abbotsholme School, Rocester, Uttoxeter, Staffordshire, England, UK.jpg|thumb|Exchange student and classmates at Abbotsholme School in 2012]]\nAbbotsholme was founded by Scottish academic and educationist [[Cecil Reddie]]<ref>{{cite web\n |url          = http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/494634/Cecil-Reddie\n |title        = Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica\n |accessdate   = 10 October 2013\n |archive-url  = https://web.archive.org/web/20150610225138/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/494634/Cecil-Reddie\n |archive-date = 2015-06-10\n |url-status     = live\n}}</ref> as an experiment for his progressive educational philosophies and theories.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abbotsholme.com/pdfs/inspection_report.pdf |title=Inspection Report |accessdate=2008-09-01 |publisher=INDEPENDENT SCHOOLS INSPECTORATE |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090320060819/http://www.abbotsholme.com/pdfs/inspection_report.pdf |archive-date=2009-03-20 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Burns|first=R.W.|title=The Life and Times of Alan Dower Blumlein|url=https://books.google.com/?id=B2z2ONO7nBQC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false|publisher=[[Institute of Engineering and Technology|IET]]|year=2000|pages=19|isbn=9780852967737}}</ref> The school, then known \"The New School\", opened to boys aged 10 to 19 in 1889. From the very beginning, the school departed from the structure of the traditional [[Public school (UK)|public school]] in favour of a less rigid environment and more liberal education. [[Top hat]]s and \"[[Eton College|Eton]] collars\" were discarded in favour of a more comfortable and practical uniform, and English, French and German were taught in place of [[Classics]] (Latin and Greek). The fine arts were introduced as core subjects, considered unusual at that time, since music and art were mostly taught at cathedral schools or specialist art institutes. Practical skills such as animal husbandry and carpentry were integrated into the curriculum.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/Abbotsholmes-History|title=Our History|access-date=2012-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120826045726/http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/Abbotsholmes-History|archive-date=2012-08-26|url-status=dead}}</ref> It has been coeducational since 1969; girls now make up over one third of overall pupil numbers. The school was bought by Chinese company, Achieve Education, in 2017.\n\n==Notable former pupils==\n{{see also|Category:People educated at Abbotsholme School}}\n* [[Roger Altounyan]] \u2013 physician and pharmacologist who pioneered the use of [[sodium cromoglycate]] as a preventative for asthma<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.wellcomelibrary.org/2012/06/if-not-duffers-wont-drown/|title='If not duffers won't drown'|access-date=2016-11-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121171323/http://blog.wellcomelibrary.org/2012/06/if-not-duffers-wont-drown/|archive-date=2016-11-21|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.wellcome.ac.uk/DServe/dserve.exe?dsqIni=Dserve.ini&dsqApp=Archive&dsqCmd=Show.tcl&dsqDb=Catalog&dsqPos=0&dsqSearch=((AltRefNo='pp/rca')AND(Level='collection'))|title=Wellcome Library Western Manuscripts and Archives catalogue|website=archives.wellcome.ac.uk}}</ref>\n* Sir [[Samuel Bedson|Samuel Phillips Bedson]], FRS  Professor of [[Bacteriology]], [[University of London]]\n* [[Alan Dower Blumlein]], Electronics engineer and inventor\n* [[Peter Crossley-Holland]], Ethnomusicologist and composer\n* [[Robin Gandy]], Mathematician\n* [[Ted Koppel|Edward James Martin Koppel]], British-born American broadcast journalist,\n* [[Alfred Angas Scott|Alfred Angas Scott (1875-1923)]], motorcycle designer, inventor and founder of The Scott Motorcycle Company <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scotttechnicalities.com.au/technicalities/Scott%20eNewsletter/Scott%20eNewsletter%2018.pdf |title=Scott e Newsletter |accessdate=5 October 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Ian Shapiro]], political scientist\n* [[Lytton Strachey]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://search.proquest.com/openview/6f3d89c1b106e348/1?pq-origsite=gscholar&cbl=1434|title=REDDIE OF ABBOTSHOLME. - ProQuest|website=search.proquest.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref> British writer and critic\n* Sir [[Alan Muir Wood]], FRS FREng FICE, Civil Engineer\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.abbotsholme.co.uk/ School Website]\n* [http://www.ukboardingschools.com/school/abbotsholme-school.html UK Boarding Schools Guide Profile]\n* [http://www.isc.co.uk/schools/england/derbyshire/uttoxeter/abbotsholme-school Profile] on the [[Independent Schools Council|ISC]] website\n\n{{Schools in Derbyshire}}\n\n[[Category:Round Square schools]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1889]]\n[[Category:Boarding schools in Derbyshire]]\n[[Category:Independent schools in Derbyshire]]\n[[Category:1889 establishments in England]]\n", "name_user": "Deaglanmcardleabbotsholme", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abbotsholme_School"}
{"title_page": "Grozilovo", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Grozilovo\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vologodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|45|N|39|07|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vologodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Grozilovo''' ({{lang-ru|\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Novlenskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vologodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 10 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vologda]] is 88 km, to Novlenskoye is 19 km. Shchetinino, Minino, Selishcha, Duplino, Stepanovo, Roslovskoye, Otekleyevo are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vologodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologodsky District]]\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name          = Grozilovo\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|image_skyline          = \n|image_caption          = \n|pushpin_map            = Russia Vologda Oblast#Russia\n|pushpin_label_position = \n|pushpin_mapsize        =\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = [[Russia]]\n|subdivision_type1      = [[List of regions of Russia|Region]] \n|subdivision_name1      = [[Vologda Oblast]]\n|subdivision_type2      = [[Counties of Russia|County]] \n|subdivision_name2      = \n|subdivision_type3      = [[Districts of Russia|District]] \n|subdivision_name3      = [[Vologodsky District]]\n|subdivision_type4      = [[List of municipalities of Russia|Municipality]]\n|subdivision_name4      = \n|timezone1              = \n|utc_offset1            = +3:00\n|timezone1_DST          = \n|utc_offset1_DST        = \n|postal_code_type       = \n|postal_code            = \n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_footnotes    = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|59|45|N|39|07|E|display=inline}}<ref>[https://mapdata.ru/vologodskaya-oblast/vologodskiy-rayon/ \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0440\u0430\u0439\u043e\u043d\u0430 \u0412\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438]</ref>\n}}\n'''Grozilovo''' ({{lang-ru|\u0413\u0440\u043e\u0437\u0438\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043e}}) is a [[types of inhabited localities in Russia|rural locality]] (a [[Village#Russia|village]]) in Novlenskoye Rural Settlement, [[Vologodsky District]], [[Vologda Oblast]], Russia. The population was 10 as of 2002.<ref>\u0414\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0438\u0441\u0438 2002 \u0433\u043e\u0434\u0430: \u0442\u0430\u0431\u043b\u0438\u0446\u0430 2\u0421. \u041c.: \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u0430\u044f \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0436\u0431\u0430 \u0433\u043e\u0441\u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0438, 2004.</ref>\n\n== Geography ==\nThe distance to [[Vologda]] is 88 km, to Novlenskoye is 19 km. Shchetinino, Minino, Selishcha, Duplino, Stepanovo, Roslovskoye, Otekleyevo are the nearest rural localities.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Rural localities in Vologodsky District}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologda Oblast]]\n[[Category:Rural localities in Vologodsky District]]\n\n\n{{VologdaOblast-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Wagino 20100516", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grozilovo"}
{"title_page": "Nirvana in Fire", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = Nirvana in Fire\n| image                = Nirvana In Fire (Lang Ya Bang) official poster.jpg\n| caption              = ''Nirvana in Fire'' promotional image\n| show_name_2          =  \n| native_name    =  {{Infobox name module\n| Chinese= \u7405\u740a\u699c\n| pinyin = L\u00e1ngy\u00e1 B\u01ceng\n}}\n| genre                = [[Wuxia]]<br/>[[historical drama|Historical]]<br/>[[Political drama|Politics]]\n|creator               = \n|based_on              = ''{{ill|Lang Ya Bang|zh|\u746f\u740a\u699c (\u5c0f\u8bf4)}}'' by Hai Yan\n| writer               = Hai Yan\n| director             = Kong Sheng<br/>Li Xue \n| starring             = [[Hu Ge]]<br />[[Liu Tao]]<br />[[Wang Kai (actor)|Wang Kai]]\n| theme_music_composer = Meng Ke\n| opentheme            = ''Main Theme''<br/>by Meng Ke\n| endtheme             = ''When the Wind Blows''<br/>by [[Hu Ge]]\n| composer             = \n| country              = [[China]]\n| language             = [[Chinese language|Mandarin Chinese]]\n| num_episodes         = 54 \n| list_episodes        = List of Nirvana in Fire episodes \n| executive_producer   =  \n| producer             = Hou Hongliang\n| location             = [[Hengdian World Studios]]<br />Xiang Shan Studios \n| cinematography       = Sun Molong\n| editor               = Li Gang\n| camera               = [[Multiple-camera setup]]\n| runtime              = 40-45 minutes\n| company              = Shandong Film & TV Production Co.,Ltd.<br/>Daylight Entertainment (Dongyang) Television Ltd.\n| distributor          = Li Huabing\n| picture_format       = [[1080i]] ([[HDTV]])\n| audio_format         = [[Stereo]]\n| first_run            = \n| first_aired          = September 19, 2015\n| last_aired           = October 15, 2015\n| preceded_by          = \n| followed_by          =''[[Nirvana in Fire II: The Wind Blows in Chang Lin]]'' \n| related              = \n| website              = \n| channel              = [[Dragon TV]]<br/>[[Beijing TV]]\n}}\n'''''Nirvana in Fire''''' ({{Zh|c = \u7405\u740a\u699c|s = |t = |p = L\u00e1ngy\u00e1 B\u01ceng}}) is a 2015 [[Chinese language|Chinese]] [[historical drama]] based on Hai Yan's {{ill|Lang Ya Bang|zh|\u746f\u740a\u699c (\u5c0f\u8bf4)}}. It was directed by Kong Sheng and Li Xue, and stars [[Hu Ge]], [[Liu Tao]] and [[Wang Kai (actor)|Wang Kai]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Mei Changsu/Su Zhe/Lin Shu|Mei Changsu]], [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Princess Mu Nihuang|Princess Nihuang]] and [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyan, Prince Jing|Prince Jing]]. The series tells the story of Lin Shu, who, under the alias Mei Changsu, enters the capital of Liang to seek justice for a conspiracy that labeled his family as traitors 12 years before.<ref>{{Cite web|title = ::\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u62cd\u6444\u5236\u4f5c\u5907\u6848\u516c\u793a\u8868::|url = http://dsj.sarft.gov.cn/tims/site/views/applications/note/noteTable.shanty?id=014203370aff33b54028e4a241a5e58a|website = dsj.sarft.gov.cn|accessdate = 2015-12-23}}</ref> It originally aired 2 episodes daily on [[Beijing Media Network|Beijing TV]] and [[Dragon Television|Dragon TV]], Monday through Sunday from 19:30 to 21:00, from September 19 to October 15, 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b9\u6708\u63ed\u699c \u53e4\u88c5\u7537\u795e\u80e1\u6b4c\u518d\u6218\"\u6c5f\u6e56\"--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51\u5a31\u4e50\u9891\u9053--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|url = http://ent.people.com.cn/n/2015/0828/c1012-27528656.html|website = [[People's Daily]]|accessdate = 2015-12-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u5b9a\u68639\u670818\u65e5 \u5317\u4eac\u4e1c\u65b9\u4e24\u661f\u8054\u64ad|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2015-05-20/doc-iavxeafs7795151.shtml|website = [[Sina Corp|Sina]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16}}</ref>\n\nThe drama was a commercial and critical success, surpassing ten million views by its second day,<ref>{{cite news|title = Online viewership surpasses ten million in two days|url = http://ent.people.com.cn/n/2015/0922/c1012-27620411.html|accessdate = 2015-10-25|date = September 22, 2015|website = ent.people.com.cn}}</ref> and receiving a total number of daily internet views on [[iQiyi]] of over 3.3 billion by the end of the series.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|title = Chinese TV phenomenon aims for South Korea success|url = http://gbtimes.com/china/chinese-tv-phenomenon-aims-south-korea-success|website = [[Global Times]]|publisher = |accessdate = 2015-12-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web| url = http://www.scmp.com/tech/enterprises/article/1886420/legend-miyue-smashes-online-video-viewing-record-china-700-million| title = Legend of Miyue smashes online video viewing record in China with 700 million hits in 24 hours as country sees industry take off| last = He| first = Huifeng| date = December 3, 2015| website = [[South China Morning Post]]| access-date = 2016-02-26}}</ref> ''Nirvana in Fire'' was considered a [[social media]] phenomenon, generating 3.55 billion posts on [[Sina Weibo]] <nowiki/>that praised its characters and story-line.<ref>{{Cite web|title = 2015 Sees Continued Boom of Online Literature Turned TV Dramas|url = http://en.yibada.com/articles/93929/20151211/2015-sees-continued-boom-online-literature-turned-tv-dramas.htm|website = Yibada|date = December 11, 2016|accessdate = 2016-01-02|first = EL|last = Borromeo}}</ref> As of December 2016, it has a total view of 13 billion views as reported by VLinkage.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.avirtualvoyage.net/2016/12/vlinkage-reveals-16-cdramas-with-over-10-billions-online-views.html|title=Vlinkage reveals 16 Cdramas with over 10 Billions Online Views|work=AVirtualVoyage|publisher=Vlinkage|date=December 11, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe drama was also one of the recipients of the Outstanding Television Drama Award at the [[Flying Apsaras Awards]], the highest government honor given for outstanding achievement in the television industry.<ref>{{Cite web|title = China's Flying Apsaras Awards nominees announced|url = http://china.org.cn/video/2015-12/25/content_37395893.htm|website = China.org.cn|accessdate = 2015-12-28|date = December 25, 2015}}</ref> Kong Sheng also won the Outstanding Director Award for his work in ''Nirvana in Fire''.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|title = \u7b2c\u4e09\u5341\u5c4a\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u98de\u5929\u5956\u5165\u56f4\u540d\u5355\u516c\u5e03|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/2015-12-23/doc-ifxmxxsr3560636.shtml|website =[[Sina Corp|Sina]]|accessdate = 2015-12-28}}</ref> In 2016, [[State Administration of Press, Publication, Radio, Film and Television|SARFT]] recognized the series as one of the top 20 most outstanding dramas of the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2016-02-17/doc-ifxpmpqt1376789.shtml|title=\u5e7f\u7535\u300a2015\u4e2d\u56fd\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u9009\u96c6\u300b\u80e1\u6b4c\u4e09\u5267\u5165\u9009|date=February 17, 2016|website=[[Sina Corp|Sina]]|access-date=2016-03-15}}</ref> It was also nominated for the [[Magnolia Award for Best Television Series]] at the 22nd [[Shanghai Television Festival]].<ref name=\":3\" />\n\nIts sequel, ''[[Nirvana in Fire II: The Wind Blows in Chang Lin]]'', began airing in December 2017.\n\n== Synopsis ==\n{{Main|List of Nirvana in Fire episodes}}\nIn sixth-century China, there was a war between feudal [[Northern Wei]] and [[Liang dynasty|Southern Liang]] dynasties. The Liang commander general, Lin Xie, his 19-year-old son, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Mei Changsu/Su Zhe/Lin Shu|Lin Shu]], and the Chiyan Army defeated hostile Wei forces. However, when the Chiyan were weakened from the battle, they were massacred under the [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Emperor of Liang|Emperor]]'s orders. Unknown to the king, the Chiyan were framed by political rivals, who claimed that they were conspiring a rebellion with the then-crown prince, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyu, Prince Qi|Prince Qi]]. As a result, Prince Qi and members of the Lin manor were also unjustly executed. Qi's mother, Consort Chen, and Lin Shu's mother, sister of the king, committed suicide.\n\nLin Shu survived but was poisoned by the Poison of the Bitter Flame as the result of the fighting. To save his life, the master of Langya Hall, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Lin Chen|Lin Chen]], gave him a treatment that ultimately led to Lin Shu's altered appearance and weakened state. For the next twelve years, he establishes the Jiang Zuo Alliance and becomes chief of the pugilist world as Mei Changsu. Lin Shu takes the opportunity to return to the capital during the fight for the throne between [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jinghuan, Prince Yu|Prince Yu]] and [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingxuan, Crown Prince Xian|Prince Xian]]. He uses this opportunity to gain a position that will allow him to restore his family's innocence as well as secretly help his childhood friend, the unfavored [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyan, Prince Jing|Prince Jing]], become Emperor.\n\nUnder the disguise of Su Zhe, Lin Shu becomes a strategist, who supports Prince Yu on the surface. He helps him take down the Crown Prince and his most powerful ally, [[Marquess]] [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xie Yu|Xie Yu]]. Secretly, he is assisting Prince Jing as he rises in power and favor. While also investigating Xie Yu, Lin Shu discovers new details of Xie Yu's involvement in the Chiyan conspiracy. He realizes that [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xia Jiang|Xia Jiang]], head of the Xuan Jing Bureau, was the instigator of the case that ultimately framed Prince Qi and the Chiyan Army so that Prince Qi could not dissolve the Xuan Jing Bureau when he becomes emperor.\n\nAfter the Crown Prince falls from grace, Prince Yu and his own strategist, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Qin Ban Ruo|Qin Banruo]], become suspicious of Mei Changsu after they saw that Prince Jing was becoming more and more powerful in the royal court. Although he was advised to stop advancing for the throne, Prince Yu forms an alliance with Xia Jiang, who agrees to help him become emperor to prevent the Chiyan case from being re-investigated under Prince Jing, for fear that the prince would try to uncover Xia's lies. Despite their plan to use the capture of ex-Chiyan general, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Wei Zheng, Li Gang and Zhen Ping|Wei Zheng]], to create bad blood between Prince Jing and his father, the prisoner's escape leads them to fail, with Xia Jiang arrested and Xuan Jing Bureau seized and searched. Prince Yu's previous crimes were also revealed, causing him to be demoted and put under house arrest. Although all seems lost for Prince Yu, Qin Banruo persuades him to hold a rebellion and take the throne by force while his father is away at the Spring Hunt with Prince Jing and Mei Changsu.\n\nDespite arriving with a more powerful army compared to the small number of soldiers stationed at the Hunt, Prince Yu fails to destroy his father. Therefore, he commits suicide in prison. Meanwhile, Xia Jiang had escaped prison during the rebellion attempt and deduces that Mei Changsu is Lin Shu. He attempts to regain the Emperor's trust by uncovering Mei's identity and accusing Prince Jing to have conspired with the strategist as the reason for the prince's quick rise in power. Although the Emperor imprisoned Xia Jiang again, he attempts to kill Mei Changsu to prevent a further mess for Prince Jing. He is stopped by Prince Jing, as the prince did not want people to die for him.\n\nTogether, Prince Jing and Mei Changsu make a plan to try and bring up the Chiyan case to the Emperor. At the Emperor's birthday celebration, the Prince has [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Grand Princess Li Yang|Grand Princess Liyang]], the wife of Xie Yu, bring up the case in front of the emperor with evidence from Xie Yu's confession. The Emperor is angered by the sudden accusation of his own mistakes, but he is powerless to stop it, as the whole court pleads for him to reopen the Chiyan case. After a final confrontation with Mei Changsu (now revealed to him as Lin Shu), the Emperor finally agrees to reopen the case. After investigating, he pronounces Prince Qi, Lin Xie, Lin Shu, and the entire Chiyan army innocent.\n\nShortly after his wish is fulfilled, Mei Changsu receives news that the [[Northern Wei]] forces has come to take advantage of the political unrest in the royal court by invading Da Liang. Mei Changsu decides to help drive off the Southern forces (Da Yu), as it would be what Lin Shu would have done. He takes a herbal medication made by Lin Chen to give himself strength for three months, so he may lead the Liang forces to defeat the enemy. He ultimately did not return to the capital. Several years later, Prince Jing becomes the new Emperor. When Commander [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Meng Zhi|Meng Zhi]] requests for Emperor Jing to name the newly merged militia, he names it \"Chang Lin\" army, in honor of Lin Shu and Mei Chang Su.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u7405\u740a\u699c\uff082015\u5e74\u80e1\u6b4c\u53e4\u88c5\u4f20\u5947\u5267\uff09_\u767e\u5ea6\u767e\u79d1|url = http://baike.baidu.com/subview/1562685/12093740.htm|website = [[Baidu|Baike Baidu]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n{{Main|List of Nirvana in Fire characters}}\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n'''Main cast'''\n*[[Hu Ge]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Mei Changsu/Su Zhe/Lin Shu|Mei Changsu/Su Zhe/Lin Shu]]\n:*[[Zhang Zhehan]] as teenage Lin Shu\n*[[Liu Tao]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Princess Mu Nihuang|Princess Mu Nihuang]]\n:*Pan Xiao Yang as teenage Nihuang\n* [[Wang Kai (actor)|Wang Kai]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyan, Prince Jing|Xiao Jingyan, Prince Jing]]\n'''Jiang Zuo Alliance'''\n*[[Leo Wu]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Fei Liu|Fei Liu]]\n* Zhou Qi Qi as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Gong Yu and Sir Shisan|Gong Yu]]\n* [[Jin Dong]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Lin Chen|Lin Chen]]\n* Wang Hong as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Wei Zheng, Li Gang and Zhen Ping|Li Gang]]\n* Zhao Yi Long as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Wei Zheng, Li Gang and Zhen Ping|Zhen Ping]]\n* Zhong Wei Hua as Physician Yan\n* Wei Wei as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Tong Lu|Tong Lu]]\n* Shan Ying Zhe as Nie Feng\n* Li Shuai as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Wei Zheng, Li Gang and Zhen Ping|Wei Zheng]]\n* Liu Hong Yuan as Han Li\n* Liu Hong Chao as An Rui\n* Gong Fang Min as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Gong Yu and Sir Shisan|Sir Shisan]]\n'''Others'''\n* [[Wang Ou]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Qin Ban Ruo|Qin Banruo]]\n* Jin Feng as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Jun Niang|Junniang]]\n* Wang Chen Yi Xian as Princess Xuanji\n* Fu Tao as Lu Yuan\n* Yan Jie as Zhuo Qingyao\n* Liu Hao Ming as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Zhuo Dingfeng|Zhuo Dingfeng]]\n* [[Qiao Xin]] as Yuwen Nian\n* Guo Dong Yue as Prince Yuwen Xuan\n* Liu Shu Chen as Madam Zhuo\n* Sun Meng Jia as Xiaoxin\n{{col-2}}\n\n'''Liang Royal Family'''\n* [[Victor Huang]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jinghuan, Prince Yu|Xiao Jinghuan, Prince Yu]]\n* Liu Min Tao as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Consort Jing|Concubine Jing]]\n* Ding Yong Dai as the [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Emperor of Liang|Emperor]]\n* Gao Xin as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingxuan, Crown Prince Xian|Xiao Jingxuan, Crown Prince Xian]]\n* Zhang Yan Yan as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Grand Princess Li Yang|Grand Princess Liyang]]\n* Fang Xiao Li as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Empress Yan and Noble Consort Yue|Empress Yan]]\n* Yang Yu Ting as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Empress Yan and Noble Consort Yue|Noble Consort Yue]]\n* Ningwen Tong as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Prince Ji|Prince Ji]]\n* Ji Chen as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingyu, Prince Qi|Xiao Jingyu, Prince Qi]]\n* Zheng Yu Zhi as Grand Empress Dowager\n* Lina Chen as Consort Hui\n\n'''Royal Court and nobles'''\n* Chen Long as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Meng Zhi|Meng Zhi]]\n* Tan Xi He as Gao Zhan\n* Zhang Ling Xin as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xia Dong|Xia Dong]]\n* Wang Yong Quan as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xia Jiang|Xia Jiang]]\n* [[Wang Jinsong]] as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Yan Que, Marquise Yan|Marquis Yan Que]]\n* Cheng Hao Feng as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xiao Jingrui|Xiao Jingrui]]\n* Guo Xiao Ran as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Yan Yujin|Yan Yujin]]\n* [[Liu Yijun (actor)|Liu Yijun]]  as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xie Yu|Marquis Xie Yu]]\n* Zhang Xiao Qian as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Mu Qing|Mu Qing]]\n* Kuang Mu Ye as Xie Bi\n* Sui Yu Meng as Xie Qi\n* Zheng Sheng Li as General Lin Xie\n* Feng Hui as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Shen Zhui and Cai Quan|Shen Zhui]]\n* Lee Duo as [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Shen Zhui and Cai Quan|Cai Quan]]\n* Liu Guanlin as Xia Chun\n* Sui Shuyang as Xia Qiu\n* [[Zhang Yujian]] as Lie Zhanying\n* Liu Yang as General Qi Meng\n* Zhang Ju Ming as Xiao Tingsheng \n{{col-end}}\n\n== Production ==\n\n=== Background ===\nIn April 2011, Shandong Television Media Group acquired the film adaption rights for the popular 2007 internet novel written by Hai Yan, ''Lang Ya Bang'', which has been called the \"Chinese version of ''[[The Count of Monte Cristo]]''\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u5f71\u89c6\u6539\u7f16\u6743\u786e\u5b9a_\u7f51\u6613\u5a31\u4e50|url = http://ent.163.com/11/0415/01/71L402BD00032DGD.html|website = [[NetEase]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = April 15, 2015|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151122173620/http://ent.163.com/11/0415/01/71L402BD00032DGD.html|archive-date = November 22, 2015|url-status = dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = How Small Screen Heroes Shape Public Debate on Social Justice|url = http://english.caixin.com/2016-01-23/100902823.html|website = english.caixin.com|access-date = 2016-01-29|date = January 23, 2016|first = Qin|last = Mi}}</ref> Producer Hou Hongliang thought that the original novel conveyed the kind of emotion people are most attracted to, the characters' inner strength and revenge, and therefore decided to adapt the novel for television.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u5236\u7247\u4eba\u4faf\u9e3f\u4eae\u4e13\u8bbf_\u7535\u89c6\u5267\u7405\u740a\u699c_\u65b0\u6d6a\u535a\u5ba2|url = http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_45a0de950101fnq8.html?tj=ent|website =[[Sina Corp|Sina Blog]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16}}</ref> The series' overall investment of the costume drama was more than one hundred million yuan, and the director and producer strived for majestic atmosphere with poetic, beautiful images.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\uff1a\u9c81\u5267\u518d\u6dfb\u529b\u4f5c \u6253\u9020\u53e4\u88c5\u60c5\u4e49\u5de8\u5236|url = http://news.sina.com.cn/c/2014-03-15/200929716289.shtml|website =[[Sina Corp|Sina]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = March 15, 2014}}</ref>\n\nDirector Kong Sheng and Hou Hongliang, who have been friends for 20 years, have worked together in ''The Age of Iron'', ''[[Chuang Guandong]]'', ''All Quiet in Peking'', and ''The Line'' and other television productions.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u5267\u7248\u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u7b79\u62cd \u7531\u767d\u7389\u5170\u5956\u6700\u4f73\u5bfc\u6f14\u5b54\u7b19\u6267\u5bfc-\u65b0\u534e\u7f51|url = http://news.xinhuanet.com/ent/2013-11/04/c_125646597.htm|website =[[Xinhua News Agency]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = November 4, 2013}}</ref> The original author, Hai Yan, said that she had no intention to make ''Lang Ya Bang'' into a television series, but Shandong producers encouraged her to do so, while also offering her the role as the drama's screenwriter, despite the fact that she had no such experience. The writing of the script lasted from mid-October 2012 to April 2013. Hai Yan stated that the story \"will certainly be changed in details, but the framework, the characters and the plot is set to no major changes..., we are most concerned about the preservation of the outcome of Mei Changsu. I think, according to my personal standards, 80% of the script is original.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://weibo.com/1212182847/AE9RbpfPe|title = \u63a2\u73ed\u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u6743\u8c0b\u4e4b\u6597\uff0c\u60c5\u4e49\u4e4b\u6218|date = April 14, 2015|accessdate = 2015-05-15|website =[[Sina Weibo|Weibo]] |publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Hou Hongliang said in earlier interviews that the series highlights justice, patriotism and brotherhood.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|title = \u2018Nirvana in Fire\u2019 is a big hit on the small screen|url = http://m.chinadaily.com.cn/en/2015-11/12/content_22435469.htm|website =[[China Daily]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = November 12, 2015}}</ref>\n[[File:Hengdian World Studios 008.jpg|thumb|251x251px|Set at [[Hengdian World Studios]] used as part of [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Xie Yu|Marquise Xie Yu]]'s manor]]\nAlthough it was not intended for any historical backstory corresponding to a certain dynasty, for the sake of the costumes, props and set designs, ''Nirvana in Fire'' was set during the [[Northern and Southern dynasties]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u5173\u6ce8\u5ea6\u6301\u7eed\u5347\u6e29 \u5267\u7ec4\u7b79\u5907\u8fdb\u5c55\u6709\u5e8f_\u7f51\u6613\u5a31\u4e50|url = http://ent.163.com/13/1211/11/9FQE33MJ00031GVS.html|website = [[NetEase]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = December 11, 2013}}</ref> Hou Hongliang stated that \"characters will be relatively free flowing, in line with ancient individuals that are typically imagined.\"<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u5efa\u7ec4 \u949f\u6c49\u826f\u80e1\u6b4c\u5510\u5ae3\u6709\u671b\u53c2\u6f14|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/w/2013-10-25/11484030603.shtml|website = [[Sina Corp|Sina]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16|date = October 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\nNotable members of production include Sun Molong and Li Gang as directors of photography, Meng Ke as head composer, Jiang Guangtuo in charge of the [[Dubbing (filmmaking)|dubbing]], Liu Jie as the stunt director, Wang Huo, Su Zhiyong and Shao Changyong as the artistic designers, Ru Mei Qi as the fashion designer, Kong Gezi in charge of [[visual effects]], and Liu Lei in charge of sound recordings.<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/micro-reading/dzh/2014-01-06/content_10970730.html\n| title = \u7405\u740a\u699c\u5267\u60c5\u89e3\u6790 \u624b\u7ed8\u6f14\u5458\u7167\u66dd\u5149\n| date = January 6, 2014\n| website = [[China Daily]]\n| access-date = 2016-02-28\n}}</ref>\n\n=== Shooting ===\nIt was announced in mid-December 2013 that [[Hu Ge]], [[Victor Huang]], [[Wang Kai (actor)|Wang Kai]] and Chen Long would act as Mei Changsu, Prince Yu, Prince Jing and Meng Zhi in the drama.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2013-12-10/10114057723.shtml?bsh_bid=322784179|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u66dd\u5149\u9635\u5bb9 \u80e1\u6b4c\u738b\u51ef\u9ec4\u7ef4\u5fb7\u52a0\u76df|date = December 10, 2013|accessdate = 2015-12-13|website = [[Sina Corp|Sina]]|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> When the cast and crew were formally established, they officially started shooting on February 12, 2014 at [[Hengdian World Studios]]. The shooting was separated into three groups, shooting at Heng Dian, Xiang Shan studios, western Zhe Jiang grasslands, [[Wuxi]] and others.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u5267\u7248\u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u4e09\u5e74\u78e8\u4e00\u5251 \u4eca\u65e5\u6a2a\u5e97\u63ed\u699c\u5f00\u673a_\u5a31\u4e50_\u817e\u8baf\u7f51|url = http://ent.qq.com/a/20140213/014661.htm|website = [[Tencent]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16}}</ref> [[Location shooting]] was finished in June 2014, and entered [[post-production]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u66dd\u5267\u60c5\u7247\u82b1 \u80e1\u6b4c\u6f14\u9634\u8c0b\u7b97\u8ba1|url = http://ent.sina.com.cn/v/m/2014-06-05/10174153436.shtml|website = [[Sina Corp|Sina]]|accessdate = 2015-12-16}}</ref>\n\n==Original Soundtrack ==\n\"When the Wind Rises\", sung by [[Hu Ge]], is the main theme song of the drama, with \"Faded Beauty\" and \"Loyal Blood Forever Runs Red\" acting as insert songs. The rest of the tracks are instrumental and performed by various artists. \"When the Wind Rises\" was composed by Meng Ke, with lyrics written by Hai Yan.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u4e3b\u9898\u66f2MV\u66dd\u5149 \u80e1\u6b4c\u503e\u60c5\u6f14\u7ece\u8d64\u5b50\u4e4b\u5fc3_\u5a31\u4e50_\u817e\u8baf\u7f51|url = http://ent.qq.com/a/20150820/015459.htm|website = [[Tencent]]|accessdate = 2016-01-09|date = August 20, 2015}}</ref> \"Faded Beauty\" was composed by Zhao Jialin and written by Yuan Liang. \"Loyal Blood Forever Runs Red\" was composed by Yu Haihang and written by Qing Yan and Bing Feng.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u63a8\u300a\u8d64\u8840\u957f\u6bb7\u300bMV \u738b\u51ef\u8be0\u91ca\u60c5\u4e49\u5343\u79cb_\u5a31\u4e50_\u817e\u8baf\u7f51|url = http://ent.qq.com/a/20150730/018100.htm|website =[[Tencent]]|accessdate = 2016-01-09|date = July 30, 2015}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| total_length  = 61:33+\n| title1 = ''When the Wind Blows'' (\u98ce\u8d77\u65f6)\n| note1 = [[Hu Ge]]\n| length1= 3:12\n| title2 = ''Faded Beauty'' (\u7ea2\u989c\u65e7)\n| length2 =3:45\n| note2 = [[Liu Tao]]\n| title3 = ''Loyal Blood Forever Runs Red'' (\u8d64\u8840\u957f\u6bb7)\n| length3 = 4:46\n| note3 = [[Wang Kai (actor)|Wang Kai]]\n| title4 = ''March'' (\u884c\u8fdb)\n| length4 = 1:18\n| title5 = ''Tense Stalemate'' (\u7d27\u5f20\u5bf9\u5cd9)\n| length5 = 1:06\n| title6 = ''Expansive'' (\u5f00\u9614)\n| length6 = 1:26\n| title7 = ''Strategise'' (\u8c0b\u5212)\n| length7 = 3:57\n| title8 = ''Interlude'' (\u63d2\u66f2)\n| length8 = 2:14\n| title9 = ''Deception'' (\u8be1\u8ba1)\n| length9 = 2:53\n| title10 = ''Emotions'' (\u60c5\u611f) ([[Bawu]] ver.)\n| length10 = 1:36\n| title11 = ''Emotions 2''\n| length11 = 3:43\n| title12 = ''Emotions 3''\n| length12 = 1:52\n| title13 =  ''Conversation'' (\u8c08\u8bdd)\n| length13 = 4:26\n| title14 = ''Suspense'' (\u60ac\u7591)\n| length14 = 2:01\n| title15 = ''Suspense'' ([[Xiao (flute)|Xiao]] ver.)\n| length15 = 1:36\n| title16 = ''Chasing'' (\u8ffd\u8d76)\n| length16 = 1:13\n| title17 = ''Last Judgement'' (\u6700\u540e\u7684\u5ba1\u5224)\n| length17 = 2:36\n| title18 = ''Main Theme'' (\u4e3b\u9898)\n| length18 = 4:06\n| title19 = ''Main Theme 2'' (\u4e3b\u98982)\n| length19 = 3:21\n| title20 = ''Battle situation'' (\u6218\u4e89\u573a\u9762)\n| length20 = 2:31\n| title21 = ''Battle situation 2'' (\u6218\u4e89\u573a\u97622)\n| length21 = 1:21\n| title22 = ''Race Against Time'' (\u4e89\u5206\u593a\u79d2)\n| length22 = 1:36\n| title23 = ''Ambience'' (\u80cc\u666f\u6c1b\u56f4\u97f3\u4e50)\n| length23 = 2:11\n| title24 = ''Suspense 3'' (\u60ac\u75913)\n| length24 = 1:10\n| title25 = ''Emotional Music'' (\u60c5\u7eea\u97f3\u4e50)\n| length25 = 0:41\n| title26 = ''Women's Theme'' (\u5973\u4e3b\u9898)\n| length26 = 1:15\n| title27 = ''Humour, Lively'' (\u5e7d\u9ed8\uff0c\u6b22\u5feb)\n| length27 = 1:05\n| title28 = ''Humour 2'' (\u5e7d\u9ed82)\n| length28 = 0:47\n| title29 = ''Longing'' (\u601d\u5ff5)\n| length29 = 1:00\n| title30 = ''Stand-off between father and son'' (\u7236\u5b50\u62d4\u5251)\n| length30 = 2:13\n}}\n\n== Reception ==\nThe series garnered critical acclaim, with many positive reviews and discussions surfacing on the internet through [[Sina Weibo|Weibo]].<ref name=global /> It topped viewership ratings in fifty cities in China and enjoyed high audience ratings in Taiwan.<ref>{{Cite web|title = TV Drama 'Nirvana in Fire' Enjoys Popularity at Home and Abroad - All China Women's Federation|url = http://www.womenofchina.cn/womenofchina/html1/news/culture_news/1511/1382-1.htm|website = Women of China|accessdate = 2016-01-02|date = November 16, 2015|first = Kate|last = Wu}}</ref> The drama is also immensely popular overseas and has been translated to and dubbed in different languages.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/culture/2015-11/16/content_22465502_2.htm|title=How 'Nirvana in Fire' became a hit abroad|date=November 16, 2015|work=[[China Daily]]}}</ref>\n\nXu Ming of ''[[Global Times]]'' praised the storyline, acting and cinematography of the series, stating that it was a quality example of Chinese [[historical drama|period dramas]], despite pointing out several flaws in the plot, such as Mei Changsu being \"too capable\" compared to the other characters.<ref name=global>{{cite news|title = Lang Ya Bang winning success with sincerity|url = http://www.globaltimes.cn/content/946888.shtml|accessdate = 2015-10-25|date = October 13, 2015|website = [[Global Times]]}}</ref> [[Douban]] gave the drama 9.2 out of 10,<ref name=\":0\" /> with the series being dubbed as \"China's ''[[Game of Thrones]]''\" due to its popularity.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/culture/2015-09/15/content_21851534.htm|title=Nirvana in Fire set to thrill viewers|date=September 15, 2015|work=[[China Daily]]}}</ref>\n\nCertain scenic spots in China have also been changed to ''Langya Ge'' (Langya Hall) to attract tourists. Although [[Anhui]], [[Jiangsu]] and [[Shandong|Shandong province]] all claim to be where the drama is set, Hai Yan clarified that the setting was fictitious.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Chinese Scenic Spots Renamed After Popular TV Series Nirvana in Fire (National)|url = https://beijingtoday.com.cn/2015/11/chinese-scenic-spots-renamed-after-popular-tv-series-nirvana-in-fire/|website = BEIJING TODAY|accessdate = 2015-12-28|language = en-US|first = Peng Qian|last = Shu|date = November 20, 2015|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180819011151/https://beijingtoday.com.cn/2015/11/chinese-scenic-spots-renamed-after-popular-tv-series-nirvana-in-fire/|archive-date = August 19, 2018|url-status = dead}}</ref> The publications for the web novel was highly anticipated, with the number of pre-orders reaching new highs.<ref>{{Cite web|title = \u7405\u740a\u699c\u5f97\u5929\u4e0b \u535a\u5ba2\u4f86\u9810\u8cfc\u9031\u903e500\u5957 {{!}} \u8ca1\u7d93 {{!}} \u4e2d\u592e\u793e\u5373\u6642\u65b0\u805e CNA NEWS|url = http://www.cna.com.tw/news/afe/201601110279-1.aspx|website = www.cna.com.tw|access-date = 2016-01-11}}</ref> At the 2015 Big Data Index of Culture and Entertainment Industry Conference, the character, [[List of Nirvana in Fire characters#Mei Changsu/Lin Shu/Su Zhe|Mei Changsu]], was named the year's \"most talked-about television character (online)\".<ref>{{Cite web|title = 2015\u6587\u5a31\u5927\u6570\u636e\u516c\u5e03 \u300a\u5927\u5723\u5f52\u6765\u300b\u300a\u7405\u740a\u699c\u300b\u6210\u8d62\u5bb6--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51\u5a31\u4e50\u9891\u9053--\u4eba\u6c11\u7f51|url = http://ent.people.com.cn/n1/2016/0116/c1012-28060497.html|website = [[People's Daily]]|access-date = 2016-01-20|date = January 16, 2016}}</ref> The success of the adaption ushered in the original book's sales increase by more than 3,300 percent on [[Amazon.com|Amazon]].<ref>{{Cite web\n| url = http://en.yibada.com/articles/102723/20160207/adaptations-bring-more-readers-source-novels.htm\n| title = Adaptations Bring More Readers to Source Novels\n| date = February 7, 2016 \n| website = Yibada\n| access-date = 2016-02-26\n}}</ref>\n\n== Ratings ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable mw-collapsible jquery-tablesorter\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n| colspan=\"11\" |'''[[China]] Dragon TV / Beijing TV premiere ratings (CSM50)'''<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.tvtv.hk/archives/category/dianshiju|title = TV rating archives for television|date = |accessdate = 2015-12-13|website = tvtv.hk|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''Episodes'''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''Broadcast date'''\n| colspan=\"3\" |'''[[Dragon Television|Dragon TV]]'''\n| colspan=\"3\" |'''[[Beijing Media Network|Beijing TV]]'''\n|-\n|'''Ratings (%)'''\n|'''Audience share (%)'''\n|'''Rankings'''\n|'''Ratings (%)'''\n|'''Audience share (%)'''\n|'''Rankings'''\n|-\n|1-2\n|September 19, 2015\n|'''<span style=\"color:blue\">0.482</span>'''\n|'''<span style=color:blue>1.38</span>'''\n|10\n|0.574\n|1.64\n|6\n|-\n|3-4\n|September 20, 2015\n|0.587\n|1.65\n|8\n|0.594\n|1.67\n|7\n|-\n|5-6\n|September 21, 2015\n|0.517\n|1.48\n|10\n|0.573\n|1.64\n|6\n|-\n|7-8\n|September 22, 2015\n|0.544\n|1.56\n|9\n|0.529\n|1.52\n|10\n|-\n|9-10\n|September 23, 2015\n|0.690\n|1.98\n|4\n|0.603\n|1.73\n|8\n|-\n|11-12\n|September 24, 2015\n|0.749\n|2.11\n|4\n|0.531\n|1.50\n|9\n|-\n|13-14\n|September 25, 2015\n|0.694\n|2.00\n|4\n|0.661\n|1.92\n|5\n|-\n|15-16\n|September 26, 2015\n|0.739\n|2.07\n|4\n|0.649\n|1.82\n|5\n|-\n|17-18\n|September 27, 2015\n|0.730\n|1.99\n|3\n|'''<span style=\"color:blue\">0.523</span>'''\n|'''<span style=color:blue>1.43</span>'''\n|5\n|-\n|19-20\n|September 28, 2015\n|0.655\n|1.82\n|3\n|0.604\n|1.68\n|4\n|-\n|21-22\n|September 29, 2015\n|0.727\n|1.97\n|4\n|0.833\n|2.26\n|3\n|-\n|23-24\n|September 30, 2015\n|0.751\n|1.99\n|4\n|0.832\n|2.21\n|3\n|-\n|25-26\n|October 1, 2015\n|0.671\n|1.97\n|4\n|0.825\n|2.41\n|3\n|-\n|27-28\n|October 2, 2015\n|0.702\n|2.11\n|4\n|0.831\n|2.50\n|2\n|-\n|29-30\n|October 3, 2015\n|0.715\n|2.08\n|4\n|0.720\n|2.10\n|3\n|-\n|31-32\n|October 4, 2015\n|0.865\n|2.47\n|3\n|0.755\n|2.15\n|4\n|-\n|33-34\n|October 5, 2015\n|0.794\n|2.24\n|5\n|0.869\n|2.45\n|4\n|-\n|35-36\n|October 6, 2015\n|0.928\n|2.55\n|5\n|0.977\n|2.69\n|4\n|-\n|37-38\n|October 7, 2015\n|0.897\n|2.35\n|3\n|1.044\n|2.73\n|1\n|-\n|39-40\n|October 8, 2015\n|1.081\n|2.99\n|2\n|0.691\n|1.91\n|6\n|-\n|41-42\n|October 9, 2015\n|1.0